58 /// Helper enum to classify mask value.
59 enum class MaskFormat {
60  AllTrue = 0,
61  AllFalse = 1,
62  Unknown = 2,
63 };
64 
65 /// Helper method to classify a mask value. Currently, the method
66 /// looks "under the hood" of a constant value with dense attributes
67 /// and a constant mask operation (since the client may be called at
68 /// various stages during progressive lowering).
69 static MaskFormat getMaskFormat(Value mask) {
70  if (auto c = mask.getDefiningOp<arith::ConstantOp>()) {
71  // Inspect constant dense values. We count up for bits that
72  // are set, count down for bits that are cleared, and bail
73  // when a mix is detected.
74  if (auto denseElts = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseIntElementsAttr>(c.getValue())) {
75  int64_t val = 0;
76  for (bool b : denseElts.getValues<bool>())
77  if (b && val >= 0)
78  val++;
79  else if (!b && val <= 0)
80  val--;
81  else
82  return MaskFormat::Unknown;
83  if (val > 0)
84  return MaskFormat::AllTrue;
85  if (val < 0)
86  return MaskFormat::AllFalse;
87  }
88  } else if (auto m = mask.getDefiningOp<ConstantMaskOp>()) {
89  // Inspect constant mask index. If the index exceeds the
90  // dimension size, all bits are set. If the index is zero
91  // or less, no bits are set.
92  ArrayRef<int64_t> masks = m.getMaskDimSizes();
93  auto shape = m.getType().getShape();
94  bool allTrue = true;
95  bool allFalse = true;
96  for (auto [maskIdx, dimSize] : llvm::zip_equal(masks, shape)) {
97  if (maskIdx < dimSize)
98  allTrue = false;
99  if (maskIdx > 0)
100  allFalse = false;
101  }
102  if (allTrue)
103  return MaskFormat::AllTrue;
104  if (allFalse)
105  return MaskFormat::AllFalse;
106  } else if (auto m = mask.getDefiningOp<CreateMaskOp>()) {
107  // Finds all-false create_masks. An all-true create_mask requires all
108  // dims to be constants, so that'll be folded to a constant_mask, then
109  // detected in the constant_mask case.
110  auto maskOperands = m.getOperands();
111  for (Value operand : maskOperands) {
112  if (auto constantOp = operand.getDefiningOp<arith::ConstantOp>()) {
113  int64_t dimSize =
114  llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(constantOp.getValue()).getInt();
115  if (dimSize <= 0)
116  return MaskFormat::AllFalse;
117  }
118  }
119  return MaskFormat::Unknown;
120  }
121  return MaskFormat::Unknown;
122 }

130 // Helper for verifying combining kinds in contractions and reductions.
131 static bool isSupportedCombiningKind(CombiningKind combiningKind,
132  Type elementType) {
133  switch (combiningKind) {
134  case CombiningKind::ADD:
135  case CombiningKind::MUL:
136  return elementType.isIntOrIndexOrFloat();
137  case CombiningKind::MINUI:
138  case CombiningKind::MINSI:
139  case CombiningKind::MAXUI:
140  case CombiningKind::MAXSI:
141  case CombiningKind::AND:
142  case CombiningKind::OR:
143  case CombiningKind::XOR:
144  return elementType.isIntOrIndex();
145  case CombiningKind::MINNUMF:
146  case CombiningKind::MAXNUMF:
147  case CombiningKind::MINIMUMF:
148  case CombiningKind::MAXIMUMF:
149  return llvm::isa<FloatType>(elementType);
150  }
151  return false;
152 }

154 /// Returns the effective rank of the vector to read/write for Xfer Ops
155 ///
156 /// When the element type of the shaped type is _a scalar_, this will simply
157 /// return the rank of the vector ( the result for xfer_read or the value to
158 /// store for xfer_write).
159 ///
160 /// When the element type of the base shaped type is _a vector_, returns the
161 /// difference between the original vector type and the element type of the
162 /// shaped type.
163 ///
164 /// EXAMPLE 1 (element type is _a scalar_):
165 /// - shapedType = tensor<10x20xf32>, vectorType = vector<2x4xf32>
166 /// - shapedType.getElementType() = f32 (rank 0)
167 /// - vectorType.getRank() = 2
168 /// - Result = 2 - 0 = 2
169 ///
170 /// EXAMPLE 2 (element type is _a vector_):
171 /// - shapedType = tensor<10xvector<20xf32>>, vectorType = vector<20xf32>
172 /// - shapedType.getElementType() = vector<20xf32> (rank 1)
173 /// - vectorType.getRank() = 1
174 /// - Result = 1 - 1 = 0
175 ///
176 /// This is used to determine the number of minor dimensions for identity maps
177 /// in vector transfer Ops.
178 static unsigned getEffectiveVectorRankForXferOp(ShapedType shapedType,
179  VectorType vectorType) {
180  unsigned elementVectorRank = 0;
181  VectorType elementVectorType =
182  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(shapedType.getElementType());
183  if (elementVectorType)
184  elementVectorRank += elementVectorType.getRank();
185  return vectorType.getRank() - elementVectorRank;
186 }
187 
188 AffineMap mlir::vector::getTransferMinorIdentityMap(ShapedType shapedType,
189  VectorType vectorType) {
190  // 0-d transfers are to/from tensor<t>/memref<t> and vector<1xt>.
191  // TODO: replace once we have 0-d vectors.
192  if (shapedType.getRank() == 0 &&
193  vectorType.getShape() == ArrayRef<int64_t>{1})
194  return AffineMap::get(
195  /*numDims=*/0, /*numSymbols=*/0,
196  getAffineConstantExpr(0, shapedType.getContext()));
197  return AffineMap::getMinorIdentityMap(
198  shapedType.getRank(),
199  getEffectiveVectorRankForXferOp(shapedType, vectorType),
200  shapedType.getContext());
201 }

203 /// Check if `write` is of a constant splat and the masked `read` is padded with
204 /// the same splat value -- meaning it could be the same value as the initial
205 /// constant splat.
206 static bool isSplatWriteConsistentWithMaskedRead(vector::TransferWriteOp write,
207  vector::TransferReadOp read) {
208  auto readMask = read.getMask();
209  auto writeMask = write.getMask();
210  // Check if the masks are consistent. The splat value could be the same if the
211  // read is masked (and padded with the splat value), and the write is unmasked
212  // or has the same mask. Note this does not allow the case where the write is
213  // masked and the read is unmasked, as then the read could be of more elements
214  // than the write (which may not be the same value).
215  bool couldBeSameSplat = readMask && (!writeMask || writeMask == readMask);
216  if (!couldBeSameSplat)
217  return false;
218  // Check for constant splat (as the source of the write).
219  DenseElementsAttr splatAttr;
220  if (!matchPattern(write.getVector(),
221  m_Constant<DenseElementsAttr>(&splatAttr)) ||
222  !splatAttr.isSplat()) {
223  return false;
224  }
225  // The padding of the read and the constant splat value must be the same.
226  Attribute padAttr;
227  if (!matchPattern(read.getPadding(), m_Constant(&padAttr)))
228  return false;
229  return padAttr == splatAttr.getSplatValue<Attribute>();
230 }

232 bool mlir::vector::checkSameValueRAW(vector::TransferWriteOp defWrite,
233  vector::TransferReadOp read) {
234  return !defWrite.hasOutOfBoundsDim() &&
235  defWrite.getIndices() == read.getIndices() &&
236  defWrite.getVectorType() == read.getVectorType() &&
237  defWrite.getPermutationMap() == read.getPermutationMap() &&
238  ((!defWrite.getMask() && !read.getMask()) ||
239  isSplatWriteConsistentWithMaskedRead(defWrite, read));
240 }
241 
242 bool mlir::vector::checkSameValueWAW(vector::TransferWriteOp write,
243  vector::TransferWriteOp priorWrite) {
244  return priorWrite.getIndices() == write.getIndices() &&
245  priorWrite.getMask() == write.getMask() &&
246  priorWrite.getVectorType() == write.getVectorType() &&
247  priorWrite.getPermutationMap() == write.getPermutationMap();
248 }

250 bool mlir::vector::isDisjointTransferIndices(
251  VectorTransferOpInterface transferA, VectorTransferOpInterface transferB,
252  bool testDynamicValueUsingBounds) {
253  // For simplicity only look at transfer of same type.
254  if (transferA.getVectorType() != transferB.getVectorType())
255  return false;
256  unsigned rankOffset = transferA.getLeadingShapedRank();
257  for (unsigned i = 0, e = transferA.getIndices().size(); i < e; i++) {
258  Value indexA = transferA.getIndices()[i];
259  Value indexB = transferB.getIndices()[i];
260  std::optional<int64_t> cstIndexA = getConstantIntValue(indexA);
261  std::optional<int64_t> cstIndexB = getConstantIntValue(indexB);
262 
263  if (i < rankOffset) {
264  // For leading dimensions, if we can prove that index are different we
265  // know we are accessing disjoint slices.
266  if (cstIndexA.has_value() && cstIndexB.has_value()) {
267  if (*cstIndexA != *cstIndexB)
268  return true;
269  continue;
270  }
271  if (testDynamicValueUsingBounds) {
272  // First try to see if we can fully compose and simplify the affine
273  // expression as a fast track.
274  FailureOr<uint64_t> delta =
275  affine::fullyComposeAndComputeConstantDelta(indexA, indexB);
276  if (succeeded(delta) && *delta != 0)
277  return true;
278 
279  FailureOr<bool> testEqual =
280  ValueBoundsConstraintSet::areEqual(indexA, indexB);
281  if (succeeded(testEqual) && !testEqual.value())
282  return true;
283  }
284  } else {
285  // For this dimension, we slice a part of the memref we need to make sure
286  // the intervals accessed don't overlap.
287  int64_t vectorDim = transferA.getVectorType().getDimSize(i - rankOffset);
288  if (cstIndexA.has_value() && cstIndexB.has_value()) {
289  int64_t distance = std::abs(*cstIndexA - *cstIndexB);
290  if (distance >= vectorDim)
291  return true;
292  continue;
293  }
294  if (testDynamicValueUsingBounds) {
295  // First try to see if we can fully compose and simplify the affine
296  // expression as a fast track.
297  FailureOr<int64_t> delta =
298  affine::fullyComposeAndComputeConstantDelta(indexA, indexB);
299  if (succeeded(delta) && std::abs(*delta) >= vectorDim)
300  return true;
301 
302  FailureOr<int64_t> computeDelta =
303  ValueBoundsConstraintSet::computeConstantDelta(indexA, indexB);
304  if (succeeded(computeDelta)) {
305  if (std::abs(computeDelta.value()) >= vectorDim)
306  return true;
307  }
308  }
309  }
310  }
311  return false;
312 }
313 
314 bool mlir::vector::isDisjointTransferSet(VectorTransferOpInterface transferA,
315  VectorTransferOpInterface transferB,
316  bool testDynamicValueUsingBounds) {
317  if (transferA.getBase() != transferB.getBase())
318  return false;
319  return isDisjointTransferIndices(transferA, transferB,
320  testDynamicValueUsingBounds);
321 }

323 // Helper to iterate over n-D vector slice elements. Calculate the next
324 // `position` in the n-D vector of size `shape`, applying an offset `offsets`.
325 // Modifies the `position` in place. Returns a failure when `position` becomes
326 // the end position.
327 static LogicalResult incSlicePosition(MutableArrayRef<int64_t> position,
328  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape,
329  ArrayRef<int64_t> offsets) {
330  for (auto [posInDim, dimSize, offsetInDim] :
331  llvm::reverse(llvm::zip_equal(position, shape, offsets))) {
332  ++posInDim;
333  if (posInDim < dimSize + offsetInDim)
334  return success();
335 
336  // Carry the overflow to the next loop iteration.
337  posInDim = offsetInDim;
338  }
339 
340  return failure();
341 }

343 /// Returns the integer numbers in `values`. `values` are expected to be
344 /// constant operations.
345 SmallVector<int64_t> vector::getAsIntegers(ArrayRef<Value> values) {
346  SmallVector<int64_t> ints;
347  llvm::transform(values, std::back_inserter(ints), [](Value value) {
348  auto constOp = value.getDefiningOp<arith::ConstantIndexOp>();
349  assert(constOp && "Unexpected non-constant index");
350  return constOp.value();
351  });
352  return ints;
353 }
354 
355 /// Returns the integer numbers in `foldResults`. `foldResults` are expected to
356 /// be constant operations.
357 SmallVector<int64_t> vector::getAsIntegers(ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> foldResults) {
358  SmallVector<int64_t> ints;
359  llvm::transform(
360  foldResults, std::back_inserter(ints), [](OpFoldResult foldResult) {
361  assert(isa<Attribute>(foldResult) && "Unexpected non-constant index");
362  return cast<IntegerAttr>(cast<Attribute>(foldResult)).getInt();
363  });
364  return ints;
365 }
366 
367 /// Convert `foldResults` into Values. Integer attributes are converted to
368 /// constant op.
369 SmallVector<Value> vector::getAsValues(OpBuilder &builder, Location loc,
370  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> foldResults) {
371  SmallVector<Value> values;
372  llvm::transform(foldResults, std::back_inserter(values),
373  [&](OpFoldResult foldResult) {
374  if (auto attr = dyn_cast<Attribute>(foldResult))
375  return arith::ConstantIndexOp::create(
376  builder, loc, cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt())
377  .getResult();
378 
379  return cast<Value>(foldResult);
380  });
381  return values;
382 }

384 std::optional<int64_t> vector::getConstantVscaleMultiplier(Value value) {
385  if (value.getDefiningOp<vector::VectorScaleOp>())
386  return 1;
387  auto mul = value.getDefiningOp<arith::MulIOp>();
388  if (!mul)
389  return {};
390  auto lhs = mul.getLhs();
391  auto rhs = mul.getRhs();
392  if (lhs.getDefiningOp<vector::VectorScaleOp>())
393  return getConstantIntValue(rhs);
394  if (rhs.getDefiningOp<vector::VectorScaleOp>())
395  return getConstantIntValue(lhs);
396  return {};
397 }

399 /// Converts numeric attributes to the expected type. Supports
400 /// integer-to-integer and float-to-integer conversions. Returns the original
401 /// attribute if no conversion is needed or supported.
402 static Attribute convertNumericAttr(Attribute attr, Type expectedType) {
403  // Integer-to-integer conversion
404  if (auto intAttr = dyn_cast<IntegerAttr>(attr)) {
405  if (auto intType = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(expectedType)) {
406  if (intAttr.getType() != expectedType)
407  return IntegerAttr::get(expectedType, intAttr.getInt());
408  }
409  return attr;
410  }
411 
412  // Float-to-integer bitcast (preserves bit representation)
413  if (auto floatAttr = dyn_cast<FloatAttr>(attr)) {
414  auto intType = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(expectedType);
415  if (!intType)
416  return attr;
417 
418  APFloat floatVal = floatAttr.getValue();
419  APInt intVal = floatVal.bitcastToAPInt();
420  return IntegerAttr::get(expectedType, intVal);
421  }
422 
423  return attr;
424 }

469 void VectorDialect::initialize() {
470  addAttributes<
471 #define GET_ATTRDEF_LIST
472 #include "mlir/Dialect/Vector/IR/VectorAttributes.cpp.inc"
473  >();
474 
475  addOperations<
476 #define GET_OP_LIST
477 #include "mlir/Dialect/Vector/IR/VectorOps.cpp.inc"
478  >();
479 
480  addInterfaces<VectorInlinerInterface>();
481 
482  declarePromisedInterfaces<bufferization::BufferizableOpInterface,
483  TransferReadOp, TransferWriteOp, GatherOp, MaskOp,
484  YieldOp>();
485  declarePromisedInterfaces<SubsetOpInterface, TransferReadOp,
486  TransferWriteOp>();
487  declarePromisedInterface<SubsetExtractionOpInterface, TransferReadOp>();
488  declarePromisedInterface<SubsetInsertionOpInterface, TransferWriteOp>();
489  declarePromisedInterface<ConvertToLLVMPatternInterface, VectorDialect>();
490 }

516 void vector::MultiDimReductionOp::build(OpBuilder &builder,
517  OperationState &result, Value source,
518  Value acc, ArrayRef<bool> reductionMask,
519  CombiningKind kind) {
520  SmallVector<int64_t> reductionDims;
521  for (const auto &en : llvm::enumerate(reductionMask))
522  if (en.value())
523  reductionDims.push_back(en.index());
524  build(builder, result, kind, source, acc, reductionDims);
525 }
526 
527 OpFoldResult MultiDimReductionOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
528  // Single parallel dim, this is a noop.
529  if (getSourceVectorType().getRank() == 1 && !isReducedDim(0))
530  return getSource();
531  return {};
532 }

534 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>>
535 MultiDimReductionOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
536  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getSourceVectorType().getShape());
537 }
538 
539 LogicalResult MultiDimReductionOp::verify() {
540  SmallVector<int64_t> targetShape;
541  SmallVector<bool> scalableDims;
542  Type inferredReturnType;
543  auto sourceScalableDims = getSourceVectorType().getScalableDims();
544  for (auto [dimIdx, dimSize] :
545  llvm::enumerate(getSourceVectorType().getShape()))
546  if (!llvm::any_of(getReductionDims(),
547  [dimIdx = dimIdx](int64_t reductionDimIdx) {
548  return reductionDimIdx == static_cast<int64_t>(dimIdx);
549  })) {
550  targetShape.push_back(dimSize);
551  scalableDims.push_back(sourceScalableDims[dimIdx]);
552  }
553  // TODO: update to also allow 0-d vectors when available.
554  if (targetShape.empty())
555  inferredReturnType = getSourceVectorType().getElementType();
556  else
557  inferredReturnType = VectorType::get(
558  targetShape, getSourceVectorType().getElementType(), scalableDims);
559  if (getType() != inferredReturnType)
560  return emitOpError() << "destination type " << getType()
561  << " is incompatible with source type "
562  << getSourceVectorType();
563 
564  return success();
565 }
566 
567 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation.
568 Type MultiDimReductionOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
569  auto vecType = getSourceVectorType();
570  return VectorType::get(vecType.getShape(),
571  IntegerType::get(vecType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
572  vecType.getScalableDims());
573 }

575 namespace {
576 // Only unit dimensions that are being reduced are folded. If the dimension is
577 // unit, but not reduced, it is not folded, thereby keeping the output type the
578 // same. If not all dimensions which are reduced are of unit dimension, this
579 // transformation does nothing. This is just a generalization of
580 // ElideSingleElementReduction for ReduceOp.
581 struct ElideUnitDimsInMultiDimReduction
582  : public OpRewritePattern<MultiDimReductionOp> {
583  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
584 
585  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(MultiDimReductionOp reductionOp,
586  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
587  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape = reductionOp.getSourceVectorType().getShape();
588  for (const auto &dim : enumerate(shape)) {
589  if (reductionOp.isReducedDim(dim.index()) && dim.value() != 1)
590  return failure();
591  }
592 
593  // Vector mask setup.
594  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(rewriter);
595  Operation *rootOp;
596  Value mask;
597  if (reductionOp.isMasked()) {
598  rewriter.setInsertionPoint(reductionOp.getMaskingOp());
599  rootOp = reductionOp.getMaskingOp();
600  mask = reductionOp.getMaskingOp().getMask();
601  } else {
602  rootOp = reductionOp;
603  }
604 
605  Location loc = reductionOp.getLoc();
606  Value acc = reductionOp.getAcc();
607  Value cast;
608  if (auto dstVecType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(reductionOp.getDestType())) {
609  if (mask) {
610  VectorType newMaskType =
611  VectorType::get(dstVecType.getShape(), rewriter.getI1Type(),
612  dstVecType.getScalableDims());
613  mask = vector::ShapeCastOp::create(rewriter, loc, newMaskType, mask);
614  }
615  cast = vector::ShapeCastOp::create(
616  rewriter, loc, reductionOp.getDestType(), reductionOp.getSource());
617  } else {
618  // This means we are reducing all the dimensions, and all reduction
619  // dimensions are of size 1. So a simple extraction would do.
620  if (mask)
621  mask = vector::ExtractOp::create(rewriter, loc, mask);
622  cast = vector::ExtractOp::create(rewriter, loc, reductionOp.getSource());
623  }
624 
625  Value result =
626  vector::makeArithReduction(rewriter, loc, reductionOp.getKind(), acc,
627  cast, /*fastmath=*/nullptr, mask);
628  rewriter.replaceOp(rootOp, result);
629  return success();
630  }
631 };
632 } // namespace
633 
634 void MultiDimReductionOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(
635  RewritePatternSet &results, MLIRContext *context) {
636  results.add<ElideUnitDimsInMultiDimReduction>(context);
637 }

657 LogicalResult ReductionOp::verify() {
658  // Verify for 0-D and 1-D vector.
659  int64_t rank = getSourceVectorType().getRank();
660  if (rank > 1)
661  return emitOpError("unsupported reduction rank: ") << rank;
662 
663  // Verify supported reduction kind.
664  Type eltType = getDest().getType();
665  if (!isSupportedCombiningKind(getKind(), eltType))
666  return emitOpError("unsupported reduction type '")
667  << eltType << "' for kind '" << stringifyCombiningKind(getKind())
668  << "'";
669 
670  return success();
671 }

675 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation.
676 Type ReductionOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
677  auto vecType = getSourceVectorType();
678  return VectorType::get(vecType.getShape(),
679  IntegerType::get(vecType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
680  vecType.getScalableDims());
681 }
682 
683 Value mlir::vector::getVectorReductionOp(arith::AtomicRMWKind op,
684  OpBuilder &builder, Location loc,
685  Value vector) {
686  switch (op) {
687  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::addf:
688  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::addi:
689  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
690  CombiningKind::ADD, vector);
691  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::mulf:
692  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::muli:
693  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
694  CombiningKind::MUL, vector);
695  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::minimumf:
696  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
697  CombiningKind::MINIMUMF, vector);
698  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::mins:
699  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
700  CombiningKind::MINSI, vector);
701  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::minu:
702  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
703  CombiningKind::MINUI, vector);
704  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::maximumf:
705  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
706  CombiningKind::MAXIMUMF, vector);
707  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::maxs:
708  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
709  CombiningKind::MAXSI, vector);
710  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::maxu:
711  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
712  CombiningKind::MAXUI, vector);
713  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::andi:
714  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
715  CombiningKind::AND, vector);
716  case arith::AtomicRMWKind::ori:
717  return vector::ReductionOp::create(builder, vector.getLoc(),
718  CombiningKind::OR, vector);
719  // TODO: Add remaining reduction operations.
720  default:
721  (void)emitOptionalError(loc, "Reduction operation type not supported");
722  break;
723  }
724  return nullptr;
725 }
726 
727 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>> ReductionOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
728  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getSourceVectorType().getShape());
729 }

731 namespace {
732 struct ElideSingleElementReduction : public OpRewritePattern<ReductionOp> {
733  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
734 
735  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ReductionOp reductionOp,
736  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
737  // Vector mask setup.
738  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(rewriter);
739  auto maskableOp =
740  cast<vector::MaskableOpInterface>(reductionOp.getOperation());
741  Operation *rootOp;
742  Value mask;
743  if (maskableOp.isMasked()) {
744  rewriter.setInsertionPoint(maskableOp.getMaskingOp());
745  rootOp = maskableOp.getMaskingOp();
746  mask = maskableOp.getMaskingOp().getMask();
747  } else {
748  rootOp = reductionOp;
749  }
750 
751  auto vectorType = reductionOp.getSourceVectorType();
752  if (vectorType.getRank() != 0 && vectorType.getDimSize(0) != 1)
753  return failure();
754 
755  Location loc = reductionOp.getLoc();
756  if (mask)
757  mask = ExtractOp::create(rewriter, loc, mask);
758  Value result = ExtractOp::create(rewriter, loc, reductionOp.getVector());
759 
760  if (Value acc = reductionOp.getAcc())
761  result = vector::makeArithReduction(rewriter, loc, reductionOp.getKind(),
762  result, acc,
763  reductionOp.getFastmathAttr(), mask);
764 
765  rewriter.replaceOp(rootOp, result);
766  return success();
767  }
768 };
769 } // namespace
770 
771 void ReductionOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
772  MLIRContext *context) {
773  results.add<ElideSingleElementReduction>(context);
774 }

780 void vector::ContractionOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
781  Value lhs, Value rhs, Value acc,
782  ArrayRef<ArrayRef<AffineExpr>> indexingExprs,
783  ArrayRef<IteratorType> iteratorTypes) {
784  result.addOperands({lhs, rhs, acc});
785  result.addTypes(acc.getType());
786  result.addAttribute(
787  getIndexingMapsAttrName(result.name),
788  builder.getAffineMapArrayAttr(
789  AffineMap::inferFromExprList(indexingExprs, builder.getContext())));
790  result.addAttribute(
791  getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name),
792  builder.getArrayAttr(llvm::to_vector(llvm::map_range(
793  iteratorTypes, [&](IteratorType t) -> mlir::Attribute {
794  return IteratorTypeAttr::get(builder.getContext(), t);
795  }))));
796 }

803  ContractionOp::getDefaultKind());

806 void vector::ContractionOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
807  Value lhs, Value rhs, Value acc,
808  ArrayAttr indexingMaps,
809  ArrayAttr iteratorTypes, CombiningKind kind) {
810  result.addOperands({lhs, rhs, acc});
811  result.addTypes(acc.getType());
812  result.addAttribute(getIndexingMapsAttrName(result.name), indexingMaps);
813  result.addAttribute(getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name), iteratorTypes);
814  result.addAttribute(getKindAttrName(result.name),
815  CombiningKindAttr::get(builder.getContext(), kind));

817 
818 ParseResult ContractionOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
819  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand lhsInfo;
820  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand rhsInfo;
821  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand accInfo;
822  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 2> masksInfo;
823  SmallVector<Type, 2> types;
824  Type resultType;
825  auto loc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
826  DictionaryAttr dictAttr;
827  // TODO: Unify linalg op attribute parsing.
828  if (parser.parseAttribute(dictAttr) || parser.parseOperand(lhsInfo) ||
829  parser.parseComma() || parser.parseOperand(rhsInfo) ||
830  parser.parseComma() || parser.parseOperand(accInfo) ||
831  parser.parseTrailingOperandList(masksInfo) ||
832  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
833  parser.parseColonTypeList(types) ||
834  parser.parseKeywordType("into", resultType) ||
835  parser.resolveOperand(lhsInfo, types[0], result.operands) ||
836  parser.resolveOperand(rhsInfo, types[1], result.operands) ||
837  parser.resolveOperand(accInfo, resultType, result.operands) ||
838  parser.addTypeToList(resultType, result.types))
839  return failure();
840  result.attributes.append(dictAttr.getValue().begin(),
841  dictAttr.getValue().end());
842 
843  // Convert array of string into an array of IteratyType enums. This is needed,
844  // because tests still use the old format when 'iterator_types' attribute is
845  // represented as an array of strings.
846  // TODO: Remove this conversion once tests are fixed.
847  auto iteratorTypes = dyn_cast_or_null<ArrayAttr>(
848  result.attributes.get(getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name)));
849  if (!iteratorTypes) {
850  return parser.emitError(loc)
851  << "expected " << getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name)
852  << " array attribute";
853  }
854 
855  SmallVector<Attribute> iteratorTypeAttrs;
856 
857  for (StringRef s : iteratorTypes.getAsValueRange<StringAttr>()) {
858  auto maybeIteratorType = symbolizeIteratorType(s);
859  if (!maybeIteratorType.has_value())
860  return parser.emitError(loc) << "unexpected iterator_type (" << s << ")";
861 
862  iteratorTypeAttrs.push_back(
863  IteratorTypeAttr::get(parser.getContext(), maybeIteratorType.value()));
864  }
865  result.attributes.set(getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name),
866  parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(iteratorTypeAttrs));
867 
868  if (!result.attributes.get(getKindAttrName(result.name))) {
869  result.addAttribute(
870  getKindAttrName(result.name),
871  CombiningKindAttr::get(result.getContext(),
872  ContractionOp::getDefaultKind()));
873  }
874  if (masksInfo.empty())
875  return success();
876  if (masksInfo.size() != 2)
877  return parser.emitError(parser.getNameLoc(),
878  "expected zero or exactly 2 vector mask operands");
879  auto lhsType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(types[0]);
880  auto rhsType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(types[1]);
881  auto maskElementType = parser.getBuilder().getI1Type();
882  std::array<VectorType, 2> maskTypes = {
883  VectorType::Builder(lhsType).setElementType(maskElementType),
884  VectorType::Builder(rhsType).setElementType(maskElementType)};
885  if (parser.resolveOperands(masksInfo, maskTypes, loc, result.operands))
886  return failure();
887  return success();
888 }
889 
890 void ContractionOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
891  // TODO: Unify printing code with linalg ops.
892  auto attrNames = getTraitAttrNames();
893  llvm::StringSet<> traitAttrsSet;
894  traitAttrsSet.insert_range(attrNames);
895  SmallVector<NamedAttribute, 8> attrs;
896  for (auto attr : (*this)->getAttrs()) {
897  if (attr.getName() == getIteratorTypesAttrName()) {
898  auto iteratorTypes =
899  llvm::cast<ArrayAttr>(attr.getValue())
900  .getAsValueRange<IteratorTypeAttr, IteratorType>();
901  // Convert IteratorType enums into the string representation. This is
902  // needed, because tests still use the old format when 'iterator_types'
903  // attribute is represented as an array of strings.
904  // TODO: Remove this conversion once tests are fixed.
905  SmallVector<Attribute> iteratorTypeNames = llvm::to_vector(
906  llvm::map_range(iteratorTypes, [&](IteratorType t) -> Attribute {
907  return StringAttr::get(getContext(), stringifyIteratorType(t));
908  }));
909 
910  attrs.emplace_back(getIteratorTypesAttrName(),
911  ArrayAttr::get(getContext(), iteratorTypeNames));
912  } else if (traitAttrsSet.count(attr.getName().strref()) > 0)
913  attrs.push_back(attr);
914  }
915 
916  auto dictAttr = DictionaryAttr::get(getContext(), attrs);
917  p << " " << dictAttr << " " << getLhs() << ", ";
918  p << getRhs() << ", " << getAcc();
919 
920  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs(), attrNames);
921  p << " : " << getLhs().getType() << ", " << getRhs().getType() << " into "
922  << getResultType();
923 }
924 
925 static bool verifyDimMap(VectorType lhsType, VectorType rhsType,
926  const std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>> &map) {
927  for (auto &dimPair : map) {
928  if (dimPair.first < 0 || dimPair.first >= lhsType.getRank() ||
929  dimPair.second < 0 || dimPair.second >= rhsType.getRank() ||
930  lhsType.getDimSize(dimPair.first) != rhsType.getDimSize(dimPair.second))
931  return false;
932  }
933  return true;
934 }
935 
936 static LogicalResult verifyOutputShape(
937  ContractionOp op, VectorType lhsType, VectorType rhsType, Type accType,
938  Type resType,
939  const std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>> &contractingDimMap,
940  const std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>> &batchDimMap) {
941  DenseSet<int64_t> lhsContractingDimSet;
942  DenseSet<int64_t> rhsContractingDimSet;
943  for (auto &dimPair : contractingDimMap) {
944  lhsContractingDimSet.insert(dimPair.first);
945  rhsContractingDimSet.insert(dimPair.second);
946  }
947  DenseSet<int64_t> rhsBatchDimSet(llvm::from_range,
948  llvm::make_second_range(batchDimMap));
949 
950  // Add free and batch dimensions from 'lhsType' to 'expectedResultDims'.
951  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> expectedResultDims;
952  for (int64_t i = 0, e = lhsType.getRank(); i < e; ++i) {
953  if (lhsContractingDimSet.count(i) > 0)
954  continue;
955  expectedResultDims.push_back(lhsType.getDimSize(i));
956  }
957 
958  // Add free dimensions from 'rhsType' to 'expectedResultDims'.
959  for (int64_t i = 0, e = rhsType.getRank(); i < e; ++i) {
960  if (rhsContractingDimSet.count(i) > 0 || rhsBatchDimSet.count(i) > 0)
961  continue;
962  expectedResultDims.push_back(rhsType.getDimSize(i));
963  }
964 
965  // Verify 'expectedResultDims'.
966  if (expectedResultDims.empty()) {
967  // No batch or free dimension implies a scalar result.
968  if (llvm::isa<VectorType>(resType) || llvm::isa<VectorType>(accType))
969  return op.emitOpError("invalid accumulator/result vector shape");
970  } else {
971  // At least one batch or free dimension implies a vector result.
972  auto resVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(resType);
973  auto accVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(accType);
974  if (!resVectorType || !accVectorType)
975  return op.emitOpError("invalid accumulator/result vector shape");
976 
977  // Infer expected result vector type. Lhs + rhs map and lhs + rhs vector
978  // types fully define the result vector type. This assumes the affine maps
979  // are well-formed, which must have been verified already.
980  MLIRContext *ctx = op.getContext();
981  AffineMap lhsMap = op.getIndexingMapsArray()[0];
982  AffineMap rhsMap = op.getIndexingMapsArray()[1];
983  if (getUnusedDimsBitVector({lhsMap, rhsMap}).any())
984  return op.emitOpError(
985  "expected all dimensions to be either a LHS or a RHS dimension");
986  SmallVector<AffineExpr, 4> extents(lhsMap.getNumInputs());
987  for (auto pair :
988  {std::make_pair(lhsType, lhsMap), std::make_pair(rhsType, rhsMap)}) {
989  VectorType v = pair.first;
990  auto map = pair.second;
991  for (unsigned idx = 0, e = v.getRank(); idx < e; ++idx) {
992  unsigned pos = map.getDimPosition(idx);
993  if (!extents[pos])
994  extents[pos] = getAffineConstantExpr(v.getShape()[idx], ctx);
995  }
996  }
997  if (!llvm::all_of(extents, [](AffineExpr e) { return e; }))
998  return op.emitOpError("expected all dimensions to get an extent as "
999  "either a LHS or a RHS dimension");
1000 
1001  AffineMap resMap = op.getIndexingMapsArray()[2];
1002  auto extentsMap = AffineMap::get(/*dimCount=*/extents.size(),
1003  /*symbolCount=*/0, extents, ctx);
1004  // Compose the resMap with the extentsMap, which is a constant map.
1005  AffineMap expectedMap = simplifyAffineMap(resMap.compose(extentsMap));
1006  assert(llvm::all_of(expectedMap.getResults(),
1007  llvm::IsaPred<AffineConstantExpr>) &&
1008  "expected constant extent along all dimensions.");
1009  // Extract the expected shape and build the type.
1010  auto expectedShape = llvm::to_vector<4>(
1011  llvm::map_range(expectedMap.getResults(), [](AffineExpr e) {
1012  return cast<AffineConstantExpr>(e).getValue();
1013  }));
1014  auto expected =
1015  VectorType::get(expectedShape, resVectorType.getElementType(),
1016  resVectorType.getScalableDims());
1017  if (resVectorType != expected || accVectorType != expected)
1018  return op.emitOpError(
1019  "invalid accumulator/result vector shape, expected: ")
1020  << expected;
1021  }
1022  return success();
1023 }
1024 
1025 LogicalResult ContractionOp::verify() {
1026  VectorType lhsType = getLhsType();
1027  VectorType rhsType = getRhsType();
1028  Type accType = getAccType();
1029  Type resType = getResultType();
1030 
1031  if (llvm::isa<IntegerType>(lhsType.getElementType())) {
1032  if (!lhsType.getElementType().isSignlessInteger())
1033  return emitOpError("only supports signless integer types");
1034  }
1035 
1036  // Verify that an indexing map was specified for each vector operand.
1037  if (getIndexingMapsArray().size() != 3)
1038  return emitOpError("expected an indexing map for each vector operand");
1039 
1040  // Verify that each index map has 'numIterators' inputs, no symbols, and
1041  // that the number of map outputs equals the rank of its associated
1042  // vector operand.
1043  unsigned numIterators = getIteratorTypes().getValue().size();
1044  for (const auto &it : llvm::enumerate(getIndexingMapsArray())) {
1045  auto index = it.index();
1046  auto map = it.value();
1047  if (map.getNumSymbols() != 0)
1048  return emitOpError("expected indexing map ")
1049  << index << " to have no symbols";
1050  auto vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(getOperand(index).getType());
1051  unsigned rank = vectorType ? vectorType.getShape().size() : 0;
1052  // Verify that the map has the right number of inputs, outputs, and indices.
1053  // This also correctly accounts for (..) -> () for rank-0 results.
1054  if (map.getNumDims() != numIterators)
1055  return emitOpError("expected indexing map ")
1056  << index << " to have " << numIterators << " number of inputs";
1057  if (map.getNumResults() != rank)
1058  return emitOpError("expected indexing map ")
1059  << index << " to have " << rank << " number of outputs";
1060  if (!map.isProjectedPermutation())
1061  return emitOpError("expected indexing map ")
1062  << index << " to be a projected permutation of its inputs";
1063  }
1064 
1065  auto contractingDimMap = getContractingDimMap();
1066  auto batchDimMap = getBatchDimMap();
1067 
1068  // Verify at least one contracting dimension pair was specified.
1069  if (contractingDimMap.empty())
1070  return emitOpError("expected at least one contracting dimension pair");
1071 
1072  // Verify contracting dimension map was properly constructed.
1073  if (!verifyDimMap(lhsType, rhsType, contractingDimMap))
1074  return emitOpError("invalid contracting dimension map");
1075 
1076  // Verify batch dimension map was properly constructed.
1077  if (!verifyDimMap(lhsType, rhsType, batchDimMap))
1078  return emitOpError("invalid batch dimension map");
1079 
1080  // Verify 'accType' and 'resType' shape.
1081  if (failed(verifyOutputShape(*this, lhsType, rhsType, accType, resType,
1082  contractingDimMap, batchDimMap)))
1083  return failure();
1084 
1085  // Verify supported combining kind.
1086  auto vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(resType);
1087  auto elementType = vectorType ? vectorType.getElementType() : resType;
1088  if (!isSupportedCombiningKind(getKind(), elementType))
1089  return emitOpError("unsupported contraction type");
1090 
1091  // Delayed calling of IndexingMapOpInterface::verifyImpl.
1092  return cast<IndexingMapOpInterface>(this->getOperation()).verifyImpl();
1093 }
1094 
1095 // MaskableOpInterface methods.
1096 
1097 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
1098 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
1099 Type ContractionOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
1100  auto indexingMaps = this->getIndexingMapsArray();
1101  AffineMap lhsIdxMap = indexingMaps[0];
1102  AffineMap rhsIdxMap = indexingMaps[1];
1103  VectorType lhsType = this->getLhsType();
1104  VectorType rhsType = this->getRhsType();
1105 
1106  unsigned numVecDims = lhsIdxMap.getNumDims();
1107  SmallVector<int64_t> maskShape(numVecDims, ShapedType::kDynamic);
1108  SmallVector<bool> maskShapeScalableDims(numVecDims, false);
1109 
1110  // Using the information in the indexing maps, extract the size of each
1111  // dimension in the vector.contract operation from the two input operands.
1112  for (auto [dimIdx, dimSize] : llvm::enumerate(lhsType.getShape())) {
1113  maskShape[lhsIdxMap.getDimPosition(dimIdx)] = dimSize;
1114  maskShapeScalableDims[lhsIdxMap.getDimPosition(dimIdx)] =
1115  lhsType.getScalableDims()[dimIdx];
1116  }
1117  for (auto [dimIdx, dimSize] : llvm::enumerate(rhsType.getShape())) {
1118  maskShape[rhsIdxMap.getDimPosition(dimIdx)] = dimSize;
1119  maskShapeScalableDims[rhsIdxMap.getDimPosition(dimIdx)] =
1120  rhsType.getScalableDims()[dimIdx];
1121  }
1122 
1123  assert(ShapedType::isStaticShape(maskShape) &&
1124  "Mask shape couldn't be computed");
1125 
1126  return VectorType::get(maskShape,
1127  IntegerType::get(lhsType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
1128  maskShapeScalableDims);
1129 }
1130 
1131 SmallVector<StringRef> ContractionOp::getTraitAttrNames() {
1132  return SmallVector<StringRef>{getIndexingMapsAttrName(),
1133  getIteratorTypesAttrName(), getKindAttrName()};
1134 }
1135 
1136 static int64_t getResultIndex(AffineMap map, AffineExpr targetExpr) {
1137  for (int64_t i = 0, e = map.getNumResults(); i < e; ++i)
1138  if (targetExpr == map.getResult(i))
1139  return i;
1140  return -1;
1141 }
1142 
1143 static std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>>
1144 getDimMap(ArrayRef<AffineMap> indexingMaps, ArrayAttr iteratorTypes,
1145  IteratorType targetIteratorType, MLIRContext *context) {
1146  std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>> dimMap;
1147  for (const auto &it : llvm::enumerate(iteratorTypes)) {
1148  auto iteratorType = llvm::cast<IteratorTypeAttr>(it.value()).getValue();
1149  if (iteratorType != targetIteratorType)
1150  continue;
1151  // Search lhs/rhs map results for 'targetExpr'.
1152  auto targetExpr = getAffineDimExpr(it.index(), context);
1153  int64_t lhsDim = getResultIndex(indexingMaps[0], targetExpr);
1154  int64_t rhsDim = getResultIndex(indexingMaps[1], targetExpr);
1155  if (lhsDim >= 0 && rhsDim >= 0)
1156  dimMap.emplace_back(lhsDim, rhsDim);
1157  }
1158  return dimMap;
1159 }
1160 
1161 void ContractionOp::getIterationBounds(
1162  SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &iterationBounds) {
1163  auto lhsShape = getLhsType().getShape();
1164  auto resVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(getResultType());
1165  SmallVector<AffineMap, 4> indexingMaps(getIndexingMapsArray());
1166  for (const auto &it : llvm::enumerate(getIteratorTypes())) {
1167  // Search lhs/rhs map results for 'targetExpr'.
1168  auto targetExpr = getAffineDimExpr(it.index(), getContext());
1169  auto iteratorType = llvm::cast<IteratorTypeAttr>(it.value()).getValue();
1170  if (iteratorType == IteratorType::reduction) {
1171  // Get reduction dim size from lhs shape (same size in rhsShape).
1172  int64_t lhsDimIndex = getResultIndex(indexingMaps[0], targetExpr);
1173  assert(lhsDimIndex >= 0);
1174  iterationBounds.push_back(lhsShape[lhsDimIndex]);
1175  continue;
1176  }
1177  // Get parallel dimension size from result shape.
1178  int64_t resDimIndex = getResultIndex(indexingMaps[2], targetExpr);
1179  assert(resDimIndex >= 0);
1180  assert(resVectorType != nullptr);
1181  iterationBounds.push_back(resVectorType.getShape()[resDimIndex]);
1182  }
1183 }
1184 
1185 void ContractionOp::getIterationIndexMap(
1186  std::vector<DenseMap<int64_t, int64_t>> &iterationIndexMap) {
1187  unsigned numMaps = getIndexingMapsArray().size();
1188  iterationIndexMap.resize(numMaps);
1189  for (const auto &it : llvm::enumerate(getIndexingMapsArray())) {
1190  auto index = it.index();
1191  auto map = it.value();
1192  for (unsigned i = 0, e = map.getNumResults(); i < e; ++i) {
1193  auto dim = cast<AffineDimExpr>(map.getResult(i));
1194  iterationIndexMap[index][dim.getPosition()] = i;
1195  }
1196  }
1197 }
1198 
1199 std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>> ContractionOp::getContractingDimMap() {
1200  SmallVector<AffineMap, 4> indexingMaps(getIndexingMapsArray());
1201  return getDimMap(indexingMaps, getIteratorTypes(), IteratorType::reduction,
1202  getContext());
1203 }
1204 
1205 std::vector<std::pair<int64_t, int64_t>> ContractionOp::getBatchDimMap() {
1206  SmallVector<AffineMap, 4> indexingMaps(getIndexingMapsArray());
1207  return getDimMap(indexingMaps, getIteratorTypes(), IteratorType::parallel,
1208  getContext());
1209 }

1211 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>> ContractionOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
1212  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> shape;
1213  getIterationBounds(shape);
1214  return shape;

1217 /// Return a fused vector::ContractionOp which represents a patterns such as:
1218 ///
1219 /// ```mlir
1220 /// %c0 = vector.constant 0: ...
1221 /// %c = vector.contract %a, %b, %c0: ...
1222 /// %e = add %c, %d: ...
1223 /// ```
1224 ///
1225 /// by:
1226 ///
1227 /// ```mlir
1228 /// %e = vector.contract %a, %b, %d: ...
1229 /// ```
1230 ///
1231 /// Return null if the canonicalization does not apply.
1232 // TODO: This should be a folding of Add into Contract in core but while they
1233 // live in different dialects, it is not possible without unnatural
1234 // dependencies.
1235 template <typename AddOpType>
1236 struct CanonicalizeContractAdd : public OpRewritePattern<AddOpType> {
1237  using OpRewritePattern<AddOpType>::OpRewritePattern;
1238 
1239  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(AddOpType addOp,
1240  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
1241  auto canonicalize = [&](Value maybeContraction,
1242  Value otherOperand) -> vector::ContractionOp {
1243  vector::ContractionOp contractionOp =
1244  dyn_cast_or_null<vector::ContractionOp>(
1245  maybeContraction.getDefiningOp());
1246  if (!contractionOp)
1247  return vector::ContractionOp();
1248  if (auto maybeZero = dyn_cast_or_null<arith::ConstantOp>(
1249  contractionOp.getAcc().getDefiningOp())) {
1250  if (maybeZero.getValue() ==
1251  rewriter.getZeroAttr(contractionOp.getAcc().getType())) {
1252  IRMapping bvm;
1253  bvm.map(contractionOp.getAcc(), otherOperand);
1254  auto newContraction =
1255  cast<vector::ContractionOp>(rewriter.clone(*contractionOp, bvm));
1256  rewriter.replaceOp(addOp, newContraction.getResult());
1257  return newContraction;
1258  }
1259  }
1260  return vector::ContractionOp();
1261  };
1262 
1263  Value a = addOp->getOperand(0), b = addOp->getOperand(1);
1264  vector::ContractionOp contract = canonicalize(a, b);
1265  contract = contract ? contract : canonicalize(b, a);
1266  return contract ? success() : failure();
1267  }
1268 };
1269 
1270 void ContractionOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
1271  MLIRContext *context) {
1272  results.add<CanonicalizeContractAdd<arith::AddIOp>,
1273  CanonicalizeContractAdd<arith::AddFOp>>(context);
1274 }

1276 // Returns `true` if `index` is either within [0, maxIndex) or equal to
1277 // `poisonValue`.
1278 static bool isValidPositiveIndexOrPoison(int64_t index, int64_t poisonValue,
1279  int64_t maxIndex) {
1280  return index == poisonValue || (index >= 0 && index < maxIndex);
1281 }
