1323 LogicalResult
1324 ExtractOp::inferReturnTypes(MLIRContext *, std::optional<Location>,
1325  ExtractOp::Adaptor adaptor,
1326  SmallVectorImpl<Type> &inferredReturnTypes) {
1327  auto vectorType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(adaptor.getSource().getType());
1328  if (static_cast<int64_t>(adaptor.getStaticPosition().size()) ==
1329  vectorType.getRank()) {
1330  inferredReturnTypes.push_back(vectorType.getElementType());
1331  } else {
1332  auto n = std::min<size_t>(adaptor.getStaticPosition().size(),
1333  vectorType.getRank());
1334  inferredReturnTypes.push_back(VectorType::get(
1335  vectorType.getShape().drop_front(n), vectorType.getElementType(),
1336  vectorType.getScalableDims().drop_front(n)));
1337  }
1338  return success();
1339 }
1340 
1341 bool ExtractOp::isCompatibleReturnTypes(TypeRange l, TypeRange r) {
1342  // Allow extracting 1-element vectors instead of scalars.
1343  auto isCompatible = [](TypeRange l, TypeRange r) {
1344  auto vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(l.front());
1345  return vectorType && vectorType.getShape().equals({1}) &&
1346  vectorType.getElementType() == r.front();
1347  };
1348  if (l.size() == 1 && r.size() == 1 &&
1349  (isCompatible(l, r) || isCompatible(r, l)))
1350  return true;
1351  return l == r;
1352 }
1353 
1354 LogicalResult vector::ExtractOp::verify() {
1355  if (auto resTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType()))
1356  if (resTy.getRank() == 0)
1357  return emitError(
1358  "expected a scalar instead of a 0-d vector as the result type");
1359 
1360  // Note: This check must come before getMixedPosition() to prevent a crash.
1361  auto dynamicMarkersCount =
1362  llvm::count_if(getStaticPosition(), ShapedType::isDynamic);
1363  if (static_cast<size_t>(dynamicMarkersCount) != getDynamicPosition().size())
1364  return emitOpError(
1365  "mismatch between dynamic and static positions (kDynamic marker but no "
1366  "corresponding dynamic position) -- this can only happen due to an "
1367  "incorrect fold/rewrite");
1368  auto position = getMixedPosition();
1369  if (position.size() > static_cast<unsigned>(getSourceVectorType().getRank()))
1370  return emitOpError(
1371  "expected position attribute of rank no greater than vector rank");
1372  for (auto [idx, pos] : llvm::enumerate(position)) {
1373  if (auto attr = dyn_cast<Attribute>(pos)) {
1374  int64_t constIdx = cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt();
1375  if (!isValidPositiveIndexOrPoison(
1376  constIdx, kPoisonIndex, getSourceVectorType().getDimSize(idx))) {
1377  return emitOpError("expected position attribute #")
1378  << (idx + 1)
1379  << " to be a non-negative integer smaller than the "
1380  "corresponding vector dimension or poison (-1)";
1381  }
1382  }
1383  }
1384  return success();
1385 }
1386 
1387 template <typename IntType>
1388 static SmallVector<IntType> extractVector(ArrayAttr arrayAttr) {
1389  return llvm::to_vector<4>(llvm::map_range(
1390  arrayAttr.getAsRange<IntegerAttr>(),
1391  [](IntegerAttr attr) { return static_cast<IntType>(attr.getInt()); }));
1392 }
1393 
1394 /// Fold the result of chains of ExtractOp in place by simply concatenating the
1395 /// positions.
1396 static LogicalResult foldExtractOpFromExtractChain(ExtractOp extractOp) {
1397  if (!extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<ExtractOp>())
1398  return failure();
1399 
1400  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1401  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1402  return failure();
1403 
1404  SmallVector<int64_t> globalPosition;
1405  ExtractOp currentOp = extractOp;
1406  ArrayRef<int64_t> extrPos = currentOp.getStaticPosition();
1407  globalPosition.append(extrPos.rbegin(), extrPos.rend());
1408  while (ExtractOp nextOp = currentOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<ExtractOp>()) {
1409  currentOp = nextOp;
1410  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1411  if (currentOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1412  return failure();
1413  ArrayRef<int64_t> extrPos = currentOp.getStaticPosition();
1414  globalPosition.append(extrPos.rbegin(), extrPos.rend());
1415  }
1416  extractOp.setOperand(0, currentOp.getSource());
1417  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
1418  OpBuilder b(extractOp.getContext());
1419  std::reverse(globalPosition.begin(), globalPosition.end());
1420  extractOp.setStaticPosition(globalPosition);
1421  return success();
1422 }
1423 
1424 namespace {
1425 /// Fold an ExtractOp that is fed by a chain of InsertOps and TransposeOps.
1426 /// Walk back a chain of InsertOp/TransposeOp until we hit a match.
1427 /// Compose TransposeOp permutations as we walk back.
1428 /// This helper class keeps an updated extraction position `extractPosition`
1429 /// with extra trailing sentinels.
1430 /// The sentinels encode the internal transposition status of the result vector.
1431 /// As we iterate, extractPosition is permuted and updated.
1432 class ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState {
1433 public:
1434  ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState(ExtractOp e);
1435 
1436  /// Iterate over producing insert and transpose ops until we find a fold.
1437  Value fold();
1438 
1439 private:
1440  /// Return true if the vector at position `a` is contained within the vector
1441  /// at position `b`. Under insert/extract semantics, this is the same as `a`
1442  /// is a prefix of `b`.
1443  template <typename ContainerA, typename ContainerB>
1444  bool isContainedWithin(const ContainerA &a, const ContainerB &b) {
1445  return a.size() <= b.size() &&
1446  std::equal(a.begin(), a.begin() + a.size(), b.begin());
1447  }
1448 
1449  /// Return true if the vector at position `a` intersects the vector at
1450  /// position `b`. Under insert/extract semantics, this is the same as equality
1451  /// of all entries of `a` that are >=0 with the corresponding entries of b.
1452  /// Comparison is on the common prefix (i.e. zip).
1453  template <typename ContainerA, typename ContainerB>
1454  bool intersectsWhereNonNegative(const ContainerA &a, const ContainerB &b) {
1455  for (auto [elemA, elemB] : llvm::zip(a, b)) {
1456  if (elemA < 0 || elemB < 0)
1457  continue;
1458  if (elemA != elemB)
1459  return false;
1460  }
1461  return true;
1462  }
1463 
1464  /// Folding is only possible in the absence of an internal permutation in the
1465  /// result vector.
1466  bool canFold() {
1467  return (sentinels == ArrayRef(extractPosition).drop_front(extractedRank));
1468  }
1469 
1470  // Helper to get the next defining op of interest.
1471  void updateStateForNextIteration(Value v) {
1472  nextInsertOp = v.getDefiningOp<vector::InsertOp>();
1473  nextTransposeOp = v.getDefiningOp<vector::TransposeOp>();
1474  };
1475 
1476  // Case 1. If we hit a transpose, just compose the map and iterate.
1477  // Invariant: insert + transpose do not change rank, we can always compose.
1478  LogicalResult handleTransposeOp();
1479 
1480  // Case 2: the insert position matches extractPosition exactly, early return.
1481  LogicalResult handleInsertOpWithMatchingPos(Value &res);
1482 
1483  /// Case 3: if the insert position is a prefix of extractPosition, extract a
1484  /// portion of the source of the insert.
1485  /// Example:
1486  /// ```
1487  /// %ins = vector.insert %source, %vest[1]: vector<3x4> into vector<2x3x4x5>
1488  /// // extractPosition == [1, 2, 3]
1489  /// %ext = vector.extract %ins[1, 0]: vector<5> from vector<3x4x5>
1490  /// // can fold to vector.extract %source[0, 3]
1491  /// %ext = vector.extract %source[3]: vector<6> from vector<5x6>
1492  /// ```
1493  /// To traverse through %source, we need to set the leading dims to 0 and
1494  /// drop the extra leading dims.
1495  /// This method updates the internal state.
1496  LogicalResult handleInsertOpWithPrefixPos(Value &res);
1497 
1498  /// Try to fold in place to extract(source, extractPosition) and return the
1499  /// folded result. Return null if folding is not possible (e.g. due to an
1500  /// internal transposition in the result).
1501  Value tryToFoldExtractOpInPlace(Value source);
1502 
1503  ExtractOp extractOp;
1504  int64_t vectorRank;
1505  int64_t extractedRank;
1506 
1507  InsertOp nextInsertOp;
1508  TransposeOp nextTransposeOp;
1509 
1510  /// Sentinel values that encode the internal permutation status of the result.
1511  /// They are set to (-1, ... , -k) at the beginning and appended to
1512  /// `extractPosition`.
1513  /// In the end, the tail of `extractPosition` must be exactly `sentinels` to
1514  /// ensure that there is no internal transposition.
1515  /// Internal transposition cannot be accounted for with a folding pattern.
1516  // TODO: We could relax the internal transposition with an extra transposition
1517  // operation in a future canonicalizer.
1518  SmallVector<int64_t> sentinels;
1519  SmallVector<int64_t> extractPosition;
1520 };
1521 } // namespace
1522 
1523 ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState::ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState(
1524  ExtractOp e)
1525  : extractOp(e), vectorRank(extractOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank()),
1526  extractedRank(extractOp.getNumIndices()) {
1527  assert(vectorRank >= extractedRank && "Extracted position overflow");
1528  sentinels.reserve(vectorRank - extractedRank);
1529  for (int64_t i = 0, e = vectorRank - extractedRank; i < e; ++i)
1530  sentinels.push_back(-(i + 1));
1531  extractPosition.assign(extractOp.getStaticPosition().begin(),
1532  extractOp.getStaticPosition().end());
1533  llvm::append_range(extractPosition, sentinels);
1534 }
1535 
1536 // Case 1. If we hit a transpose, just compose the map and iterate.
1537 // Invariant: insert + transpose do not change rank, we can always compose.
1538 LogicalResult ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState::handleTransposeOp() {
1539  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1540  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1541  return failure();
1542 
1543  if (!nextTransposeOp)
1544  return failure();
1545  AffineMap m = inversePermutation(AffineMap::getPermutationMap(
1546  nextTransposeOp.getPermutation(), extractOp.getContext()));
1547  extractPosition = applyPermutationMap(m, ArrayRef(extractPosition));
1548  return success();
1549 }
1550 
1551 // Case 2: the insert position matches extractPosition exactly, early return.
1552 LogicalResult
1553 ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState::handleInsertOpWithMatchingPos(
1554  Value &res) {
1555  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1556  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition() || nextInsertOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1557  return failure();
1558 
1559  ArrayRef<int64_t> insertedPos = nextInsertOp.getStaticPosition();
1560  if (insertedPos != llvm::ArrayRef(extractPosition).take_front(extractedRank))
1561  return failure();
1562  // Case 2.a. early-exit fold.
1563  res = nextInsertOp.getValueToStore();
1564  // Case 2.b. if internal transposition is present, canFold will be false.
1565  return success(canFold());
1566 }
1567 
1568 /// Case 3: if inserted position is a prefix of extractPosition,
1569 /// extract a portion of the source of the insertion.
1570 /// This method updates the internal state.
1571 LogicalResult
1572 ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState::handleInsertOpWithPrefixPos(Value &res) {
1573  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1574  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition() || nextInsertOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1575  return failure();
1576 
1577  ArrayRef<int64_t> insertedPos = nextInsertOp.getStaticPosition();
1578  if (!isContainedWithin(insertedPos, extractPosition))
1579  return failure();
1580  // Set leading dims to zero.
1581  std::fill_n(extractPosition.begin(), insertedPos.size(), 0);
1582  // Drop extra leading dims.
1583  extractPosition.erase(extractPosition.begin(),
1584  extractPosition.begin() + insertedPos.size());
1585  extractedRank = extractPosition.size() - sentinels.size();
1586  // Case 3.a. early-exit fold (break and delegate to post-while path).
1587  res = nextInsertOp.getValueToStore();
1588  // Case 3.b. if internal transposition is present, canFold will be false.
1589  return success();
1590 }
1591 
1592 /// Try to fold in place to extract(source, extractPosition) and return the
1593 /// folded result. Return null if folding is not possible (e.g. due to an
1594 /// internal transposition in the result).
1595 Value ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState::tryToFoldExtractOpInPlace(
1596  Value source) {
1597  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1598  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1599  return Value();
1600 
1601  // If we can't fold (either internal transposition, or nothing to fold), bail.
1602  bool nothingToFold = (source == extractOp.getSource());
1603  if (nothingToFold || !canFold())
1604  return Value();
1605 
1606  // Otherwise, fold by updating the op inplace and return its result.
1607  OpBuilder b(extractOp.getContext());
1608  extractOp.setStaticPosition(
1609  ArrayRef(extractPosition).take_front(extractedRank));
1610  extractOp.getSourceMutable().assign(source);
1611  return extractOp.getResult();
1612 }
1613 
1614 /// Iterate over producing insert and transpose ops until we find a fold.
1615 Value ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState::fold() {
1616  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1617  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1618  return Value();
1619 
1620  Value valueToExtractFrom = extractOp.getSource();
1621  updateStateForNextIteration(valueToExtractFrom);
1622  while (nextInsertOp || nextTransposeOp) {
1623  // Case 1. If we hit a transpose, just compose the map and iterate.
1624  // Invariant: insert + transpose do not change rank, we can always compose.
1625  if (succeeded(handleTransposeOp())) {
1626  valueToExtractFrom = nextTransposeOp.getVector();
1627  updateStateForNextIteration(valueToExtractFrom);
1628  continue;
1629  }
1630 
1631  Value result;
1632  // Case 2: the position match exactly.
1633  if (succeeded(handleInsertOpWithMatchingPos(result)))
1634  return result;
1635 
1636  // Case 3: if the inserted position is a prefix of extractPosition, we can
1637  // just extract a portion of the source of the insert.
1638  if (succeeded(handleInsertOpWithPrefixPos(result)))
1639  return tryToFoldExtractOpInPlace(result);
1640 
1641  // Case 4: extractPositionRef intersects insertedPosRef on non-sentinel
1642  // values. This is a more difficult case and we bail.
1643  ArrayRef<int64_t> insertedPos = nextInsertOp.getStaticPosition();
1644  if (isContainedWithin(extractPosition, insertedPos) ||
1645  intersectsWhereNonNegative(extractPosition, insertedPos))
1646  return Value();
1647 
1648  // Case 5: No intersection, we forward the extract to insertOp.dest().
1649  valueToExtractFrom = nextInsertOp.getDest();
1650  updateStateForNextIteration(valueToExtractFrom);
1651  }
1652  // If after all this we can fold, go for it.
1653  return tryToFoldExtractOpInPlace(valueToExtractFrom);
1654 }
1655 
1656 /// Returns true if the operation has a 0-D vector type operand or result.
1657 static bool hasZeroDimVectors(Operation *op) {
1658  auto hasZeroDimVectorType = [](Type type) -> bool {
1659  auto vecType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(type);
1660  return vecType && vecType.getRank() == 0;
1661  };
1662 
1663  return llvm::any_of(op->getOperandTypes(), hasZeroDimVectorType) ||
1664  llvm::any_of(op->getResultTypes(), hasZeroDimVectorType);
1665 }
1666 
1667 /// All BroadcastOps and SplatOps, as well as ShapeCastOps that only prepend
1668 /// 1s, are considered to be 'broadcastlike'.
1669 static bool isBroadcastLike(Operation *op) {
1670  if (isa<BroadcastOp, SplatOp>(op))
1671  return true;
1672 
1673  auto shapeCast = dyn_cast<ShapeCastOp>(op);
1674  if (!shapeCast)
1675  return false;
1676 
1677  // Check that shape_cast **only** prepends 1s, like (2,3) -> (1,1,2,3).
1678  // Checking that the destination shape has a prefix of 1s is not sufficient,
1679  // for example (2,3) -> (1,3,2) is not broadcastlike. A sufficient condition
1680  // is that the source shape is a suffix of the destination shape.
1681  VectorType srcType = shapeCast.getSourceVectorType();
1682  ArrayRef<int64_t> srcShape = srcType.getShape();
1683  uint64_t srcRank = srcType.getRank();
1684  ArrayRef<int64_t> dstShape = shapeCast.getType().getShape();
1685  return dstShape.size() >= srcRank && dstShape.take_back(srcRank) == srcShape;
1686 }
1687 
1688 /// Fold extract(broadcast(X)) to either extract(X) or just X.
1689 ///
1690 /// Example:
1691 ///
1692 /// broadcast extract [1][2]
1693 /// (3, 4) --------> (2, 3, 4) ----------------> (4)
1694 ///
1695 /// becomes
1696 /// extract [1]
1697 /// (3,4) -------------------------------------> (4)
1698 ///
1699 ///
1700 /// The variable names used in this implementation correspond to the above
1701 /// shapes as,
1702 ///
1703 /// - (3, 4) is `input` shape.
1704 /// - (2, 3, 4) is `broadcast` shape.
1705 /// - (4) is `extract` shape.
1706 ///
1707 /// This folding is possible when the suffix of `input` shape is the same as
1708 /// `extract` shape.
1709 static Value foldExtractFromBroadcast(ExtractOp extractOp) {
1710 
1711  Operation *defOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp();
1712  if (!defOp || !isBroadcastLike(defOp))
1713  return Value();
1714 
1715  Value input = defOp->getOperand(0);
1716 
1717  // Replace extract(broadcast(X)) with X
1718  if (extractOp.getType() == input.getType())
1719  return input;
1720 
1721  // Get required types and ranks in the chain
1722  // input -> broadcast -> extract
1723  // (scalars are treated as rank-0).
1724  auto inputType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(input.getType());
1725  auto extractType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType());
1726  unsigned inputRank = inputType ? inputType.getRank() : 0;
1727  unsigned broadcastRank = extractOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank();
1728  unsigned extractRank = extractType ? extractType.getRank() : 0;
1729 
1730  // Cannot do without the broadcast if overall the rank increases.
1731  if (extractRank > inputRank)
1732  return Value();
1733 
1734  // The above condition guarantees that input is a vector.
1735  assert(inputType && "input must be a vector type because of previous checks");
1736  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
1737 
1738  // In the case where there is a broadcast dimension in the suffix, it is not
1739  // possible to replace extract(broadcast(X)) with extract(X). Example:
1740  //
1741  // broadcast extract
1742  // (1) --------> (3,4) ------> (4)
1743  if (extractType &&
1744  extractType.getShape() != inputShape.take_back(extractRank))
1745  return Value();
1746 
1747  // Replace extract(broadcast(X)) with extract(X).
1748  // First, determine the new extraction position.
1749  unsigned deltaOverall = inputRank - extractRank;
1750  unsigned deltaBroadcast = broadcastRank - inputRank;
1751  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> oldPositions = extractOp.getMixedPosition();
1752  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> newPositions(deltaOverall);
1753  IntegerAttr zero = OpBuilder(extractOp.getContext()).getIndexAttr(0);
1754  for (auto [i, size] : llvm::enumerate(inputShape.take_front(deltaOverall))) {
1755  newPositions[i] = size == 1 ? zero : oldPositions[i + deltaBroadcast];
1756  }
1757  auto [staticPos, dynPos] = decomposeMixedValues(newPositions);
1758  extractOp->setOperands(
1759  llvm::to_vector(llvm::concat<Value>(ValueRange(input), dynPos)));
1760  extractOp.setStaticPosition(staticPos);
1761  return extractOp.getResult();
1762 }
1763 
1764 /// Fold extractOp coming from ShuffleOp.
1765 ///
1766 /// Example:
1767 ///
1768 /// %shuffle = vector.shuffle %a, %b [0, 8, 7, 15]
1769 /// : vector<8xf32>, vector<8xf32>
1770 /// %extract = vector.extract %shuffle[3] : f32 from vector<4xf32>
1771 /// ->
1772 /// %extract = vector.extract %b[7] : f32 from vector<8xf32>
1773 ///
1774 static Value foldExtractFromShuffle(ExtractOp extractOp) {
1775  // Dynamic positions are not folded as the resulting code would be more
1776  // complex than the input code.
1777  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1778  return Value();
1779 
1780  auto shuffleOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<ShuffleOp>();
1781  if (!shuffleOp)
1782  return Value();
1783 
1784  // TODO: 0-D or multi-dimensional vectors not supported yet.
1785  if (shuffleOp.getResultVectorType().getRank() != 1)
1786  return Value();
1787 
1788  int64_t inputVecSize = shuffleOp.getV1().getType().getShape()[0];
1789  auto shuffleMask = shuffleOp.getMask();
1790  int64_t extractIdx = extractOp.getStaticPosition()[0];
1791  int64_t shuffleIdx = shuffleMask[extractIdx];
1792 
1793  // Find the shuffled vector to extract from based on the shuffle index.
1794  if (shuffleIdx < inputVecSize) {
1795  extractOp.setOperand(0, shuffleOp.getV1());
1796  extractOp.setStaticPosition({shuffleIdx});
1797  } else {
1798  extractOp.setOperand(0, shuffleOp.getV2());
1799  extractOp.setStaticPosition({shuffleIdx - inputVecSize});
1800  }
1801 
1802  return extractOp.getResult();
1803 }
1804 
1805 // Fold extractOp with source coming from ShapeCast op.
1806 static Value foldExtractFromShapeCast(ExtractOp extractOp) {
1807  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1808  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1809  return Value();
1810 
1811  auto shapeCastOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>();
1812  if (!shapeCastOp)
1813  return Value();
1814 
1815  // Get the nth dimension size starting from lowest dimension.
1816  auto getDimReverse = [](VectorType type, int64_t n) {
1817  return type.getShape().take_back(n + 1).front();
1818  };
1819  int64_t destinationRank =
1820  llvm::isa<VectorType>(extractOp.getType())
1821  ? llvm::cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType()).getRank()
1822  : 0;
1823  if (destinationRank > shapeCastOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank())
1824  return Value();
1825  if (destinationRank > 0) {
1826  auto destinationType =
1827  llvm::cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getResult().getType());
1828  for (int64_t i = 0; i < destinationRank; i++) {
1829  // The lowest dimension of the destination must match the lowest
1830  // dimension of the shapecast op source.
1831  // TODO: This case could be support in a canonicalization pattern.
1832  if (getDimReverse(shapeCastOp.getSourceVectorType(), i) !=
1833  getDimReverse(destinationType, i))
1834  return Value();
1835  }
1836  }
1837  // Extract the strides associated with the extract op vector source. Then use
1838  // this to calculate a linearized position for the extract.
1839  SmallVector<int64_t> extractedPos(extractOp.getStaticPosition());
1840  std::reverse(extractedPos.begin(), extractedPos.end());
1841  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> strides;
1842  int64_t stride = 1;
1843  for (int64_t i = 0, e = extractedPos.size(); i < e; i++) {
1844  strides.push_back(stride);
1845  stride *=
1846  getDimReverse(extractOp.getSourceVectorType(), i + destinationRank);
1847  }
1848 
1849  int64_t position = linearize(extractedPos, strides);
1850  // Then extract the strides associated to the shapeCast op vector source and
1851  // delinearize the position using those strides.
1852  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> newStrides;
1853  int64_t numDimension =
1854  shapeCastOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank() - destinationRank;
1855  stride = 1;
1856  for (int64_t i = 0; i < numDimension; i++) {
1857  newStrides.push_back(stride);
1858  stride *=
1859  getDimReverse(shapeCastOp.getSourceVectorType(), i + destinationRank);
1860  }
1861  std::reverse(newStrides.begin(), newStrides.end());
1862  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> newPosition = delinearize(position, newStrides);
1863  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
1864  OpBuilder b(extractOp.getContext());
1865  extractOp.setStaticPosition(newPosition);
1866  extractOp.setOperand(0, shapeCastOp.getSource());
1867  return extractOp.getResult();
1868 }
1869 
1870 /// Fold an ExtractOp from ExtractStridedSliceOp.
1871 static Value foldExtractFromExtractStrided(ExtractOp extractOp) {
1872  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1873  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1874  return Value();
1875 
1876  auto extractStridedSliceOp =
1877  extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<vector::ExtractStridedSliceOp>();
1878  if (!extractStridedSliceOp)
1879  return Value();
1880 
1881  // 0-D vectors not supported.
1882  assert(!hasZeroDimVectors(extractOp) && "0-D vectors not supported");
1883  if (hasZeroDimVectors(extractStridedSliceOp))
1884  return Value();
1885 
1886  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' has non-unit strides.
1887  if (extractStridedSliceOp.hasNonUnitStrides())
1888  return Value();
1889 
1890  // Trim offsets for dimensions fully extracted.
1891  auto sliceOffsets =
1892  extractVector<int64_t>(extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets());
1893  while (!sliceOffsets.empty()) {
1894  size_t lastOffset = sliceOffsets.size() - 1;
1895  if (sliceOffsets.back() != 0 ||
1896  extractStridedSliceOp.getType().getDimSize(lastOffset) !=
1897  extractStridedSliceOp.getSourceVectorType().getDimSize(lastOffset))
1898  break;
1899  sliceOffsets.pop_back();
1900  }
1901  unsigned destinationRank = 0;
1902  if (auto vecType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType()))
1903  destinationRank = vecType.getRank();
1904  // The dimensions of the result need to be untouched by the
1905  // extractStridedSlice op.
1906  if (destinationRank > extractStridedSliceOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank() -
1907  sliceOffsets.size())
1908  return Value();
1909 
1910  SmallVector<int64_t> extractedPos(extractOp.getStaticPosition());
1911  assert(extractedPos.size() >= sliceOffsets.size());
1912  for (size_t i = 0, e = sliceOffsets.size(); i < e; i++)
1913  extractedPos[i] = extractedPos[i] + sliceOffsets[i];
1914  extractOp.getSourceMutable().assign(extractStridedSliceOp.getSource());
1915 
1916  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
1917  OpBuilder b(extractOp.getContext());
1918  extractOp.setStaticPosition(extractedPos);
1919  return extractOp.getResult();
1920 }
1921 
1922 /// Fold extract_op fed from a chain of insertStridedSlice ops.
1923 static Value foldExtractStridedOpFromInsertChain(ExtractOp extractOp) {
1924  // TODO: Canonicalization for dynamic position not implemented yet.
1925  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
1926  return Value();
1927 
1928  int64_t destinationRank =
1929  llvm::isa<VectorType>(extractOp.getType())
1930  ? llvm::cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType()).getRank()
1931  : 0;
1932  auto insertOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<InsertStridedSliceOp>();
1933  if (!insertOp)
1934  return Value();
1935 
1936  // 0-D vectors not supported.
1937  assert(!hasZeroDimVectors(extractOp) && "0-D vectors not supported");
1938  if (hasZeroDimVectors(insertOp))
1939  return Value();
1940 
1941  while (insertOp) {
1942  int64_t insertRankDiff = insertOp.getDestVectorType().getRank() -
1943  insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank();
1944  if (destinationRank > insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank())
1945  return Value();
1946  auto insertOffsets = extractVector<int64_t>(insertOp.getOffsets());
1947  ArrayRef<int64_t> extractOffsets = extractOp.getStaticPosition();
1948 
1949  if (llvm::any_of(insertOp.getStrides(), [](Attribute attr) {
1950  return llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt() != 1;
1951  }))
1952  return Value();
1953  bool disjoint = false;
1954  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsetDiffs;
1955  for (unsigned dim = 0, e = extractOffsets.size(); dim < e; ++dim) {
1956  int64_t start = insertOffsets[dim];
1957  int64_t size =
1958  (dim < insertRankDiff)
1959  ? 1
1960  : insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getDimSize(dim - insertRankDiff);
1961  int64_t end = start + size;
1962  int64_t offset = extractOffsets[dim];
1963  // Check if the start of the extract offset is in the interval inserted.
1964  if (start <= offset && offset < end) {
1965  if (dim >= insertRankDiff)
1966  offsetDiffs.push_back(offset - start);
1967  continue;
1968  }
1969  disjoint = true;
1970  break;
1971  }
1972  // The extract element chunk overlap with the vector inserted.
1973  if (!disjoint) {
1974  // If any of the inner dimensions are only partially inserted we have a
1975  // partial overlap.
1976  int64_t srcRankDiff =
1977  insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank() - destinationRank;
1978  for (int64_t i = 0; i < destinationRank; i++) {
1979  if (insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getDimSize(i + srcRankDiff) !=
1980  insertOp.getDestVectorType().getDimSize(i + srcRankDiff +
1981  insertRankDiff))
1982  return Value();
1983  }
1984  extractOp.getSourceMutable().assign(insertOp.getValueToStore());
1985  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
1986  OpBuilder b(extractOp.getContext());
1987  extractOp.setStaticPosition(offsetDiffs);
1988  return extractOp.getResult();
1989  }
1990  // If the chunk extracted is disjoint from the chunk inserted, keep
1991  // looking in the insert chain.
1992  insertOp = insertOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<InsertStridedSliceOp>();
1993  }
1994  return Value();
1995 }
1996 
1997 /// Try to fold the extraction of a scalar from a vector defined by
1998 /// vector.from_elements. E.g.:
1999 ///
2000 /// %0 = vector.from_elements %a, %b : vector<2xf32>
2001 /// %1 = vector.extract %0[0] : f32 from vector<2xf32>
2002 /// ==> fold to %a
2003 static Value foldScalarExtractFromFromElements(ExtractOp extractOp) {
2004  // Dynamic extractions cannot be folded.
2005  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
2006  return {};
2007 
2008  // Look for extract(from_elements).
2009  auto fromElementsOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<FromElementsOp>();
2010  if (!fromElementsOp)
2011  return {};
2012 
2013  // Scalable vectors are not supported.
2014  auto vecType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(fromElementsOp.getType());
2015  if (vecType.isScalable())
2016  return {};
2017 
2018  // Only extractions of scalars are supported.
2019  int64_t rank = vecType.getRank();
2020  ArrayRef<int64_t> indices = extractOp.getStaticPosition();
2021  if (extractOp.getType() != vecType.getElementType())
2022  return {};
2023  assert(static_cast<int64_t>(indices.size()) == rank &&
2024  "unexpected number of indices");
2025 
2026  // Compute flattened/linearized index and fold to operand.
2027  int flatIndex = 0;
2028  int stride = 1;
2029  for (int i = rank - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2030  flatIndex += indices[i] * stride;
2031  stride *= vecType.getDimSize(i);
2032  }
2033  return fromElementsOp.getElements()[flatIndex];
2034 }
2035 
2036 /// If the dynamic indices of `extractOp` or `insertOp` are in fact constants,
2037 /// then fold it.
2038 template <typename OpType, typename AdaptorType>
2039 static Value extractInsertFoldConstantOp(OpType op, AdaptorType adaptor,
2040  SmallVectorImpl<Value> &operands) {
2041  std::vector<int64_t> staticPosition = op.getStaticPosition().vec();
2042  OperandRange dynamicPosition = op.getDynamicPosition();
2043  ArrayRef<Attribute> dynamicPositionAttr = adaptor.getDynamicPosition();
2044  ArrayRef<int64_t> vectorShape;
2045  if constexpr (std::is_same_v<OpType, ExtractOp>)
2046  vectorShape = op.getSourceVectorType().getShape();
2047  else
2048  vectorShape = op.getDestVectorType().getShape();
2049 
2050  // If the dynamic operands is empty, it is returned directly.
2051  if (!dynamicPosition.size())
2052  return {};
2053 
2054  // `index` is used to iterate over the `dynamicPosition`.
2055  unsigned index = 0;
2056 
2057  // `opChange` is a flag. If it is true, it means to update `op` in place.
2058  bool opChange = false;
2059  for (unsigned i = 0, e = staticPosition.size(); i < e; ++i) {
2060  if (ShapedType::isStatic(staticPosition[i]))
2061  continue;
2062  Attribute positionAttr = dynamicPositionAttr[index];
2063  Value position = dynamicPosition[index++];
2064  if (auto attr = mlir::dyn_cast_if_present<IntegerAttr>(positionAttr)) {
2065  int64_t value = attr.getInt();
2066  // Do not fold if the value is out of bounds (-1 signifies a poison
2067  // value rather than OOB index).
2068  if (value >= -1 && value < vectorShape[i]) {
2069  staticPosition[i] = attr.getInt();
2070  opChange = true;
2071  continue;
2072  }
2073  }
2074  operands.push_back(position);
2075  }
2076 
2077  if (opChange) {
2078  op.setStaticPosition(staticPosition);
2079  op.getOperation()->setOperands(operands);
2080  // Return the original result to indicate an in-place folding happened.
2081  return op.getResult();
2082  }
2083  return {};
2084 }
2085 
2086 /// Fold an insert or extract operation into an poison value when a poison index
2087 /// is found at any dimension of the static position.
2088 static Attribute foldPoisonIndexInsertExtractOp(MLIRContext *context,
2089  ArrayRef<int64_t> staticPos,
2090  int64_t poisonVal) {
2091  if (!is_contained(staticPos, poisonVal))
2092  return {};
2093 
2094  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(context);
2095 }
2096 
2097 /// Fold a vector extract from is a poison source.
2098 static Attribute foldPoisonSrcExtractOp(Attribute srcAttr) {
2099  if (isa_and_nonnull<ub::PoisonAttr>(srcAttr))
2100  return srcAttr;
2101 
2102  return {};
2103 }
2104 
2105 /// Fold a vector extract extracting from a DenseElementsAttr.
2106 static Attribute foldDenseElementsAttrSrcExtractOp(ExtractOp extractOp,
2107  Attribute srcAttr) {
2108  auto denseAttr = dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(srcAttr);
2109  if (!denseAttr) {
2110  return {};
2111  }
2112 
2113  if (denseAttr.isSplat()) {
2114  Attribute newAttr = denseAttr.getSplatValue<Attribute>();
2115  if (auto vecDstType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType()))
2116  newAttr = DenseElementsAttr::get(vecDstType, newAttr);
2117  return newAttr;
2118  }
2119 
2120  auto vecTy = cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getSourceVectorType());
2121  if (vecTy.isScalable())
2122  return {};
2123 
2124  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition()) {
2125  return {};
2126  }
2127 
2128  // Materializing subsets of a large constant array can generally lead to
2129  // explosion in IR size because of different combination of subsets that
2130  // can exist. However, vector.extract is a restricted form of subset
2131  // extract where you can only extract non-overlapping (or the same) subset for
2132  // a given rank of the subset. Because of this property, the IR size can only
2133  // increase at most by `rank * size(array)` from a single constant array being
2134  // extracted by multiple extracts.
2135 
2136  // Calculate the linearized position of the continuous chunk of elements to
2137  // extract.
2138  SmallVector<int64_t> completePositions(vecTy.getRank(), 0);
2139  copy(extractOp.getStaticPosition(), completePositions.begin());
2140  int64_t startPos =
2141  linearize(completePositions, computeStrides(vecTy.getShape()));
2142  auto denseValuesBegin = denseAttr.value_begin<TypedAttr>() + startPos;
2143 
2144  TypedAttr newAttr;
2145  if (auto resVecTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType())) {
2146  SmallVector<Attribute> elementValues(
2147  denseValuesBegin, denseValuesBegin + resVecTy.getNumElements());
2148  newAttr = DenseElementsAttr::get(resVecTy, elementValues);
2149  } else {
2150  newAttr = *denseValuesBegin;
2151  }
2152 
2153  return newAttr;
2154 }
2155 
2156 OpFoldResult ExtractOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
2157  // Fold "vector.extract %v[] : vector<2x2xf32> from vector<2x2xf32>" to %v.
2158  // Note: Do not fold "vector.extract %v[] : f32 from vector<f32>" (type
2159  // mismatch).
2160  if (getNumIndices() == 0 && getSource().getType() == getResult().getType())
2161  return getSource();
2162  if (auto res = foldPoisonSrcExtractOp(adaptor.getSource()))
2163  return res;
2164  // Fold `arith.constant` indices into the `vector.extract` operation.
2165  // Do not stop here as this fold may enable subsequent folds that require
2166  // constant indices.
2167  SmallVector<Value> operands = {getSource()};
2168  auto inplaceFolded = extractInsertFoldConstantOp(*this, adaptor, operands);
2169 
2170  if (auto res = foldPoisonIndexInsertExtractOp(
2171  getContext(), adaptor.getStaticPosition(), kPoisonIndex))
2172  return res;
2173  if (auto res = foldDenseElementsAttrSrcExtractOp(*this, adaptor.getSource()))
2174  return res;
2175  if (succeeded(foldExtractOpFromExtractChain(*this)))
2176  return getResult();
2177  if (auto res = ExtractFromInsertTransposeChainState(*this).fold())
2178  return res;
2179  if (auto res = foldExtractFromBroadcast(*this))
2180  return res;
2181  if (auto res = foldExtractFromShuffle(*this))
2182  return res;
2183  if (auto res = foldExtractFromShapeCast(*this))
2184  return res;
2185  if (auto val = foldExtractFromExtractStrided(*this))
2186  return val;
2187  if (auto val = foldExtractStridedOpFromInsertChain(*this))
2188  return val;
2189  if (auto val = foldScalarExtractFromFromElements(*this))
2190  return val;
2191 
2192  return inplaceFolded;
2193 }

2195 namespace {

2197 // Pattern to rewrite a ExtractOp(Broadcast) -> Broadcast.
2198 class ExtractOpFromBroadcast final : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractOp> {
2199 public:
2200  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
2201 
2202  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractOp extractOp,
2203  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2204 
2205  Operation *defOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp();
2206  VectorType outType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType());
2207  if (!defOp || !isBroadcastLike(defOp) || !outType)
2208  return failure();
2209 
2210  Value source = defOp->getOperand(0);
2211  if (isBroadcastableTo(source.getType(), outType) !=
2212  BroadcastableToResult::Success)
2213  return failure();
2214 
2215  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(extractOp, outType, source);
2216  return success();
2217  }
2218 };
2219 
2220 // Pattern to rewrite a ExtractOp(CreateMask) -> CreateMask.
2221 class ExtractOpFromCreateMask final : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractOp> {
2222 public:
2223  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
2224 
2225  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractOp extractOp,
2226  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2227  auto createMaskOp =
2228  extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>();
2229  if (!createMaskOp)
2230  return failure();
2231 
2232  VectorType extractedMaskType =
2233  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getResult().getType());
2234 
2235  if (!extractedMaskType)
2236  return failure();
2237 
2238  auto maskOperands = createMaskOp.getOperands();
2239  ArrayRef<int64_t> extractOpPos = extractOp.getStaticPosition();
2240  VectorType maskType = createMaskOp.getVectorType();
2241 
2242  bool containsUnknownDims = false;
2243  bool allFalse = getMaskFormat(createMaskOp) == MaskFormat::AllFalse;
2244 
2245  for (size_t dimIdx = 0; !allFalse && dimIdx < extractOpPos.size();
2246  dimIdx++) {
2247  int64_t pos = extractOpPos[dimIdx];
2248  Value operand = maskOperands[dimIdx];
2249  auto constantOp = operand.getDefiningOp<arith::ConstantOp>();
2250  if (!constantOp) {
2251  // Bounds of this dim unknown.
2252  containsUnknownDims = true;
2253  continue;
2254  }
2255 
2256  int64_t createMaskBound =
2257  llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(constantOp.getValue()).getInt();
2258 
2259  if (pos != ShapedType::kDynamic) {
2260  // If any position is outside the range from the `create_mask`, then the
2261  // extracted mask will be all-false.
2262  allFalse |= pos >= createMaskBound;
2263  } else if (createMaskBound < maskType.getDimSize(dimIdx)) {
2264  // This dim is not all-true and since this is a dynamic index we don't
2265  // know if the extraction is within the true or false region.
2266  // Note: Zero dims have already handled via getMaskFormat().
2267  containsUnknownDims = true;
2268  }
2269  }
2270 
2271  if (allFalse) {
2272  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<arith::ConstantOp>(
2273  extractOp, DenseElementsAttr::get(extractedMaskType, false));
2274  } else if (!containsUnknownDims) {
2275  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>(
2276  extractOp, extractedMaskType,
2277  maskOperands.drop_front(extractOpPos.size()));
2278  } else {
2279  return failure();
2280  }
2281  return success();
2282  }
2283 };
2284 
2285 // Folds extract(shape_cast(..)) into shape_cast when the total element count
2286 // does not change.
2287 LogicalResult foldExtractFromShapeCastToShapeCast(ExtractOp extractOp,
2288  PatternRewriter &rewriter) {
2289  auto castOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<ShapeCastOp>();
2290  if (!castOp)
2291  return failure();
2292 
2293  VectorType sourceType = castOp.getSourceVectorType();
2294  auto targetType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getResult().getType());
2295  if (!targetType)
2296  return failure();
2297 
2298  if (sourceType.getNumElements() != targetType.getNumElements())
2299  return failure();
2300 
2301  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(extractOp, targetType,
2302  castOp.getSource());
2303  return success();
2304 }
2305 
2306 /// Try to canonicalize the extraction of a subvector from a vector defined by
2307 /// vector.from_elements. E.g.:
2308 ///
2309 /// %0 = vector.from_elements %a, %b, %a, %a : vector<2x2xf32>
2310 /// %1 = vector.extract %0[0] : vector<2xf32> from vector<2x2xf32>
2311 /// ==> canonicalize to vector.from_elements %a, %b : vector<2xf32>
2312 LogicalResult foldExtractFromFromElements(ExtractOp extractOp,
2313  PatternRewriter &rewriter) {
2314  // Dynamic positions are not supported.
2315  if (extractOp.hasDynamicPosition())
2316  return failure();
2317 
2318  // Scalar extracts are handled by the folder.
2319  auto resultType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(extractOp.getType());
2320  if (!resultType)
2321  return failure();
2322 
2323  // Look for extracts from a from_elements op.
2324  auto fromElementsOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<FromElementsOp>();
2325  if (!fromElementsOp)
2326  return failure();
2327  VectorType inputType = fromElementsOp.getType();
2328 
2329  // Scalable vectors are not supported.
2330  if (resultType.isScalable() || inputType.isScalable())
2331  return failure();
2332 
2333  // Compute the position of first extracted element and flatten/linearize the
2334  // position.
2335  SmallVector<int64_t> firstElementPos =
2336  llvm::to_vector(extractOp.getStaticPosition());
2337  firstElementPos.append(/*NumInputs=*/resultType.getRank(), /*Elt=*/0);
2338  int flatIndex = 0;
2339  int stride = 1;
2340  for (int64_t i = inputType.getRank() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2341  flatIndex += firstElementPos[i] * stride;
2342  stride *= inputType.getDimSize(i);
2343  }
2344 
2345  // Replace the op with a smaller from_elements op.
2346  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<FromElementsOp>(
2347  extractOp, resultType,
2348  fromElementsOp.getElements().slice(flatIndex,
2349  resultType.getNumElements()));
2350  return success();
2351 }
2352 
2353 } // namespace
2354 
2355 void ExtractOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
2356  MLIRContext *context) {
2357  results.add<ExtractOpFromBroadcast, ExtractOpFromCreateMask>(context);
2358  results.add(foldExtractFromShapeCastToShapeCast);
2359  results.add(foldExtractFromFromElements);
2360 }

2362 static void populateFromInt64AttrArray(ArrayAttr arrayAttr,
2363  SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &results) {
2364  for (auto attr : arrayAttr)
2365  results.push_back(llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt());
2366 }

2380 /// Returns true if all the `operands` are defined by `defOp`.
2381 /// Otherwise, returns false.
2382 static bool haveSameDefiningOp(OperandRange operands, Operation *defOp) {
2383  if (operands.empty())
2384  return false;
2385 
2386  return llvm::all_of(operands, [&](Value operand) {
2387  Operation *currentDef = operand.getDefiningOp();
2388  return currentDef == defOp;
2389  });
2390 }

2392 /// Folds vector.to_elements(vector.from_elements(%e0, %e1, ...)) into
2393 /// (%e0, %e1, ...). For example:
2394 ///
2395 /// %0 = vector.from_elements %a, %b, %c : vector<3xf32>
2396 /// %1:3 = vector.to_elements %0 : vector<3xf32>
2397 /// user_op %1#0, %1#1, %1#2
2398 ///
2399 /// becomes:
2400 ///
2401 /// user_op %a, %b, %c
2402 ///
2403 static LogicalResult
2404 foldToElementsFromElements(ToElementsOp toElementsOp,
2405  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
2406  auto fromElementsOp =
2407  toElementsOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<FromElementsOp>();
2408  if (!fromElementsOp)
2409  return failure();
2410 
2411  llvm::append_range(results, fromElementsOp.getElements());
2412  return success();
2413 }
2414 
2415 LogicalResult ToElementsOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor,
2416  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
2417  return foldToElementsFromElements(*this, results);
2418 }

2420 LogicalResult
2421 ToElementsOp::inferReturnTypes(MLIRContext *ctx, std::optional<Location> loc,
2422  ToElementsOp::Adaptor adaptor,
2423  SmallVectorImpl<Type> &inferredReturnTypes) {
2424  auto vecType = cast<VectorType>(adaptor.getSource().getType());
2425  Type elType = vecType.getElementType();
2426  inferredReturnTypes.append(vecType.getNumElements(), elType);
2427  return success();
2428 }

2430 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2431 // FromElementsOp
2432 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2433 
2434 /// Folds vector.from_elements(vector.to_elements(%vector)) into %vector.
2435 ///
2436 /// Case #1: Input and output vectors are the same.
2437 ///
2438 /// %0:3 = vector.to_elements %a : vector<3xf32>
2439 /// %1 = vector.from_elements %0#0, %0#1, %0#2 : vector<3xf32>
2440 /// user_op %1
2441 ///
2442 /// becomes:
2443 ///
2444 /// user_op %a
2445 ///
2446 static OpFoldResult foldFromElementsToElements(FromElementsOp fromElementsOp) {
2447  OperandRange fromElemsOperands = fromElementsOp.getElements();
2448  if (fromElemsOperands.empty())
2449  return {};
2450 
2451  auto toElementsOp = fromElemsOperands[0].getDefiningOp<ToElementsOp>();
2452  if (!toElementsOp)
2453  return {};
2454 
2455  if (!haveSameDefiningOp(fromElemsOperands, toElementsOp))
2456  return {};
2457 
2458  // Case #1: Input and output vectors are the same. Forward the input vector.
2459  Value toElementsInput = toElementsOp.getSource();
2460  if (fromElementsOp.getType() == toElementsInput.getType() &&
2461  llvm::equal(fromElemsOperands, toElementsOp.getResults())) {
2462  return toElementsInput;
2463  }
2464 
2465  // TODO: Support cases with different input and output shapes and different
2466  // number of elements.
2467 
2468  return {};
2469 }
2470 
2471 /// Fold vector.from_elements to a constant when all operands are constants.
2472 /// Example:
2473 /// %c1 = arith.constant 1 : i32
2474 /// %c2 = arith.constant 2 : i32
2475 /// %v = vector.from_elements %c1, %c2 : vector<2xi32>
2476 /// =>
2477 /// %v = arith.constant dense<[1, 2]> : vector<2xi32>
2478 ///
2479 static OpFoldResult foldFromElementsToConstant(FromElementsOp fromElementsOp,
2480  ArrayRef<Attribute> elements) {
2481  // Check for null or poison attributes before any processing.
2482  if (llvm::any_of(elements, [](Attribute attr) {
2483  return !attr || isa<ub::PoisonAttrInterface>(attr);
2484  }))
2485  return {};
2486 
2487  // DenseElementsAttr only supports int/index/float/complex types.
2488  auto destVecType = fromElementsOp.getDest().getType();
2489  auto destEltType = destVecType.getElementType();
2490  if (!destEltType.isIntOrIndexOrFloat() && !isa<ComplexType>(destEltType))
2491  return {};
2492 
2493  // Constant attributes might have a different type than the return type.
2494  // Convert them before creating the dense elements attribute.
2495  auto convertedElements = llvm::map_to_vector(elements, [&](Attribute attr) {
2496  return convertNumericAttr(attr, destEltType);
2497  });
2498 
2499  return DenseElementsAttr::get(destVecType, convertedElements);
2500 }
2501 
2502 OpFoldResult FromElementsOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
2503  if (auto res = foldFromElementsToElements(*this))
2504  return res;
2505  if (auto res = foldFromElementsToConstant(*this, adaptor.getElements()))
2506  return res;
2507 
2508  return {};
2509 }
2510 
2511 /// Rewrite vector.from_elements as vector.broadcast if the elements are the
2512 /// same. Example:
2513 /// %0 = vector.from_elements %a, %a, %a : vector<3xf32>
2514 /// =>
2515 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %a : f32 to vector<3xf32>
2516 static LogicalResult
2517 rewriteFromElementsAsBroadcast(FromElementsOp fromElementsOp,
2518  PatternRewriter &rewriter) {
2519  if (!llvm::all_equal(fromElementsOp.getElements()))
2520  return failure();
2521  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(
2522  fromElementsOp, fromElementsOp.getType(),
2523  fromElementsOp.getElements().front());
2524  return success();
2525 }
2526 
2527 /// Rewrite from_elements on multiple scalar extracts as a shape_cast
2528 /// on a single extract. Example:
2529 /// %0 = vector.extract %source[0, 0] : i8 from vector<2x2xi8>
2530 /// %1 = vector.extract %source[0, 1] : i8 from vector<2x2xi8>
2531 /// %2 = vector.from_elements %0, %1 : vector<2xi8>
2532 ///
2533 /// becomes
2534 /// %1 = vector.extract %source[0] : vector<1x2xi8> from vector<2x2xi8>
2535 /// %2 = vector.shape_cast %1 : vector<1x2xi8> to vector<2xi8>
2536 ///
2537 /// The requirements for this to be valid are
2538 ///
2539 /// i) The elements are extracted from the same vector (%source).
2540 ///
2541 /// ii) The elements form a suffix of %source. Specifically, the number
2542 /// of elements is the same as the product of the last N dimension sizes
2543 /// of %source, for some N.
2544 ///
2545 /// iii) The elements are extracted contiguously in ascending order.
2546 
2547 class FromElementsToShapeCast : public OpRewritePattern<FromElementsOp> {
2548 
2549  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
2550 
2551  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(FromElementsOp fromElements,
2552  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2553 
2554  // Handled by `rewriteFromElementsAsBroadcast`.
2555  if (fromElements.getType().getNumElements() == 1)
2556  return failure();
2557 
2558  // The common source that all elements are extracted from, if one exists.
2559  TypedValue<VectorType> source;
2560  // The position of the combined extract operation, if one is created.
2561  ArrayRef<int64_t> combinedPosition;
2562  // The expected index of extraction of the current element in the loop, if
2563  // elements are extracted contiguously in ascending order.
2564  SmallVector<int64_t> expectedPosition;
2565 
2566  for (auto [insertIndex, element] :
2567  llvm::enumerate(fromElements.getElements())) {
2568 
2569  // Check that the element is from a vector.extract operation.
2570  auto extractOp = element.getDefiningOp<vector::ExtractOp>();
2571  if (!extractOp) {
2572  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(fromElements,
2573  "element not from vector.extract");
2574  }
2575 
2576  // Check condition (i) by checking that all elements have the same source
2577  // as the first element.
2578  if (insertIndex == 0) {
2579  source = extractOp.getSource();
2580  } else if (extractOp.getSource() != source) {
2581  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(fromElements,
2582  "element from different vector");
2583  }
2584 
2585  ArrayRef<int64_t> position = extractOp.getStaticPosition();
2586  int64_t rank = position.size();
2587  assert(rank == source.getType().getRank() &&
2588  "scalar extract must have full rank position");
2589 
2590  // Check condition (ii) by checking that the position that the first
2591  // element is extracted from has sufficient trailing 0s. For example, in
2592  //
2593  // %elm0 = vector.extract %source[1, 0, 0] : i8 from vector<2x3x4xi8>
2594  // [...]
2595  // %elms = vector.from_elements %elm0, [...] : vector<12xi8>
2596  //
2597  // The 2 trailing 0s in the position of extraction of %elm0 cover 3*4 = 12
2598  // elements, which is the number of elements of %n, so this is valid.
2599  if (insertIndex == 0) {
2600  const int64_t numElms = fromElements.getType().getNumElements();
2601  int64_t numSuffixElms = 1;
2602  int64_t index = rank;
2603  while (index > 0 && position[index - 1] == 0 &&
2604  numSuffixElms < numElms) {
2605  numSuffixElms *= source.getType().getDimSize(index - 1);
2606  --index;
2607  }
2608  if (numSuffixElms != numElms) {
2609  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
2610  fromElements, "elements do not form a suffix of source");
2611  }
2612  expectedPosition = llvm::to_vector(position);
2613  combinedPosition = position.drop_back(rank - index);
2614  }
2615 
2616  // Check condition (iii).
2617  else if (expectedPosition != position) {
2618  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
2619  fromElements, "elements not in ascending order (static order)");
2620  }
2621  increment(expectedPosition, source.getType().getShape());
2622  }
2623 
2624  auto extracted = rewriter.createOrFold<vector::ExtractOp>(
2625  fromElements.getLoc(), source, combinedPosition);
2626 
2627  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(
2628  fromElements, fromElements.getType(), extracted);
2629 
2630  return success();
2631  }
2632 
2633  /// Increments n-D `indices` by 1 starting from the innermost dimension.
2634  static void increment(MutableArrayRef<int64_t> indices,
2635  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape) {
2636  for (int dim : llvm::reverse(llvm::seq<int>(0, indices.size()))) {
2637  indices[dim] += 1;
2638  if (indices[dim] < shape[dim])
2639  break;
2640  indices[dim] = 0;
2641  }
2642  }
2643 };
2644 
2645 void FromElementsOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
2646  MLIRContext *context) {
2647  results.add(rewriteFromElementsAsBroadcast);
2648  results.add<FromElementsToShapeCast>(context);
2649 }

2660 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>> BroadcastOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
2661  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getResultVectorType().getShape());
2662 }
2663 
2664 /// Return the dimensions of the result vector that were formerly ones in the
2665 /// source tensor and thus correspond to "dim-1" broadcasting.
2666 static llvm::SetVector<int64_t>
2667 computeBroadcastedUnitDims(ArrayRef<int64_t> srcShape,
2668  ArrayRef<int64_t> dstShape) {
2669  int64_t rankDiff = dstShape.size() - srcShape.size();
2670  int64_t dstDim = rankDiff;
2671  llvm::SetVector<int64_t> res;
2672  for (auto [s1, s2] :
2673  llvm::zip_equal(srcShape, dstShape.drop_front(rankDiff))) {
2674  if (s1 != s2) {
2675  assert(s1 == 1 && "expected \"dim-1\" broadcasting");
2676  res.insert(dstDim);
2677  }
2678  ++dstDim;
2679  }
2680  return res;
2681 }
2682 
2683 llvm::SetVector<int64_t> BroadcastOp::computeBroadcastedUnitDims() {
2684  // Scalar broadcast is without any unit dim broadcast.
2685  auto srcVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(getSourceType());
2686  if (!srcVectorType)
2687  return {};
2688  return ::computeBroadcastedUnitDims(srcVectorType.getShape(),
2689  getResultVectorType().getShape());
2690 }
2691 
2692 /// Broadcast `value` to a vector of `dstShape`, knowing that exactly the
2693 /// `broadcastedDims` dimensions in the dstShape are broadcasted.
2694 /// This requires (and asserts) that the broadcast is free of "dim-1"
2695 /// broadcasting.
2696 /// Since vector.broadcast only allows expanding leading dimensions, an extra
2697 /// vector.transpose may be inserted to make the broadcast possible.
2698 /// `value`, `dstShape` and `broadcastedDims` must be properly specified or
2699 /// the helper will assert. This means:
2700 /// 1. `dstShape` must not be empty.
2701 /// 2. `broadcastedDims` must be confined to [0 .. rank(value.getVectorType)]
2702 /// 2. `dstShape` trimmed of the dimensions specified in `broadcastedDims`
2703 // must match the `value` shape.
2704 Value BroadcastOp::createOrFoldBroadcastOp(
2705  OpBuilder &b, Value value, ArrayRef<int64_t> dstShape,
2706  const llvm::SetVector<int64_t> &broadcastedDims) {
2707  assert(!dstShape.empty() && "unexpected empty dst shape");
2708 
2709  // Well-formedness check.
2710  SmallVector<int64_t> checkShape;
2711  for (int i = 0, e = dstShape.size(); i < e; ++i) {
2712  if (broadcastedDims.contains(i))
2713  continue;
2714  checkShape.push_back(dstShape[i]);
2715  }
2716  assert(broadcastedDims.size() == dstShape.size() - checkShape.size() &&
2717  "ill-formed broadcastedDims contains values not confined to "
2718  "destVectorShape");
2719 
2720  Location loc = value.getLoc();
2721  Type elementType = getElementTypeOrSelf(value.getType());
2722  VectorType srcVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(value.getType());
2723  VectorType dstVectorType = VectorType::get(dstShape, elementType);
2724 
2725  // Step 2. If scalar -> dstShape broadcast, just do it.
2726  if (!srcVectorType) {
2727  assert(checkShape.empty() &&
2728  "ill-formed createOrFoldBroadcastOp arguments");
2729  return b.createOrFold<vector::BroadcastOp>(loc, dstVectorType, value);
2730  }
2731 
2732  assert(srcVectorType.getShape().equals(checkShape) &&
2733  "ill-formed createOrFoldBroadcastOp arguments");
2734 
2735  // Step 3. Since vector.broadcast only allows creating leading dims,
2736  // vector -> dstShape broadcast may require a transpose.
2737  // Traverse the dims in order and construct:
2738  // 1. The leading entries of the broadcastShape that is guaranteed to be
2739  // achievable by a simple broadcast.
2740  // 2. The induced permutation for the subsequent vector.transpose that will
2741  // bring us from `broadcastShape` back to he desired `dstShape`.
2742  // If the induced permutation is not the identity, create a vector.transpose.
2743  SmallVector<int64_t> broadcastShape, permutation(dstShape.size(), -1);
2744  broadcastShape.reserve(dstShape.size());
2745  // Consider the example:
2746  // srcShape = 2x4
2747  // dstShape = 1x2x3x4x5
2748  // broadcastedDims = [0, 2, 4]
2749  //
2750  // We want to build:
2751  // broadcastShape = 1x3x5x2x4
2752  // permutation = [0, 2, 4, 1, 3]
2753  // ---V--- -----V-----
2754  // leading broadcast part src shape part
2755  //
2756  // Note that the trailing dims of broadcastShape are exactly the srcShape
2757  // by construction.
2758  // nextSrcShapeDim is used to keep track of where in the permutation the
2759  // "src shape part" occurs.
2760  int64_t nextSrcShapeDim = broadcastedDims.size();
2761  for (int64_t i = 0, e = dstShape.size(); i < e; ++i) {
2762  if (broadcastedDims.contains(i)) {
2763  // 3.a. For each dim in the dst shape, if it is a broadcasted dim,
2764  // bring it to the head of the broadcastShape.
2765  // It will need to be permuted back from `broadcastShape.size() - 1` into
2766  // position `i`.
2767  broadcastShape.push_back(dstShape[i]);
2768  permutation[i] = broadcastShape.size() - 1;
2769  } else {
2770  // 3.b. Otherwise, the dim is not broadcasted, it comes from the src
2771  // shape and needs to be permuted into position `i`.
2772  // Don't touch `broadcastShape` here, the whole srcShape will be
2773  // appended after.
2774  permutation[i] = nextSrcShapeDim++;
2775  }
2776  }
2777  // 3.c. Append the srcShape.
2778  llvm::append_range(broadcastShape, srcVectorType.getShape());
2779 
2780  // Ensure there are no "dim-1" broadcasts.
2781  assert(::computeBroadcastedUnitDims(srcVectorType.getShape(), broadcastShape)
2782  .empty() &&
2783  "unexpected \"dim-1\" broadcast");
2784 
2785  VectorType broadcastType = VectorType::get(broadcastShape, elementType);
2786  assert(vector::isBroadcastableTo(value.getType(), broadcastType) ==
2787  vector::BroadcastableToResult::Success &&
2788  "must be broadcastable");
2789  Value res = b.createOrFold<vector::BroadcastOp>(loc, broadcastType, value);
2790  // Step 4. If we find any dimension that indeed needs to be permuted,
2791  // immediately return a new vector.transpose.
2792  for (int64_t i = 0, e = permutation.size(); i < e; ++i)
2793  if (permutation[i] != i)
2794  return b.createOrFold<vector::TransposeOp>(loc, res, permutation);
2795  // Otherwise return res.
2796  return res;
2797 }
2798 
2799 BroadcastableToResult mlir::vector::isBroadcastableTo(
2800  Type srcType, VectorType dstVectorType,
2801  std::pair<VectorDim, VectorDim> *mismatchingDims) {
2802  // Broadcast scalar to vector of the same element type.
2803  if (isa<VectorElementTypeInterface>(srcType) && dstVectorType &&
2804  srcType == getElementTypeOrSelf(dstVectorType))
2805  return BroadcastableToResult::Success;
2806  // From now on, only vectors broadcast.
2807  VectorType srcVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(srcType);
2808  if (!srcVectorType)
2809  return BroadcastableToResult::SourceTypeNotAVector;
2810 
2811  int64_t srcRank = srcVectorType.getRank();
2812  int64_t dstRank = dstVectorType.getRank();
2813  if (srcRank > dstRank)
2814  return BroadcastableToResult::SourceRankHigher;
2815  // Source has an exact match or singleton value for all trailing dimensions
2816  // (all leading dimensions are simply duplicated).
2817  int64_t lead = dstRank - srcRank;
2818  for (int64_t dimIdx = 0; dimIdx < srcRank; ++dimIdx) {
2819  // Have mismatching dims (in the sense of vector.broadcast semantics) been
2820  // encountered?
2821  bool foundMismatchingDims = false;
2822 
2823  // Check fixed-width dims.
2824  int64_t srcDim = srcVectorType.getDimSize(dimIdx);
2825  int64_t dstDim = dstVectorType.getDimSize(lead + dimIdx);
2826  if (srcDim != 1 && srcDim != dstDim)
2827  foundMismatchingDims = true;
2828 
2829  // Check scalable flags.
2830  bool srcDimScalableFlag = srcVectorType.getScalableDims()[dimIdx];
2831  bool dstDimScalableFlag = dstVectorType.getScalableDims()[lead + dimIdx];
2832  if ((srcDim == 1 && srcDimScalableFlag && dstDim != 1) ||
2833  // 1 -> [N] is fine, everything else should be rejected when mixing
2834  // fixed-width and scalable dims
2835  (srcDimScalableFlag != dstDimScalableFlag &&
2836  (srcDim != 1 || srcDimScalableFlag)))
2837  foundMismatchingDims = true;
2838 
2839  if (foundMismatchingDims) {
2840  if (mismatchingDims != nullptr) {
2841  mismatchingDims->first.dim = srcDim;
2842  mismatchingDims->first.isScalable = srcDimScalableFlag;
2843 
2844  mismatchingDims->second.dim = dstDim;
2845  mismatchingDims->second.isScalable = dstDimScalableFlag;
2846  }
2847  return BroadcastableToResult::DimensionMismatch;
2848  }
2849  }
2850 
2851  return BroadcastableToResult::Success;
2852 }
2853 
2854 LogicalResult BroadcastOp::verify() {
2855  std::pair<VectorDim, VectorDim> mismatchingDims;
2856  BroadcastableToResult res = isBroadcastableTo(
2857  getSourceType(), getResultVectorType(), &mismatchingDims);
2858  if (res == BroadcastableToResult::Success)
2859  return success();
2860  if (res == BroadcastableToResult::SourceRankHigher)
2861  return emitOpError("source rank higher than destination rank");
2862  if (res == BroadcastableToResult::DimensionMismatch) {
2863  return emitOpError("dimension mismatch (")
2864  << (mismatchingDims.first.isScalable ? "[" : "")
2865  << mismatchingDims.first.dim
2866  << (mismatchingDims.first.isScalable ? "]" : "") << " vs. "
2867  << (mismatchingDims.second.isScalable ? "[" : "")
2868  << mismatchingDims.second.dim
2869  << (mismatchingDims.second.isScalable ? "]" : "") << ")";
2870  }
2871  if (res == BroadcastableToResult::SourceTypeNotAVector)
2872  return emitOpError("source type is not a vector");
2873  llvm_unreachable("unexpected vector.broadcast op error");
2874 }
2875 
2876 // Fold broadcast(shape_cast(x)) into broadcast(x) if x's type is compatible
2877 // with broadcast's result type and shape_cast only adds or removes ones in the
2878 // leading dimensions.
2879 static LogicalResult foldBroadcastOfShapeCast(BroadcastOp broadcastOp) {
2880  auto srcShapeCast = broadcastOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<ShapeCastOp>();
2881  if (!srcShapeCast)
2882  return failure();
2883 
2884  VectorType srcType = srcShapeCast.getSourceVectorType();
2885  VectorType destType = broadcastOp.getResultVectorType();
2886  // Check type compatibility.
2887  if (vector::isBroadcastableTo(srcType, destType) !=
2888  BroadcastableToResult::Success)
2889  return failure();
2890 
2891  ArrayRef<int64_t> srcShape = srcType.getShape();
2892  ArrayRef<int64_t> shapecastShape =
2893  srcShapeCast.getResultVectorType().getShape();
2894  // Trailing dimensions should be the same if shape_cast only alters the
2895  // leading dimensions.
2896  unsigned numTrailingDims = std::min(srcShape.size(), shapecastShape.size());
2897  if (!llvm::equal(srcShape.take_back(numTrailingDims),
2898  shapecastShape.take_back(numTrailingDims)))
2899  return failure();
2900 
2901  assert(all_of(srcShape.drop_back(numTrailingDims),
2902  [](int64_t E) { return E == 1; }) &&
2903  all_of(shapecastShape.drop_back(numTrailingDims),
2904  [](int64_t E) { return E == 1; }) &&
2905  "ill-formed shape_cast");
2906 
2907  broadcastOp.getSourceMutable().assign(srcShapeCast.getSource());
2908  return success();
2909 }
2910 
2911 OpFoldResult BroadcastOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
2912  if (getSourceType() == getResultVectorType())
2913  return getSource();
2914  if (succeeded(foldBroadcastOfShapeCast(*this)))
2915  return getResult();
2916 
2917  if (!adaptor.getSource())
2918  return {};
2919  auto vectorType = getResultVectorType();
2920  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<IntegerAttr>(adaptor.getSource())) {
2921  if (vectorType.getElementType() != attr.getType())
2922  return {};
2923  return DenseElementsAttr::get(vectorType, attr);
2924  }
2925  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<FloatAttr>(adaptor.getSource())) {
2926  if (vectorType.getElementType() != attr.getType())
2927  return {};
2928  return DenseElementsAttr::get(vectorType, attr);
2929  }
2930  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<SplatElementsAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
2931  return DenseElementsAttr::get(vectorType, attr.getSplatValue<Attribute>());
2932  if (llvm::dyn_cast<ub::PoisonAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
2933  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(getContext());
2934  return {};
2935 }

2939 // Fold broadcast1(broadcast2(x)) into broadcast1(x).
2940 struct BroadcastFolder : public OpRewritePattern<BroadcastOp> {
2941  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
2942 
2943  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(BroadcastOp broadcastOp,
2944  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2945  auto srcBroadcast = broadcastOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>();
2946  if (!srcBroadcast)
2947  return failure();
2948  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(broadcastOp,
2949  broadcastOp.getResultVectorType(),
2950  srcBroadcast.getSource());
2951  return success();
2952  }
2953 };
2954 } // namespace

2959  // calling `populateCastAwayVectorLeadingOneDimPatterns`

2963 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

2966 
2967 LogicalResult ShuffleOp::verify() {
2968  VectorType resultType = getResultVectorType();
2969  VectorType v1Type = getV1VectorType();
2970  VectorType v2Type = getV2VectorType();
2971  // Verify ranks.
2972  int64_t resRank = resultType.getRank();
2973  int64_t v1Rank = v1Type.getRank();
2974  int64_t v2Rank = v2Type.getRank();
2975  bool wellFormed0DCase = v1Rank == 0 && v2Rank == 0 && resRank == 1;
2976  bool wellFormedNDCase = v1Rank == resRank && v2Rank == resRank;
2977  if (!wellFormed0DCase && !wellFormedNDCase)
2978  return emitOpError("rank mismatch");
2979 
2980  // Verify all but leading dimension sizes.
2981  for (int64_t r = 1; r < v1Rank; ++r) {
2982  int64_t resDim = resultType.getDimSize(r);
2983  int64_t v1Dim = v1Type.getDimSize(r);
2984  int64_t v2Dim = v2Type.getDimSize(r);
2985  if (resDim != v1Dim || v1Dim != v2Dim)
2986  return emitOpError("dimension mismatch");
2987  }
2988  // Verify mask length.
2989  ArrayRef<int64_t> mask = getMask();
2990  int64_t maskLength = mask.size();
2991  if (maskLength <= 0)
2992  return emitOpError("invalid mask length");
2993  if (maskLength != resultType.getDimSize(0))
2994  return emitOpError("mask length mismatch");
2995  // Verify all indices.
2996  int64_t indexSize = (v1Type.getRank() == 0 ? 1 : v1Type.getDimSize(0)) +
2997  (v2Type.getRank() == 0 ? 1 : v2Type.getDimSize(0));
2998  for (auto [idx, maskPos] : llvm::enumerate(mask)) {
2999  if (!isValidPositiveIndexOrPoison(maskPos, kPoisonIndex, indexSize))
3000  return emitOpError("mask index #") << (idx + 1) << " out of range";
3001  }
3002  return success();
3003 }
3004 
3005 LogicalResult
3006 ShuffleOp::inferReturnTypes(MLIRContext *, std::optional<Location>,
3007  ShuffleOp::Adaptor adaptor,
3008  SmallVectorImpl<Type> &inferredReturnTypes) {
3009  auto v1Type = llvm::cast<VectorType>(adaptor.getV1().getType());
3010  auto v1Rank = v1Type.getRank();
3011  // Construct resulting type: leading dimension matches mask
3012  // length, all trailing dimensions match the operands.
3013  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> shape;
3014  shape.reserve(v1Rank);
3015  shape.push_back(std::max<size_t>(1, adaptor.getMask().size()));
3016  // In the 0-D case there is no trailing shape to append.
3017  if (v1Rank > 0)
3018  llvm::append_range(shape, v1Type.getShape().drop_front());
3019  inferredReturnTypes.push_back(
3020  VectorType::get(shape, v1Type.getElementType()));
3021  return success();
3022 }
3023 
3024 template <typename T>
3025 static bool isStepIndexArray(ArrayRef<T> idxArr, uint64_t begin, size_t width) {
3026  T expected = begin;
3027  return idxArr.size() == width && llvm::all_of(idxArr, [&expected](T value) {
3028  return value == expected++;
3029  });
3030 }
3031 
3032 OpFoldResult vector::ShuffleOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
3033  auto v1Type = getV1VectorType();
3034  auto v2Type = getV2VectorType();
3035 
3036  assert(!v1Type.isScalable() && !v2Type.isScalable() &&
3037  "Vector shuffle does not support scalable vectors");
3038 
3039  // For consistency: 0-D shuffle return type is 1-D, this cannot be a folding
3040  // but must be a canonicalization into a vector.broadcast.
3041  if (v1Type.getRank() == 0)
3042  return {};
3043 
3044  // Fold shuffle V1, V2, [0, 1, 2, 3] : <4xi32>, <2xi32> -> V1.
3045  auto mask = getMask();
3046  if (isStepIndexArray(mask, 0, v1Type.getDimSize(0)))
3047  return getV1();
3048  // Fold shuffle V1, V2, [4, 5] : <4xi32>, <2xi32> -> V2.
3049  if (isStepIndexArray(mask, v1Type.getDimSize(0), v2Type.getDimSize(0)))
3050  return getV2();
3051 
3052  Attribute v1Attr = adaptor.getV1(), v2Attr = adaptor.getV2();
3053  if (!v1Attr || !v2Attr)
3054  return {};
3055 
3056  // Fold shuffle poison, poison -> poison.
3057  bool isV1Poison = isa<ub::PoisonAttr>(v1Attr);
3058  bool isV2Poison = isa<ub::PoisonAttr>(v2Attr);
3059  if (isV1Poison && isV2Poison)
3060  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(getContext());
3061 
3062  // Only support 1-D for now to avoid complicated n-D DenseElementsAttr
3063  // manipulation.
3064  if (v1Type.getRank() != 1)
3065  return {};
3066 
3067  // Poison input attributes need special handling as they are not
3068  // DenseElementsAttr. If an index is poison, we select the first element of
3069  // the first non-poison input.
3070  SmallVector<Attribute> v1Elements, v2Elements;
3071  Attribute poisonElement;
3072  if (!isV2Poison) {
3073  auto v2DenseAttr = dyn_cast<DenseElementsAttr>(v2Attr);
3074  if (!v2DenseAttr)
3075  return {};
3076  v2Elements = to_vector(v2DenseAttr.getValues<Attribute>());
3077  poisonElement = v2Elements[0];
3078  }
3079  if (!isV1Poison) {
3080  auto v1DenseAttr = dyn_cast<DenseElementsAttr>(v1Attr);
3081  if (!v1DenseAttr)
3082  return {};
3083  v1Elements = to_vector(v1DenseAttr.getValues<Attribute>());
3084  poisonElement = v1Elements[0];
3085  }
3086 
3087  SmallVector<Attribute> results;
3088  int64_t v1Size = v1Type.getDimSize(0);
3089  for (int64_t maskIdx : mask) {
3090  Attribute indexedElm;
3091  // TODO: Return a partial poison vector when supported by the UB dialect.
3092  if (maskIdx == ShuffleOp::kPoisonIndex) {
3093  indexedElm = poisonElement;
3094  } else {
3095  if (maskIdx < v1Size)
3096  indexedElm = isV1Poison ? poisonElement : v1Elements[maskIdx];
3097  else
3098  indexedElm = isV2Poison ? poisonElement : v2Elements[maskIdx - v1Size];
3099  }
3100 
3101  results.push_back(indexedElm);
3102  }
3103 
3104  return DenseElementsAttr::get(getResultVectorType(), results);
3105 }

3109 // Pattern to rewrite a 0-D shuffle with [0] or [1] mask returning a 1-D vector
3110 // to a broadcast.
3111 struct Canonicalize0DShuffleOp : public OpRewritePattern<ShuffleOp> {
3112  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3113 
3114  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShuffleOp shuffleOp,
3115  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3116  VectorType v1VectorType = shuffleOp.getV1VectorType();
3117  ArrayRef<int64_t> mask = shuffleOp.getMask();
3118  if (v1VectorType.getRank() > 0)
3119  return failure();
3120  if (mask.size() != 1)
3121  return failure();
3122  VectorType resType = VectorType::Builder(v1VectorType).setShape({1});
3123  if (mask[0] == 0)
3124  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(shuffleOp, resType,
3125  shuffleOp.getV1());
3126  else
3127  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(shuffleOp, resType,
3128  shuffleOp.getV2());
3129  return success();
3130  }
3131 };
3132 
3133 /// Consider the defining operation `defOp` of `value`. If `defOp` is a
3134 /// vector.splat or a vector.broadcast with a scalar operand, return the scalar
3135 /// value that is splatted. Otherwise return null.
3136 ///
3137 /// Examples:
3138 ///
3139 /// scalar_source --> vector.splat --> value - return scalar_source
3140 /// scalar_source --> vector.broadcast --> value - return scalar_source
3141 static Value getScalarSplatSource(Value value) {
3142  // Block argument:
3143  Operation *defOp = value.getDefiningOp();
3144  if (!defOp)
3145  return {};
3146 
3147  // Splat:
3148  if (auto splat = dyn_cast<vector::SplatOp>(defOp))
3149  return splat.getInput();
3150 
3151  auto broadcast = dyn_cast<vector::BroadcastOp>(defOp);
3152 
3153  // Not broadcast (and not splat):
3154  if (!broadcast)
3155  return {};
3156 
3157  // Broadcast of a vector:
3158  if (isa<VectorType>(broadcast.getSourceType()))
3159  return {};
3160 
3161  // Broadcast of a scalar:
3162  return broadcast.getSource();
3163 }
3164 
3165 /// Pattern to rewrite shuffle(splat-like(v), splat-like(v)) as broadcast(v).
3166 class ShuffleSplat final : public OpRewritePattern<ShuffleOp> {
3167 public:
3168  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3169 
3170  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShuffleOp op,
3171  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3172  Value splat = getScalarSplatSource(op.getV1());
3173  if (!splat || getScalarSplatSource(op.getV2()) != splat)
3174  return failure();
3175 
3176  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(op, op.getType(), splat);
3177  return success();
3178  }
3179 };
3180 
3181 /// Pattern to rewrite a fixed-size interleave via vector.shuffle to
3182 /// vector.interleave.
3183 class ShuffleInterleave : public OpRewritePattern<ShuffleOp> {
3184 public:
3185  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3186 
3187  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShuffleOp op,
3188  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3189  VectorType resultType = op.getResultVectorType();
3190  if (resultType.isScalable())
3191  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
3192  op, "ShuffleOp can't represent a scalable interleave");
3193 
3194  if (resultType.getRank() != 1)
3195  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
3196  op, "ShuffleOp can't represent an n-D interleave");
3197 
3198  VectorType sourceType = op.getV1VectorType();
3199  if (sourceType != op.getV2VectorType() ||
3200  sourceType.getNumElements() * 2 != resultType.getNumElements()) {
3201  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
3202  op, "ShuffleOp types don't match an interleave");
3203  }
3204 
3205  ArrayRef<int64_t> shuffleMask = op.getMask();
3206  int64_t resultVectorSize = resultType.getNumElements();
3207  for (int i = 0, e = resultVectorSize / 2; i < e; ++i) {
3208  int64_t maskValueA = shuffleMask[i * 2];
3209  int64_t maskValueB = shuffleMask[(i * 2) + 1];
3210  if (maskValueA != i || maskValueB != (resultVectorSize / 2) + i)
3211  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(op,
3212  "ShuffleOp mask not interleaving");
3213  }
3214 
3215  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<InterleaveOp>(op, op.getV1(), op.getV2());
3216  return success();
3217  }
3218 };
3219

3223  MLIRContext *context) {
3224  results.add<ShuffleSplat, ShuffleInterleave, Canonicalize0DShuffleOp>(
3225  context);
3226 }

3274 LogicalResult InsertOp::verify() {
3275  if (auto srcTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(getValueToStoreType()))
3276  if (srcTy.getRank() == 0)
3277  return emitError(
3278  "expected a scalar instead of a 0-d vector as the source operand");
3279 
3280  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> position = getMixedPosition();
3281  auto destVectorType = getDestVectorType();
3282  if (position.size() > static_cast<unsigned>(destVectorType.getRank()))
3283  return emitOpError(
3284  "expected position attribute of rank no greater than dest vector rank");
3285  auto srcVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(getValueToStoreType());
3286  if (srcVectorType &&
3287  (static_cast<unsigned>(srcVectorType.getRank()) + position.size() !=
3288  static_cast<unsigned>(destVectorType.getRank())))
3289  return emitOpError("expected position attribute rank + source rank to "
3290  "match dest vector rank");
3291  if (!srcVectorType &&
3292  (position.size() != static_cast<unsigned>(destVectorType.getRank())))
3293  return emitOpError(
3294  "expected position attribute rank to match the dest vector rank");
3295  for (auto [idx, pos] : llvm::enumerate(position)) {
3296  if (auto attr = dyn_cast<Attribute>(pos)) {
3297  int64_t constIdx = cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt();
3298  if (!isValidPositiveIndexOrPoison(constIdx, kPoisonIndex,
3299  destVectorType.getDimSize(idx))) {
3300  return emitOpError("expected position attribute #")
3301  << (idx + 1)
3302  << " to be a non-negative integer smaller than the "
3303  "corresponding "
3304  "dest vector dimension";
3305  }
3306  }
3307  }
3308  return success();
3309 }
3310 
3311 // Calculate the linearized position of the continuous chunk of elements to
3312 // insert, based on the shape of the value to insert and the positions to insert
3313 // at.
3314 static int64_t calculateInsertPosition(VectorType destTy,
3315  ArrayRef<int64_t> positions) {
3316  llvm::SmallVector<int64_t> completePositions(destTy.getRank(), 0);
3317  assert(positions.size() <= completePositions.size() &&
3318  "positions size must be less than or equal to destTy rank");
3319  copy(positions, completePositions.begin());
3320  return linearize(completePositions, computeStrides(destTy.getShape()));
3321 }

3325 // If insertOp is only inserting unit dimensions it can be transformed to a

3334  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(insertOp.getValueToStoreType());
3335  if (!srcVecType || insertOp.getDestVectorType().getNumElements() !=
3336  srcVecType.getNumElements())
3337  return failure();
3338  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(
3339  insertOp, insertOp.getDestVectorType(), insertOp.getValueToStore());
3340  return success();
3341  }
