3360 
3361 /// Pattern to optimize a chain of insertions.
3362 ///
3363 /// This pattern identifies chains of vector.insert operations that:
3364 /// 1. Only insert values at static positions.
3365 /// 2. Completely initialize all elements in the resulting vector.
3366 /// 3. All intermediate insert operations have only one use.
3367 ///
3368 /// When these conditions are met, the entire chain can be replaced with a
3369 /// single vector.from_elements operation.
3370 ///
3371 /// To keep this pattern simple, and avoid spending too much time on matching
3372 /// fragmented insert chains, this pattern only considers the last insert op in
3373 /// the chain.
3374 ///
3375 /// Example transformation:
3376 /// %poison = ub.poison : vector<2xi32>
3377 /// %0 = vector.insert %c1, %poison[0] : i32 into vector<2xi32>
3378 /// %1 = vector.insert %c2, %0[1] : i32 into vector<2xi32>
3379 /// ->
3380 /// %result = vector.from_elements %c1, %c2 : vector<2xi32>
3381 class InsertChainFullyInitialized final : public OpRewritePattern<InsertOp> {
3382 public:
3383  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3384  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertOp op,
3385  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3386 
3387  VectorType destTy = op.getDestVectorType();
3388  if (destTy.isScalable())
3389  return failure();
3390  // Ensure this is the trailing vector.insert op in a chain of inserts.
3391  for (Operation *user : op.getResult().getUsers())
3392  if (auto insertOp = dyn_cast<InsertOp>(user))
3393  if (insertOp.getDest() == op.getResult())
3394  return failure();
3395 
3396  InsertOp currentOp = op;
3397  SmallVector<InsertOp> chainInsertOps;
3398  while (currentOp) {
3399  // Check cond 1: Dynamic position is not supported.
3400  if (currentOp.hasDynamicPosition())
3401  return failure();
3402 
3403  chainInsertOps.push_back(currentOp);
3404  currentOp = currentOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<InsertOp>();
3405  // Check cond 3: Intermediate inserts have only one use to avoid an
3406  // explosion of vectors.
3407  if (currentOp && !currentOp->hasOneUse())
3408  return failure();
3409  }
3410 
3411  int64_t vectorSize = destTy.getNumElements();
3412  int64_t initializedCount = 0;
3413  SmallVector<bool> initializedDestIdxs(vectorSize, false);
3414  SmallVector<int64_t> pendingInsertPos;
3415  SmallVector<int64_t> pendingInsertSize;
3416  SmallVector<Value> pendingInsertValues;
3417 
3418  for (auto insertOp : chainInsertOps) {
3419  // This pattern can do nothing with poison index.
3420  if (is_contained(insertOp.getStaticPosition(), InsertOp::kPoisonIndex))
3421  return failure();
3422 
3423  // Calculate the linearized position for inserting elements.
3424  int64_t insertBeginPosition =
3425  calculateInsertPosition(destTy, insertOp.getStaticPosition());
3426 
3427  // The valueToStore operand may be a vector or a scalar. Need to handle
3428  // both cases.
3429  int64_t insertSize = 1;
3430  if (auto srcVectorType =
3431  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(insertOp.getValueToStoreType()))
3432  insertSize = srcVectorType.getNumElements();
3433 
3434  assert(insertBeginPosition + insertSize <= vectorSize &&
3435  "insert would overflow the vector");
3436 
3437  for (auto index : llvm::seq<int64_t>(insertBeginPosition,
3438  insertBeginPosition + insertSize)) {
3439  if (initializedDestIdxs[index])
3440  continue;
3441  initializedDestIdxs[index] = true;
3442  ++initializedCount;
3443  }
3444 
3445  // Defer the creation of ops before we can make sure the pattern can
3446  // succeed.
3447  pendingInsertPos.push_back(insertBeginPosition);
3448  pendingInsertSize.push_back(insertSize);
3449  pendingInsertValues.push_back(insertOp.getValueToStore());
3450 
3451  if (initializedCount == vectorSize)
3452  break;
3453  }
3454 
3455  // Check cond 2: all positions must be initialized.
3456  if (initializedCount != vectorSize)
3457  return failure();
3458 
3459  SmallVector<Value> elements(vectorSize);
3460  for (auto [insertBeginPosition, insertSize, valueToStore] :
3461  llvm::reverse(llvm::zip(pendingInsertPos, pendingInsertSize,
3462  pendingInsertValues))) {
3463  auto srcVectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(valueToStore.getType());
3464 
3465  if (!srcVectorType) {
3466  elements[insertBeginPosition] = valueToStore;
3467  continue;
3468  }
3469 
3470  SmallVector<Type> elementToInsertTypes(insertSize,
3471  srcVectorType.getElementType());
3472  // Get all elements from the vector in row-major order.
3473  auto elementsToInsert = vector::ToElementsOp::create(
3474  rewriter, op.getLoc(), elementToInsertTypes, valueToStore);
3475  for (int64_t linearIdx = 0; linearIdx < insertSize; linearIdx++) {
3476  elements[insertBeginPosition + linearIdx] =
3477  elementsToInsert.getResult(linearIdx);
3478  }
3479  }
3480 
3481  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::FromElementsOp>(op, destTy, elements);
3482  return success();
3483  }
3484 };
3485 
3486 } // namespace
3487 
3488 static Attribute
3489 foldDenseElementsAttrDestInsertOp(InsertOp insertOp, Attribute srcAttr,
3490  Attribute dstAttr,
3491  int64_t maxVectorSizeFoldThreshold) {
3492  if (insertOp.hasDynamicPosition())
3493  return {};
3494 
3495  auto denseDst = llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(dstAttr);
3496  if (!denseDst)
3497  return {};
3498 
3499  if (!srcAttr) {
3500  return {};
3501  }
3502 
3503  VectorType destTy = insertOp.getDestVectorType();
3504  if (destTy.isScalable())
3505  return {};
3506 
3507  // Make sure we do not create too many large constants.
3508  if (destTy.getNumElements() > maxVectorSizeFoldThreshold &&
3509  !insertOp->hasOneUse())
3510  return {};
3511 
3512  // Calculate the linearized position for inserting elements.
3513  int64_t insertBeginPosition =
3514  calculateInsertPosition(destTy, insertOp.getStaticPosition());
3515  SmallVector<Attribute> insertedValues;
3516  Type destEltType = destTy.getElementType();
3517 
3518  /// Converts attribute to the expected type if there's
3519  /// a mismatch.
3520  if (auto denseSource = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseElementsAttr>(srcAttr)) {
3521  for (auto value : denseSource.getValues<Attribute>())
3522  insertedValues.push_back(convertNumericAttr(value, destEltType));
3523  } else {
3524  insertedValues.push_back(convertNumericAttr(srcAttr, destEltType));
3525  }
3526 
3527  auto allValues = llvm::to_vector(denseDst.getValues<Attribute>());
3528  copy(insertedValues, allValues.begin() + insertBeginPosition);
3529  auto newAttr = DenseElementsAttr::get(destTy, allValues);
3530 
3531  return newAttr;
3532 }
3533 
3534 /// Folder to replace the `dest` operand of the insert op with the root dest of
3535 /// the insert op use chain.
3536 static Value foldInsertUseChain(InsertOp insertOp) {
3537  auto destInsert = insertOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<InsertOp>();
3538  if (!destInsert)
3539  return {};
3540 
3541  if (insertOp.getMixedPosition() != destInsert.getMixedPosition())
3542  return {};
3543 
3544  insertOp.setOperand(1, destInsert.getDest());
3545  return insertOp.getResult();
3546 }
3547 
3548 void InsertOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
3549  MLIRContext *context) {
3550  results.add<InsertToBroadcast, BroadcastFolder, InsertSplatToSplat,
3551  InsertChainFullyInitialized>(context);
3552 }
3553 
3554 OpFoldResult InsertOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
3555  // Do not create constants with more than `vectorSizeFoldThreashold` elements,
3556  // unless the source vector constant has a single use.
3557  constexpr int64_t vectorSizeFoldThreshold = 256;
3558  // Fold "vector.insert %v, %dest [] : vector<2x2xf32> from vector<2x2xf32>" to
3559  // %v. Note: Do not fold "vector.insert %v, %dest [] : f32 into vector<f32>"
3560  // (type mismatch).
3561  if (getNumIndices() == 0 && getValueToStoreType() == getType())
3562  return getValueToStore();
3563  // Fold `arith.constant` indices into the `vector.insert` operation.
3564  // Do not stop here as this fold may enable subsequent folds that require
3565  // constant indices.
3566  SmallVector<Value> operands = {getValueToStore(), getDest()};
3567  auto inplaceFolded = extractInsertFoldConstantOp(*this, adaptor, operands);
3568 
3569  if (auto res = foldInsertUseChain(*this))
3570  return res;
3571  if (auto res = foldPoisonIndexInsertExtractOp(
3572  getContext(), adaptor.getStaticPosition(), kPoisonIndex))
3573  return res;
3574  if (auto res = foldDenseElementsAttrDestInsertOp(
3575  *this, adaptor.getValueToStore(), adaptor.getDest(),
3576  vectorSizeFoldThreshold)) {
3577  return res;
3578  }
3579 
3580  return inplaceFolded;
3581 }

3587 void InsertStridedSliceOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
3588  Value source, Value dest,
3589  ArrayRef<int64_t> offsets,
3590  ArrayRef<int64_t> strides) {
3591  result.addOperands({source, dest});
3592  auto offsetsAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, offsets);
3593  auto stridesAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, strides);
3594  result.addTypes(dest.getType());
3595  result.addAttribute(InsertStridedSliceOp::getOffsetsAttrName(result.name),
3596  offsetsAttr);
3597  result.addAttribute(InsertStridedSliceOp::getStridesAttrName(result.name),
3598  stridesAttr);
3599 }

3601 // TODO: Should be moved to Tablegen ConfinedAttr attributes.
3602 template <typename OpType>
3603 static LogicalResult isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(OpType op,
3604  ArrayAttr arrayAttr,
3605  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape,
3606  StringRef attrName) {
3607  if (arrayAttr.size() > shape.size())
3608  return op.emitOpError("expected ")
3609  << attrName << " attribute of rank no greater than vector rank";
3610  return success();
3611 }
3612 
3613 // Returns true if all integers in `arrayAttr` are in the half-open [min, max}
3614 // interval. If `halfOpen` is true then the admissible interval is [min, max).
3615 // Otherwise, the admissible interval is [min, max].
3616 template <typename OpType>
3617 static LogicalResult
3618 isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToRange(OpType op, ArrayAttr arrayAttr, int64_t min,
3619  int64_t max, StringRef attrName,
3620  bool halfOpen = true) {
3621  for (auto attr : arrayAttr) {
3622  auto val = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt();
3623  auto upper = max;
3624  if (!halfOpen)
3625  upper += 1;
3626  if (val < min || val >= upper)
3627  return op.emitOpError("expected ") << attrName << " to be confined to ["
3628  << min << ", " << upper << ")";
3629  }
3630  return success();
3631 }
3632 
3633 // Returns true if all integers in `arrayAttr` are in the half-open [min, max}
3634 // interval. If `halfOpen` is true then the admissible interval is [min, max).
3635 // Otherwise, the admissible interval is [min, max].
3636 template <typename OpType>
3637 static LogicalResult
3638 isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(OpType op, ArrayAttr arrayAttr,
3639  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape, StringRef attrName,
3640  bool halfOpen = true, int64_t min = 0) {
3641  for (auto [index, attrDimPair] :
3642  llvm::enumerate(llvm::zip_first(arrayAttr, shape))) {
3643  int64_t val = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(std::get<0>(attrDimPair)).getInt();
3644  int64_t max = std::get<1>(attrDimPair);
3645  if (!halfOpen)
3646  max += 1;
3647  if (val < min || val >= max)
3648  return op.emitOpError("expected ")
3649  << attrName << " dimension " << index << " to be confined to ["
3650  << min << ", " << max << ")";
3651  }
3652  return success();
3653 }
3654 
3655 // Returns true if, for all indices i = 0..shape.size()-1, val is in the
3656 // [min, max} interval:
3657 // val = `arrayAttr1[i]` + `arrayAttr2[i]`,
3658 // If `halfOpen` is true then the admissible interval is [min, max). Otherwise,
3659 // the admissible interval is [min, max].
3660 template <typename OpType>
3661 static LogicalResult isSumOfIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(
3662  OpType op, ArrayAttr arrayAttr1, ArrayAttr arrayAttr2,
3663  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape, StringRef attrName1, StringRef attrName2,
3664  bool halfOpen = true, int64_t min = 1) {
3665  assert(arrayAttr1.size() <= shape.size());
3666  assert(arrayAttr2.size() <= shape.size());
3667  for (auto [index, it] :
3668  llvm::enumerate(llvm::zip(arrayAttr1, arrayAttr2, shape))) {
3669  auto val1 = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(std::get<0>(it)).getInt();
3670  auto val2 = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(std::get<1>(it)).getInt();
3671  int64_t max = std::get<2>(it);
3672  if (!halfOpen)
3673  max += 1;
3674  if (val1 + val2 < 0 || val1 + val2 >= max)
3675  return op.emitOpError("expected sum(")
3676  << attrName1 << ", " << attrName2 << ") dimension " << index
3677  << " to be confined to [" << min << ", " << max << ")";
3678  }
3679  return success();
3680 }
3681 
3682 static ArrayAttr makeI64ArrayAttr(ArrayRef<int64_t> values,
3683  MLIRContext *context) {
3684  auto attrs = llvm::map_range(values, [context](int64_t v) -> Attribute {
3685  return IntegerAttr::get(IntegerType::get(context, 64), APInt(64, v));
3686  });
3687  return ArrayAttr::get(context, llvm::to_vector<8>(attrs));
3688 }
3689 
3690 LogicalResult InsertStridedSliceOp::verify() {
3691  auto sourceVectorType = getSourceVectorType();
3692  auto destVectorType = getDestVectorType();
3693  auto offsets = getOffsetsAttr();
3694  auto strides = getStridesAttr();
3695  if (offsets.size() != static_cast<unsigned>(destVectorType.getRank()))
3696  return emitOpError(
3697  "expected offsets of same size as destination vector rank");
3698  if (strides.size() != static_cast<unsigned>(sourceVectorType.getRank()))
3699  return emitOpError("expected strides of same size as source vector rank");
3700  if (sourceVectorType.getRank() > destVectorType.getRank())
3701  return emitOpError(
3702  "expected source rank to be no greater than destination rank");
3703 
3704  auto sourceShape = sourceVectorType.getShape();
3705  auto destShape = destVectorType.getShape();
3706  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> sourceShapeAsDestShape(
3707  destShape.size() - sourceShape.size(), 0);
3708  sourceShapeAsDestShape.append(sourceShape.begin(), sourceShape.end());
3709  auto offName = InsertStridedSliceOp::getOffsetsAttrName();
3710  auto stridesName = InsertStridedSliceOp::getStridesAttrName();
3711  if (failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, offsets, destShape,
3712  offName)) ||
3713  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToRange(*this, strides, /*min=*/1,
3714  /*max=*/1, stridesName,
3715  /*halfOpen=*/false)) ||
3716  failed(isSumOfIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(
3717  *this, offsets,
3718  makeI64ArrayAttr(sourceShapeAsDestShape, getContext()), destShape,
3719  offName, "source vector shape",
3720  /*halfOpen=*/false, /*min=*/1)))
3721  return failure();
3722 
3723  unsigned rankDiff = destShape.size() - sourceShape.size();
3724  for (unsigned idx = 0; idx < sourceShape.size(); ++idx) {
3725  if (sourceVectorType.getScalableDims()[idx] !=
3726  destVectorType.getScalableDims()[idx + rankDiff]) {
3727  return emitOpError("mismatching scalable flags (at source vector idx=")
3728  << idx << ")";
3729  }
3730  if (sourceVectorType.getScalableDims()[idx]) {
3731  auto sourceSize = sourceShape[idx];
3732  auto destSize = destShape[idx + rankDiff];
3733  if (sourceSize != destSize) {
3734  return emitOpError("expected size at idx=")
3735  << idx
3736  << (" to match the corresponding base size from the input "
3737  "vector (")
3738  << sourceSize << (" vs ") << destSize << (")");
3739  }
3740  }
3741  }
3742 
3743  return success();
3744 }
3745 
3746 namespace {
3747 /// Rewrite insert_strided_slice(splat-like(v), splat-like(v)) as v.
3748 class FoldInsertStridedSliceSplat final
3749  : public OpRewritePattern<InsertStridedSliceOp> {
3750 public:
3751  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3752 
3753  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertStridedSliceOp insertStridedSliceOp,
3754  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3755 
3756  auto dst = insertStridedSliceOp.getDest();
3757  auto splat = getScalarSplatSource(insertStridedSliceOp.getValueToStore());
3758  if (!splat || getScalarSplatSource(dst) != splat)
3759  return failure();
3760 
3761  rewriter.replaceOp(insertStridedSliceOp, dst);
3762  return success();
3763  }
3764 };
3765 
3766 /// Pattern to rewrite an InsertStridedSliceOp(ExtractStridedSliceOp(dst), dst)
3767 /// to dst.
3768 class FoldInsertStridedSliceOfExtract final
3769  : public OpRewritePattern<InsertStridedSliceOp> {
3770 public:
3771  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3772 
3773  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertStridedSliceOp insertStridedSliceOp,
3774  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3775  auto extractStridedSliceOp =
3776  insertStridedSliceOp.getValueToStore()
3777  .getDefiningOp<vector::ExtractStridedSliceOp>();
3778 
3779  if (!extractStridedSliceOp)
3780  return failure();
3781 
3782  if (extractStridedSliceOp.getOperand() != insertStridedSliceOp.getDest())
3783  return failure();
3784 
3785  // Check if have the same strides and offsets.
3786  if (extractStridedSliceOp.getStrides() !=
3787  insertStridedSliceOp.getStrides() ||
3788  extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets() != insertStridedSliceOp.getOffsets())
3789  return failure();
3790 
3791  rewriter.replaceOp(insertStridedSliceOp, insertStridedSliceOp.getDest());
3792  return success();
3793  }
3794 };
3795 
3796 // Pattern to rewrite an InsertStridedSliceOp(ConstantOp into ConstantOp) ->
3797 // ConstantOp.
3798 class InsertStridedSliceConstantFolder final
3799  : public OpRewritePattern<InsertStridedSliceOp> {
3800 public:
3801  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3802 
3803  // Do not create constants with more than `vectorSizeFoldThreashold` elements,
3804  // unless the source vector constant has a single use.
3805  static constexpr int64_t vectorSizeFoldThreshold = 256;
3806 
3807  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertStridedSliceOp op,
3808  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3809  // Return if 'InsertOp' operand is not defined by a compatible vector
3810  // ConstantOp.
3811  TypedValue<VectorType> destVector = op.getDest();
3812  Attribute vectorDestCst;
3813  if (!matchPattern(destVector, m_Constant(&vectorDestCst)))
3814  return failure();
3815 
3816  VectorType destTy = destVector.getType();
3817  if (destTy.isScalable())
3818  return failure();
3819 
3820  // Make sure we do not create too many large constants.
3821  if (destTy.getNumElements() > vectorSizeFoldThreshold &&
3822  !destVector.hasOneUse())
3823  return failure();
3824 
3825  TypedValue<VectorType> sourceValue = op.getValueToStore();
3826  Attribute sourceCst;
3827  if (!matchPattern(sourceValue, m_Constant(&sourceCst)))
3828  return failure();
3829 
3830  // TODO: Support poison.
3831  if (isa<ub::PoisonAttr>(vectorDestCst) || isa<ub::PoisonAttr>(sourceCst))
3832  return failure();
3833 
3834  // TODO: Handle non-unit strides when they become available.
3835  if (op.hasNonUnitStrides())
3836  return failure();
3837 
3838  VectorType sliceVecTy = sourceValue.getType();
3839  ArrayRef<int64_t> sliceShape = sliceVecTy.getShape();
3840  int64_t rankDifference = destTy.getRank() - sliceVecTy.getRank();
3841  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsets = getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets());
3842  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> destStrides = computeStrides(destTy.getShape());
3843 
3844  // Calcualte the destination element indices by enumerating all slice
3845  // positions within the destination and linearizing them. The enumeration
3846  // order is lexicographic which yields a sequence of monotonically
3847  // increasing linearized position indices.
3848  // Because the destination may have higher dimensionality then the slice,
3849  // we keep track of two overlapping sets of positions and offsets.
3850  auto denseDest = llvm::cast<DenseElementsAttr>(vectorDestCst);
3851  auto denseSlice = llvm::cast<DenseElementsAttr>(sourceCst);
3852  auto sliceValuesIt = denseSlice.value_begin<Attribute>();
3853  auto newValues = llvm::to_vector(denseDest.getValues<Attribute>());
3854  SmallVector<int64_t> currDestPosition(offsets.begin(), offsets.end());
3855  MutableArrayRef<int64_t> currSlicePosition(
3856  currDestPosition.begin() + rankDifference, currDestPosition.end());
3857  ArrayRef<int64_t> sliceOffsets(offsets.begin() + rankDifference,
3858  offsets.end());
3859  do {
3860  int64_t linearizedPosition = linearize(currDestPosition, destStrides);
3861  assert(linearizedPosition < destTy.getNumElements() && "Invalid index");
3862  assert(sliceValuesIt != denseSlice.value_end<Attribute>() &&
3863  "Invalid slice element");
3864  newValues[linearizedPosition] = *sliceValuesIt;
3865  ++sliceValuesIt;
3866  } while (succeeded(
3867  incSlicePosition(currSlicePosition, sliceShape, sliceOffsets)));
3868 
3869  auto newAttr = DenseElementsAttr::get(destTy, newValues);
3870  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<arith::ConstantOp>(op, newAttr);
3871  return success();
3872  }
3873 };
3874 
3875 } // namespace

3879  results.add<FoldInsertStridedSliceSplat, FoldInsertStridedSliceOfExtract,
3880  InsertStridedSliceConstantFolder>(context);
3881 }

3886  return {};

3900 void OuterProductOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
3901  p << " " << getLhs() << ", " << getRhs();
3902  if (getAcc()) {
3903  p << ", " << getAcc();
3904  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs());
3905  }
3906  p << " : " << getLhs().getType() << ", " << getRhs().getType();

3908 
3909 ParseResult OuterProductOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
3910  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 3> operandsInfo;
3911  Type tLHS, tRHS;
3912  if (parser.parseOperandList(operandsInfo) ||
3913  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
3914  parser.parseColonType(tLHS) || parser.parseComma() ||
3915  parser.parseType(tRHS))
3916  return failure();
3917  if (operandsInfo.size() < 2)
3918  return parser.emitError(parser.getNameLoc(),
3919  "expected at least 2 operands");
3920  VectorType vLHS = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(tLHS);
3921  VectorType vRHS = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(tRHS);
3922  if (!vLHS)
3923  return parser.emitError(parser.getNameLoc(),
3924  "expected vector type for operand #1");
3925 
3926  VectorType resType;
3927  if (vRHS) {
3928  SmallVector<bool> scalableDimsRes{vLHS.getScalableDims()[0],
3929  vRHS.getScalableDims()[0]};
3930  resType = VectorType::get({vLHS.getDimSize(0), vRHS.getDimSize(0)},
3931  vLHS.getElementType(), scalableDimsRes);
3932  } else {
3933  // Scalar RHS operand
3934  SmallVector<bool> scalableDimsRes{vLHS.getScalableDims()[0]};
3935  resType = VectorType::get({vLHS.getDimSize(0)}, vLHS.getElementType(),
3936  scalableDimsRes);
3937  }
3938 
3939  if (!result.attributes.get(OuterProductOp::getKindAttrName(result.name))) {
3940  result.attributes.append(
3941  OuterProductOp::getKindAttrName(result.name),
3942  CombiningKindAttr::get(result.getContext(),
3943  OuterProductOp::getDefaultKind()));
3944  }
3945 
3946  return failure(
3947  parser.resolveOperand(operandsInfo[0], tLHS, result.operands) ||
3948  parser.resolveOperand(operandsInfo[1], tRHS, result.operands) ||
3949  (operandsInfo.size() > 2 &&
3950  parser.resolveOperand(operandsInfo[2], resType, result.operands)) ||
3951  parser.addTypeToList(resType, result.types));
3952 }
3953 
3954 LogicalResult OuterProductOp::verify() {
3955  Type tRHS = getOperandTypeRHS();
3956  VectorType vLHS = getOperandVectorTypeLHS(),
3957  vRHS = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(tRHS),
3958  vACC = getOperandVectorTypeACC(), vRES = getResultVectorType();
3959 
3960  if (vLHS.getRank() != 1)
3961  return emitOpError("expected 1-d vector for operand #1");
3962 
3963  if (vRHS) {
3964  // Proper OUTER operation.
3965  if (vRHS.getRank() != 1)
3966  return emitOpError("expected 1-d vector for operand #2");
3967  if (vRES.getRank() != 2)
3968  return emitOpError("expected 2-d vector result");
3969  if (vLHS.getDimSize(0) != vRES.getDimSize(0))
3970  return emitOpError("expected #1 operand dim to match result dim #1");
3971  if (vRHS.getDimSize(0) != vRES.getDimSize(1))
3972  return emitOpError("expected #2 operand dim to match result dim #2");
3973  if (vLHS.isScalable() && !vRHS.isScalable()) {
3974  // This restriction reflects what's currently supported in terms of
3975  // scalable vectors. However, we could relax this if there's a use case.
3976  return emitOpError(
3977  "expected either both or only #2 operand dim to be scalable");
3978  }
3979  } else {
3980  // An AXPY operation.
3981  if (vRES.getRank() != 1)
3982  return emitOpError("expected 1-d vector result");
3983  if (vLHS.getDimSize(0) != vRES.getDimSize(0))
3984  return emitOpError("expected #1 operand dim to match result dim #1");
3985  }
3986 
3987  if (vACC && vACC != vRES)
3988  return emitOpError("expected operand #3 of same type as result type");
3989 
3990  // Verify supported combining kind.
3991  if (!isSupportedCombiningKind(getKind(), vRES.getElementType()))
3992  return emitOpError("unsupported outerproduct type");
3993 
3994  return success();
3995 }
3996 
3997 // MaskableOpInterface methods.
3998 
3999 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
4000 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
4001 Type OuterProductOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
4002  auto vecType = this->getResultVectorType();
4003  return VectorType::get(vecType.getShape(),
4004  IntegerType::get(vecType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
4005  vecType.getScalableDims());
4006 }
4007 
4008 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4009 // ExtractStridedSliceOp
4010 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4011 
4012 // Inference works as follows:
4013 // 1. Add 'sizes' from prefix of dims in 'offsets'.
4014 // 2. Add sizes from 'vectorType' for remaining dims.
4015 // Scalable flags are inherited from 'vectorType'.
4016 static Type inferStridedSliceOpResultType(VectorType vectorType,
4017  ArrayAttr offsets, ArrayAttr sizes,
4018  ArrayAttr strides) {
4019  assert(offsets.size() == sizes.size() && offsets.size() == strides.size());
4020  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> shape;
4021  shape.reserve(vectorType.getRank());
4022  unsigned idx = 0;
4023  for (unsigned e = offsets.size(); idx < e; ++idx)
4024  shape.push_back(llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(sizes[idx]).getInt());
4025  for (unsigned e = vectorType.getShape().size(); idx < e; ++idx)
4026  shape.push_back(vectorType.getShape()[idx]);
4027 
4028  return VectorType::get(shape, vectorType.getElementType(),
4029  vectorType.getScalableDims());
4030 }
4031 
4032 void ExtractStridedSliceOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
4033  Value source, ArrayRef<int64_t> offsets,
4034  ArrayRef<int64_t> sizes,
4035  ArrayRef<int64_t> strides) {
4036  result.addOperands(source);
4037  auto offsetsAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, offsets);
4038  auto sizesAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, sizes);
4039  auto stridesAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, strides);
4040  result.addTypes(
4041  inferStridedSliceOpResultType(llvm::cast<VectorType>(source.getType()),
4042  offsetsAttr, sizesAttr, stridesAttr));
4043  result.addAttribute(ExtractStridedSliceOp::getOffsetsAttrName(result.name),
4044  offsetsAttr);
4045  result.addAttribute(ExtractStridedSliceOp::getSizesAttrName(result.name),
4046  sizesAttr);
4047  result.addAttribute(ExtractStridedSliceOp::getStridesAttrName(result.name),
4048  stridesAttr);
4049 }
4050 
4051 LogicalResult ExtractStridedSliceOp::verify() {
4052  auto type = getSourceVectorType();
4053  auto offsets = getOffsetsAttr();
4054  auto sizes = getSizesAttr();
4055  auto strides = getStridesAttr();
4056  if (offsets.size() != sizes.size() || offsets.size() != strides.size())
4057  return emitOpError(
4058  "expected offsets, sizes and strides attributes of same size");
4059 
4060  auto shape = type.getShape();
4061  auto offName = getOffsetsAttrName();
4062  auto sizesName = getSizesAttrName();
4063  auto stridesName = getStridesAttrName();
4064  if (failed(
4065  isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(*this, offsets, shape, offName)) ||
4066  failed(
4067  isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(*this, sizes, shape, sizesName)) ||
4068  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(*this, strides, shape,
4069  stridesName)) ||
4070  failed(
4071  isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, offsets, shape, offName)) ||
4072  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, sizes, shape, sizesName,
4073  /*halfOpen=*/false,
4074  /*min=*/1)) ||
4075  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToRange(*this, strides, /*min=*/1,
4076  /*max=*/1, stridesName,
4077  /*halfOpen=*/false)) ||
4078  failed(isSumOfIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, offsets, sizes,
4079  shape, offName, sizesName,
4080  /*halfOpen=*/false)))
4081  return failure();
4082 
4083  auto resultType = inferStridedSliceOpResultType(getSourceVectorType(),
4084  offsets, sizes, strides);
4085  if (getResult().getType() != resultType)
4086  return emitOpError("expected result type to be ") << resultType;
4087 
4088  for (unsigned idx = 0; idx < sizes.size(); ++idx) {
4089  if (type.getScalableDims()[idx]) {
4090  auto inputDim = type.getShape()[idx];
4091  auto inputSize = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(sizes[idx]).getInt();
4092  if (inputDim != inputSize)
4093  return emitOpError("expected size at idx=")
4094  << idx
4095  << (" to match the corresponding base size from the input "
4096  "vector (")
4097  << inputSize << (" vs ") << inputDim << (")");
4098  }
4099  }
4100 
4101  return success();
4102 }
4103 
4104 // When the source of ExtractStrided comes from a chain of InsertStrided ops try
4105 // to use the source of the InsertStrided ops if we can detect that the
4106 // extracted vector is a subset of one of the vector inserted.
4107 static LogicalResult
4108 foldExtractStridedOpFromInsertChain(ExtractStridedSliceOp op) {
4109  // Helper to extract integer out of ArrayAttr.
4110  auto getElement = [](ArrayAttr array, int idx) {
4111  return llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(array[idx]).getInt();
4112  };
4113  ArrayAttr extractOffsets = op.getOffsets();
4114  ArrayAttr extractStrides = op.getStrides();
4115  ArrayAttr extractSizes = op.getSizes();
4116  auto insertOp = op.getSource().getDefiningOp<InsertStridedSliceOp>();
4117  while (insertOp) {
4118  if (op.getSourceVectorType().getRank() !=
4119  insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank())
4120  return failure();
4121  ArrayAttr insertOffsets = insertOp.getOffsets();
4122  ArrayAttr insertStrides = insertOp.getStrides();
4123  // If the rank of extract is greater than the rank of insert, we are likely
4124  // extracting a partial chunk of the vector inserted.
4125  if (extractOffsets.size() > insertOffsets.size())
4126  return failure();
4127  bool patialoverlap = false;
4128  bool disjoint = false;
4129  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsetDiffs;
4130  for (unsigned dim = 0, e = extractOffsets.size(); dim < e; ++dim) {
4131  if (getElement(extractStrides, dim) != getElement(insertStrides, dim))
4132  return failure();
4133  int64_t start = getElement(insertOffsets, dim);
4134  int64_t end = start + insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getDimSize(dim);
4135  int64_t offset = getElement(extractOffsets, dim);
4136  int64_t size = getElement(extractSizes, dim);
4137  // Check if the start of the extract offset is in the interval inserted.
4138  if (start <= offset && offset < end) {
4139  // If the extract interval overlaps but is not fully included we may
4140  // have a partial overlap that will prevent any folding.
4141  if (offset + size > end)
4142  patialoverlap = true;
4143  offsetDiffs.push_back(offset - start);
4144  continue;
4145  }
4146  disjoint = true;
4147  break;
4148  }
4149  // The extract element chunk is a subset of the insert element.
4150  if (!disjoint && !patialoverlap) {
4151  op.setOperand(insertOp.getValueToStore());
4152  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
4153  OpBuilder b(op.getContext());
4154  op.setOffsetsAttr(b.getI64ArrayAttr(offsetDiffs));
4155  return success();
4156  }
4157  // If the chunk extracted is disjoint from the chunk inserted, keep looking
4158  // in the insert chain.
4159  if (disjoint)
4160  insertOp = insertOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<InsertStridedSliceOp>();
4161  else {
4162  // The extracted vector partially overlap the inserted vector, we cannot
4163  // fold.
4164  return failure();
4165  }
4166  }
4167  return failure();
4168 }
4169 
4170 // ExtractStridedSliceOp(non-splat ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4171 static OpFoldResult
4172 foldExtractStridedSliceNonSplatConstant(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4173  Attribute foldInput) {
4174 
4175  auto dense = llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(foldInput);
4176  if (!dense)
4177  return {};
4178 
4179  // TODO: Handle non-unit strides when they become available.
4180  if (op.hasNonUnitStrides())
4181  return {};
4182 
4183  VectorType sourceVecTy = op.getSourceVectorType();
4184  ArrayRef<int64_t> sourceShape = sourceVecTy.getShape();
4185  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> sourceStrides = computeStrides(sourceShape);
4186 
4187  VectorType sliceVecTy = op.getType();
4188  ArrayRef<int64_t> sliceShape = sliceVecTy.getShape();
4189  int64_t rank = sliceVecTy.getRank();
4190 
4191  // Expand offsets and sizes to match the vector rank.
4192  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsets(rank, 0);
4193  copy(getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets()), offsets.begin());
4194 
4195  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> sizes(sourceShape);
4196  copy(getI64SubArray(op.getSizes()), sizes.begin());
4197 
4198  // Calculate the slice elements by enumerating all slice positions and
4199  // linearizing them. The enumeration order is lexicographic which yields a
4200  // sequence of monotonically increasing linearized position indices.
4201  const auto denseValuesBegin = dense.value_begin<Attribute>();
4202  SmallVector<Attribute> sliceValues;
4203  sliceValues.reserve(sliceVecTy.getNumElements());
4204  SmallVector<int64_t> currSlicePosition(offsets.begin(), offsets.end());
4205  do {
4206  int64_t linearizedPosition = linearize(currSlicePosition, sourceStrides);
4207  assert(linearizedPosition < sourceVecTy.getNumElements() &&
4208  "Invalid index");
4209  sliceValues.push_back(*(denseValuesBegin + linearizedPosition));
4210  } while (succeeded(incSlicePosition(currSlicePosition, sliceShape, offsets)));
4211 
4212  assert(static_cast<int64_t>(sliceValues.size()) ==
4213  sliceVecTy.getNumElements() &&
4214  "Invalid number of slice elements");
4215  return DenseElementsAttr::get(sliceVecTy, sliceValues);
4216 }
4217 
4218 OpFoldResult ExtractStridedSliceOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
4219  if (getSourceVectorType() == getResult().getType())
4220  return getSource();
4221  if (succeeded(foldExtractStridedOpFromInsertChain(*this)))
4222  return getResult();
4223 
4224  // ExtractStridedSliceOp(splat ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4225  if (auto splat =
4226  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<SplatElementsAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
4227  DenseElementsAttr::get(getType(), splat.getSplatValue<Attribute>());
4228 
4229  // ExtractStridedSliceOp(non-splat ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4230  return foldExtractStridedSliceNonSplatConstant(*this, adaptor.getSource());
4231 }
4232 
4233 void ExtractStridedSliceOp::getOffsets(SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &results) {
4234  populateFromInt64AttrArray(getOffsets(), results);
4235 }

4239 // Pattern to rewrite an ExtractStridedSliceOp(CreateMaskOp) to
4240 // CreateMaskOp.
4241 //
4242 // Example:
4243 //
4244 // %mask = vector.create_mask %ub : vector<16xi1>
4245 // %slice = vector.extract_strided_slice [%offset] [8] [1]
4246 //
4247 // to
4248 //
4249 // %new_ub = arith.subi %ub, %offset
4250 // %mask = vector.create_mask %new_ub : vector<8xi1>
4251 class StridedSliceCreateMaskFolder final
4252  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4253  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4254 
4255 public:
4256  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp extractStridedSliceOp,
4257  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4258  Location loc = extractStridedSliceOp.getLoc();
4259  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' operand is not defined by a
4260  // CreateMaskOp.
4261  auto createMaskOp =
4262  extractStridedSliceOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<CreateMaskOp>();
4263  if (!createMaskOp)
4264  return failure();
4265  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' has non-unit strides.
4266  if (extractStridedSliceOp.hasNonUnitStrides())
4267  return failure();
4268  // Gather constant mask dimension sizes.
4269  SmallVector<Value> maskDimSizes(createMaskOp.getOperands());
4270  // Gather strided slice offsets and sizes.
4271  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceOffsets;
4272  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets(),
4273  sliceOffsets);
4274  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceSizes;
4275  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getSizes(), sliceSizes);
4276 
4277  // Compute slice of vector mask region.
4278  SmallVector<Value> sliceMaskDimSizes;
4279  sliceMaskDimSizes.reserve(maskDimSizes.size());
4280  // sliceOffsets.size() <= maskDimSizes.size(), so we use llvm::zip and
4281  // only iterate on the leading dim sizes. The tail accounts for the
4282  // remaining dim sizes.
4283  for (auto [maskDimSize, sliceOffset, sliceSize] :
4284  llvm::zip(maskDimSizes, sliceOffsets, sliceSizes)) {
4285  // No need to clamp on min/max values, because create_mask has clamping
4286  // semantics, i.e. the sliceMaskDimSize is allowed to be negative or
4287  // greater than the vector dim size.
4288  IntegerAttr offsetAttr =
4289  rewriter.getIntegerAttr(maskDimSize.getType(), sliceOffset);
4290  Value offset = arith::ConstantOp::create(rewriter, loc, offsetAttr);
4291  Value sliceMaskDimSize =
4292  arith::SubIOp::create(rewriter, loc, maskDimSize, offset);
4293  sliceMaskDimSizes.push_back(sliceMaskDimSize);
4294  }
4295  // Add unchanged dimensions.
4296  llvm::append_range(
4297  sliceMaskDimSizes,
4298  llvm::drop_begin(maskDimSizes, sliceMaskDimSizes.size()));
4299  // Replace 'extractStridedSliceOp' with CreateMaskOp with sliced mask
4300  // region.
4301  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<CreateMaskOp>(
4302  extractStridedSliceOp, extractStridedSliceOp.getResult().getType(),
4303  sliceMaskDimSizes);
4304  return success();
4305  }
4306 };
4307 
4308 // Pattern to rewrite an ExtractStridedSliceOp(ConstantMaskOp) to
4309 // ConstantMaskOp.
4310 class StridedSliceConstantMaskFolder final
4311  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4312 public:
4313  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4314 
4315  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp extractStridedSliceOp,
4316  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4317  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' operand is not defined by a
4318  // ConstantMaskOp.
4319  auto *defOp = extractStridedSliceOp.getSource().getDefiningOp();
4320  auto constantMaskOp = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantMaskOp>(defOp);
4321  if (!constantMaskOp)
4322  return failure();
4323  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' has non-unit strides.
4324  if (extractStridedSliceOp.hasNonUnitStrides())
4325  return failure();
4326  // Gather constant mask dimension sizes.
4327  ArrayRef<int64_t> maskDimSizes = constantMaskOp.getMaskDimSizes();
4328  // Gather strided slice offsets and sizes.
4329  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceOffsets;
4330  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets(),
4331  sliceOffsets);
4332  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceSizes;
4333  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getSizes(), sliceSizes);
4334 
4335  // Compute slice of vector mask region.
4336  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceMaskDimSizes;
4337  sliceMaskDimSizes.reserve(maskDimSizes.size());
4338  for (auto [maskDimSize, sliceOffset, sliceSize] :
4339  llvm::zip(maskDimSizes, sliceOffsets, sliceSizes)) {
4340  int64_t sliceMaskDimSize = std::max(
4341  static_cast<int64_t>(0),
4342  std::min(sliceOffset + sliceSize, maskDimSize) - sliceOffset);
4343  sliceMaskDimSizes.push_back(sliceMaskDimSize);
4344  }
4345  // Add unchanged dimensions.
4346  if (sliceMaskDimSizes.size() < maskDimSizes.size())
4347  for (size_t i = sliceMaskDimSizes.size(); i < maskDimSizes.size(); ++i)
4348  sliceMaskDimSizes.push_back(maskDimSizes[i]);
4349  // If any of 'sliceMaskDimSizes' are zero, then set all to zero (masked
4350  // region is a conjunction of mask dim intervals).
4351  if (llvm::is_contained(sliceMaskDimSizes, 0))
4352  sliceMaskDimSizes.assign(maskDimSizes.size(), 0);
4353 
4354  // Replace 'extractStridedSliceOp' with ConstantMaskOp with sliced mask
4355  // region.
4356  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<ConstantMaskOp>(
4357  extractStridedSliceOp, extractStridedSliceOp.getResult().getType(),
4358  sliceMaskDimSizes);
4359  return success();
4360  }
4361 };
4362 
4363 // Pattern to rewrite an ExtractStridedSliceOp(BroadcastOp) to
4364 // BroadcastOp(ExtractStrideSliceOp).
4365 class StridedSliceBroadcast final
4366  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4367 public:
4368  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4369 
4370  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4371  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4372  auto broadcast = op.getSource().getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>();
4373  if (!broadcast)
4374  return failure();
4375  auto srcVecType =
4376  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(broadcast.getSource().getType());
4377  unsigned srcRank = srcVecType ? srcVecType.getRank() : 0;
4378  auto dstVecType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(op.getType());
4379  unsigned dstRank = dstVecType.getRank();
4380  unsigned rankDiff = dstRank - srcRank;
4381  // Source dimensions can be broadcasted (1 -> n with n > 1) or sliced
4382  // (n -> m with n > m). If they are originally both broadcasted *and*
4383  // sliced, this can be simplified to just broadcasting.
4384  bool needsSlice = false;
4385  for (unsigned i = 0; i < srcRank; i++) {
4386  if (srcVecType.getDimSize(i) != 1 &&
4387  srcVecType.getDimSize(i) != dstVecType.getDimSize(i + rankDiff)) {
4388  needsSlice = true;
4389  break;
4390  }
4391  }
4392  Value source = broadcast.getSource();
4393  if (needsSlice) {
4394  SmallVector<int64_t> offsets =
4395  getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets(), /*dropFront=*/rankDiff);
4396  SmallVector<int64_t> sizes =
4397  getI64SubArray(op.getSizes(), /*dropFront=*/rankDiff);
4398  for (unsigned i = 0; i < srcRank; i++) {
4399  if (srcVecType.getDimSize(i) == 1) {
4400  // In case this dimension was broadcasted *and* sliced, the offset
4401  // and size need to be updated now that there is no broadcast before
4402  // the slice.
4403  offsets[i] = 0;
4404  sizes[i] = 1;
4405  }
4406  }
4407  source = ExtractStridedSliceOp::create(
4408  rewriter, op->getLoc(), source, offsets, sizes,
4409  getI64SubArray(op.getStrides(), /*dropFront=*/rankDiff));
4410  }
4411  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(op, op.getType(), source);
4412  return success();
4413  }
4414 };
4415 
4416 /// Rewrite extract_strided_slice(splat-like(v)) with broadcast(v).
4417 class StridedSliceSplat final : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4418 public:
4419  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4420 
4421  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4422  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4423 
4424  Value splat = getScalarSplatSource(op.getSource());
4425  if (!splat)
4426  return failure();
4427  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(op, op.getType(), splat);
4428  return success();
4429  }
4430 };
4431 
4432 /// Pattern to rewrite simple cases of N-D extract_strided_slice, where the
4433 /// slice is contiguous, into extract and shape_cast.
4434 ///
4435 /// Example:
4436 /// Before:
4437 /// %1 = vector.extract_strided_slice %arg0 {
4438 /// offsets = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0],
4439 /// sizes = [1, 1, 1, 1, 8],
4440 /// strides = [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]
4441 /// } : vector<8x1x1x2x8xi8> to vector<1x1x1x1x8xi8>
4442 /// After:
4443 /// %0 = vector.extract %arg0[0, 0, 0, 0]
4444 /// : vector<8xi8> from vector<8x1x1x2x8xi8>
4445 /// %1 = vector.shape_cast %0
4446 /// : vector<8xi8> to vector<1x1x1x1x8xi8>
4447 ///
4448 class ContiguousExtractStridedSliceToExtract final
4449  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4450 public:
4451  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4452 
4453  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4454  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4455  if (op.hasNonUnitStrides())
4456  return failure();
4457  Value source = op.getOperand();
4458  auto sourceType = cast<VectorType>(source.getType());
4459  if (sourceType.isScalable() || sourceType.getRank() == 0)
4460  return failure();
4461 
4462  // Compute the number of offsets to pass to ExtractOp::build. That is the
4463  // difference between the source rank and the desired slice rank. We walk
4464  // the dimensions from innermost out, and stop when the next slice dimension
4465  // is not full-size.
4466  SmallVector<int64_t> sizes = getI64SubArray(op.getSizes());
4467  int numOffsets;
4468  for (numOffsets = sizes.size(); numOffsets > 0; --numOffsets) {
4469  if (sizes[numOffsets - 1] != sourceType.getDimSize(numOffsets - 1))
4470  break;
4471  }
4472 
4473  // If the created extract op would have no offsets, then this whole
4474  // extract_strided_slice is the identity and should have been handled by
4475  // other canonicalizations.
4476  if (numOffsets == 0)
4477  return failure();
4478 
4479  // If not even the inner-most dimension is full-size, this op can't be
4480  // rewritten as an ExtractOp.
4481  if (numOffsets == sourceType.getRank() &&
4482  static_cast<int>(sizes.size()) == sourceType.getRank())
4483  return failure();
4484 
4485  // The outer dimensions must have unit size.
4486  for (int i = 0; i < numOffsets; ++i) {
4487  if (sizes[i] != 1)
4488  return failure();
4489  }
4490 
4491  // Avoid generating slices that have leading unit dimensions. The shape_cast
4492  // op that we create below would take bad generic fallback patterns
4493  // (ShapeCastOpRewritePattern).
4494  while (numOffsets < static_cast<int>(sizes.size()) - 1 &&
4495  sizes[numOffsets] == 1) {
4496  ++numOffsets;
4497  }
4498 
4499  SmallVector<int64_t> offsets = getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets());
4500  auto extractOffsets = ArrayRef(offsets).take_front(numOffsets);
4501  Value extract = vector::ExtractOp::create(rewriter, op->getLoc(), source,
4502  extractOffsets);
4503  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(op, op.getType(), extract);
4504  return success();
4505  }
4506 };
4507 
4508 } // namespace
4509 
4510 void ExtractStridedSliceOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(
4511  RewritePatternSet &results, MLIRContext *context) {
4512  // Pattern to rewrite a ExtractStridedSliceOp(ConstantMaskOp) ->
4513  // ConstantMaskOp and ExtractStridedSliceOp(ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4514  results.add<StridedSliceCreateMaskFolder, StridedSliceConstantMaskFolder,
4515  StridedSliceBroadcast, StridedSliceSplat,
4516  ContiguousExtractStridedSliceToExtract>(context);
4517 }

4523 /// 1. Builder that sets padding to zero and an empty mask (variant with attrs).
4524 void TransferReadOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
4525  VectorType vectorType, Value source,
4526  ValueRange indices, std::optional<Value> padding,
4527  AffineMapAttr permutationMapAttr,
4528  /*optional*/ ArrayAttr inBoundsAttr) {
4529 
4530  Type elemType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType()).getElementType();
4531  if (!padding)
4532  padding = ub::PoisonOp::create(builder, result.location, elemType);
4533  build(builder, result, vectorType, source, indices, permutationMapAttr,
4534  *padding, /*mask=*/Value(), inBoundsAttr);
4535 }
4536 
4537 /// 2. Builder that sets padding to zero an empty mask (variant without attrs).
4538 void TransferReadOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
4539  VectorType vectorType, Value source,
4540  ValueRange indices, std::optional<Value> padding,
4541  AffineMap permutationMap,
4542  std::optional<ArrayRef<bool>> inBounds) {
4543  auto permutationMapAttr = AffineMapAttr::get(permutationMap);
4544  auto inBoundsAttr = (inBounds && !inBounds.value().empty())
4545  ? builder.getBoolArrayAttr(inBounds.value())
4546  : builder.getBoolArrayAttr(
4547  SmallVector<bool>(vectorType.getRank(), false));
4548  Type elemType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType()).getElementType();
4549  if (!padding)
4550  padding = ub::PoisonOp::create(builder, result.location, elemType);
4551  build(builder, result, vectorType, source, indices, *padding,
4552  permutationMapAttr, inBoundsAttr);
4553 }
4554 
4555 /// 3. Builder that sets permutation map to 'getMinorIdentityMap'.
4556 void TransferReadOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
4557  VectorType vectorType, Value source,
4558  ValueRange indices, std::optional<Value> padding,
4559  std::optional<ArrayRef<bool>> inBounds) {
4560  AffineMap permutationMap = getTransferMinorIdentityMap(
4561  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType()), vectorType);
4562  auto permutationMapAttr = AffineMapAttr::get(permutationMap);
4563  auto inBoundsAttr = (inBounds && !inBounds.value().empty())
4564  ? builder.getBoolArrayAttr(inBounds.value())
4565  : builder.getBoolArrayAttr(
4566  SmallVector<bool>(vectorType.getRank(), false));
4567  Type elemType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType()).getElementType();
4568  if (!padding)
4569  padding = ub::PoisonOp::create(builder, result.location, elemType);
4570  build(builder, result, vectorType, source, indices, permutationMapAttr,
4571  *padding,
4572  /*mask=*/Value(), inBoundsAttr);
4573 }
4574 
4575 template <typename EmitFun>
4576 static LogicalResult verifyPermutationMap(AffineMap permutationMap,
4577  EmitFun emitOpError) {
4578  SmallVector<bool, 8> seen(permutationMap.getNumInputs(), false);
4579  for (auto expr : permutationMap.getResults()) {
4580  auto dim = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(expr);
4581  auto zero = dyn_cast<AffineConstantExpr>(expr);
4582  if (zero) {
4583  if (zero.getValue() != 0) {
4584  return emitOpError(
4585  "requires a projected permutation_map (at most one dim or the zero "
4586  "constant can appear in each result)");
4587  }
4588  continue;
4589  }
4590  if (!dim) {
4591  return emitOpError("requires a projected permutation_map (at most one "
4592  "dim or the zero constant can appear in each result)");
4593  }
4594  if (seen[dim.getPosition()]) {
4595  return emitOpError(
4596  "requires a permutation_map that is a permutation (found one dim "
4597  "used more than once)");
4598  }
4599  seen[dim.getPosition()] = true;
4600  }
4601  return success();
4602 }
4603 
4604 static LogicalResult
4605 verifyTransferOp(VectorTransferOpInterface op, ShapedType shapedType,
4606  VectorType vectorType, VectorType maskType,
4607  VectorType inferredMaskType, AffineMap permutationMap,
4608  ArrayAttr inBounds) {
4609  if (op->hasAttr("masked")) {
4610  return op->emitOpError("masked attribute has been removed. "
4611  "Use in_bounds instead.");
4612  }
4613 
4614  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(shapedType))
4615  return op->emitOpError(
4616  "requires source to be a memref or ranked tensor type");
4617 
4618  auto elementType = shapedType.getElementType();
4619  DataLayout dataLayout = DataLayout::closest(op);
4620  if (auto vectorElementType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(elementType)) {
4621  // Memref or tensor has vector element type.
4622  unsigned sourceVecSize =
4623  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(vectorElementType.getElementType()) *
4624  vectorElementType.getShape().back();
4625  unsigned resultVecSize =
4626  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(vectorType.getElementType()) *
4627  vectorType.getShape().back();
4628  if (resultVecSize % sourceVecSize != 0)
4629  return op->emitOpError(
4630  "requires the bitwidth of the minor 1-D vector to be an integral "
4631  "multiple of the bitwidth of the minor 1-D vector of the source");
4632 
4633  unsigned sourceVecEltRank = vectorElementType.getRank();
4634  unsigned resultVecRank = vectorType.getRank();
4635  if (sourceVecEltRank > resultVecRank)
4636  return op->emitOpError(
4637  "requires source vector element and vector result ranks to match.");
4638  unsigned rankOffset = resultVecRank - sourceVecEltRank;
4639  // Check that permutation map results match 'rankOffset' of vector type.
4640  if (permutationMap.getNumResults() != rankOffset)
4641  return op->emitOpError("requires a permutation_map with result dims of "
4642  "the same rank as the vector type");
4643 
4644  if (maskType)
4645  return op->emitOpError("does not support masks with vector element type");
4646  } else {
4647  // Memref or tensor has scalar element type.
4648  unsigned minorSize =
4649  vectorType.getRank() == 0 ? 1 : vectorType.getShape().back();
4650  unsigned resultVecSize =
4651  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(vectorType.getElementType()) * minorSize;
4652  if (resultVecSize % dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(elementType) != 0)
4653  return op->emitOpError(
4654  "requires the bitwidth of the minor 1-D vector to be an integral "
4655  "multiple of the bitwidth of the source element type");
4656 
4657  // Check that permutation map results match rank of vector type.
4658  if (permutationMap.getNumResults() != vectorType.getRank())
4659  return op->emitOpError("requires a permutation_map with result dims of "
4660  "the same rank as the vector type");
4661  }
4662 
4663  if (permutationMap.getNumSymbols() != 0)
4664  return op->emitOpError("requires permutation_map without symbols");
4665 
4666  if (permutationMap.getNumInputs() != shapedType.getRank())
4667  return op->emitOpError("requires a permutation_map with input dims of the "
4668  "same rank as the source type");
4669 
4670  if (maskType && maskType != inferredMaskType)
4671  return op->emitOpError("inferred mask type (")
4672  << inferredMaskType << ") and mask operand type (" << maskType
4673  << ") don't match";
4674 
4675  if (permutationMap.getNumResults() != static_cast<int64_t>(inBounds.size()))
4676  return op->emitOpError("expects the in_bounds attr of same rank "
4677  "as permutation_map results: ")
4678  << AffineMapAttr::get(permutationMap)
4679  << " vs inBounds of size: " << inBounds.size();
4680 
4681  return success();
4682 }
4683 
4684 static void printTransferAttrs(OpAsmPrinter &p, VectorTransferOpInterface op) {
4685  SmallVector<StringRef, 3> elidedAttrs;
4686  elidedAttrs.push_back(TransferReadOp::getOperandSegmentSizeAttr());
4687  if (op.getPermutationMap().isMinorIdentity())
4688  elidedAttrs.push_back(op.getPermutationMapAttrName());
4689  // Elide in_bounds attribute if all dims are out-of-bounds.
4690  if (llvm::none_of(op.getInBoundsValues(), [](bool b) { return b; }))
4691  elidedAttrs.push_back(op.getInBoundsAttrName());
4692  p.printOptionalAttrDict(op->getAttrs(), elidedAttrs);
4693 }

4695 void TransferReadOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
4696  p << " " << getBase() << "[" << getIndices() << "], " << getPadding();
4697  if (getMask())
4698  p << ", " << getMask();
4699  printTransferAttrs(p, *this);
4700  p << " : " << getShapedType() << ", " << getVectorType();
4701 }
4702 
4703 VectorType mlir::vector::inferTransferOpMaskType(VectorType vecType,
4704  AffineMap permMap) {
4705  auto i1Type = IntegerType::get(permMap.getContext(), 1);
4706  AffineMap invPermMap = inversePermutation(compressUnusedDims(permMap));
4707  assert(invPermMap && "Inversed permutation map couldn't be computed");
4708  SmallVector<int64_t, 8> maskShape = invPermMap.compose(vecType.getShape());
4709 
4710  // The MaskOp specification doesn't support 0-D vectors at the moment. Turn a
4711  // 0-D mask into a single-element 1-D mask.
4712  if (maskShape.empty())
4713  maskShape.push_back(1);
4714 
4715  SmallVector<bool> scalableDims =
4716  applyPermutationMap(invPermMap, vecType.getScalableDims());
4717 
4718  return VectorType::get(maskShape, i1Type, scalableDims);
4719 }
4720 
4721 ParseResult TransferReadOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
4722  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
4723  SMLoc typesLoc;
4724  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand sourceInfo;
4725  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 8> indexInfo;
4726  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand paddingInfo;
4727  SmallVector<Type, 2> types;
4728  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand maskInfo;
4729  // Parsing with support for paddingValue.
4730  if (parser.parseOperand(sourceInfo) ||
4731  parser.parseOperandList(indexInfo, OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Square) ||
4732  parser.parseComma() || parser.parseOperand(paddingInfo))
4733  return failure();
4734  ParseResult hasMask = parser.parseOptionalComma();
4735  if (hasMask.succeeded()) {
4736  if (parser.parseOperand(maskInfo))
4737  return failure();
4738  }
4739  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
4740  parser.getCurrentLocation(&typesLoc) || parser.parseColonTypeList(types))
4741  return failure();
4742  if (types.size() != 2)
4743  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires two types");
4744  auto indexType = builder.getIndexType();
4745  auto shapedType = llvm::dyn_cast<ShapedType>(types[0]);
4746  if (!shapedType || !llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(shapedType))
4747  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires memref or ranked tensor type");
4748  VectorType vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(types[1]);
4749  if (!vectorType)
4750  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires vector type");
4751  auto permMapAttrName = TransferReadOp::getPermutationMapAttrName(result.name);
4752  Attribute permMapAttr = result.attributes.get(permMapAttrName);
4753  AffineMap permMap;
4754  if (!permMapAttr) {
4755  if (shapedType.getRank() <
4756  getEffectiveVectorRankForXferOp(shapedType, vectorType))
4757  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
4758  "expected a custom permutation_map when "
4759  "rank(source) != rank(destination)");
4760  permMap = getTransferMinorIdentityMap(shapedType, vectorType);
4761  result.attributes.set(permMapAttrName, AffineMapAttr::get(permMap));
4762  } else {
4763  permMap = llvm::cast<AffineMapAttr>(permMapAttr).getValue();
4764  }
4765  auto inBoundsAttrName = TransferReadOp::getInBoundsAttrName(result.name);
4766  Attribute inBoundsAttr = result.attributes.get(inBoundsAttrName);
4767  if (!inBoundsAttr) {
4768  result.addAttribute(inBoundsAttrName,
4769  builder.getBoolArrayAttr(
4770  SmallVector<bool>(permMap.getNumResults(), false)));
4771  }
4772  if (parser.resolveOperand(sourceInfo, shapedType, result.operands) ||
4773  parser.resolveOperands(indexInfo, indexType, result.operands) ||
4774  parser.resolveOperand(paddingInfo, shapedType.getElementType(),
4775  result.operands))
4776  return failure();
4777  if (hasMask.succeeded()) {
4778  if (llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(shapedType.getElementType()))
4779  return parser.emitError(
4780  maskInfo.location, "does not support masks with vector element type");
4781  if (vectorType.getRank() != permMap.getNumResults()) {
4782  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
4783  "expected the same rank for the vector and the "
4784  "results of the permutation map");
4785  }
4786  // Instead of adding the mask type as an op type, compute it based on the
4787  // vector type and the permutation map (to keep the type signature small).
4788  auto maskType = inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permMap);
4789  if (parser.resolveOperand(maskInfo, maskType, result.operands))
4790  return failure();
4791  }
4792  result.addAttribute(TransferReadOp::getOperandSegmentSizeAttr(),
4793  builder.getDenseI32ArrayAttr(
4794  {1, static_cast<int32_t>(indexInfo.size()), 1,
4795  static_cast<int32_t>(hasMask.succeeded())}));
4796  return parser.addTypeToList(vectorType, result.types);
4797 }
4798 
4799 LogicalResult TransferReadOp::verify() {
4800  // Consistency of elemental types in source and vector.
4801  ShapedType shapedType = getShapedType();
4802  VectorType vectorType = getVectorType();
4803  VectorType maskType = getMaskType();
4804  auto paddingType = getPadding().getType();
4805  auto permutationMap = getPermutationMap();
4806  VectorType inferredMaskType =
4807  maskType ? inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permutationMap)
4808  : VectorType();
4809  auto sourceElementType = shapedType.getElementType();
4810 
4811  if (static_cast<int64_t>(getIndices().size()) != shapedType.getRank())
4812  return emitOpError("requires ") << shapedType.getRank() << " indices";
4813 
4814  if (failed(verifyTransferOp(cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(getOperation()),
4815  shapedType, vectorType, maskType,
4816  inferredMaskType, permutationMap, getInBounds())))
4817  return failure();
4818 
4819  if (auto sourceVectorElementType =
4820  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(sourceElementType)) {
4821  // Source has vector element type.
4822  // Check that 'sourceVectorElementType' and 'paddingType' types match.
4823  if (sourceVectorElementType != paddingType)
4824  return emitOpError(
4825  "requires source element type and padding type to match.");
4826 
4827  } else {
4828  // Check that 'paddingType' is valid to store in a vector type.
4829  if (!VectorType::isValidElementType(paddingType))
4830  return emitOpError("requires valid padding vector elemental type");
4831 
4832  // Check that padding type and vector element types match.
4833  if (paddingType != sourceElementType)
4834  return emitOpError(
4835  "requires formal padding and source of the same elemental type");
4836  }
4837 
4838  return verifyPermutationMap(permutationMap,
4839  [&](Twine t) { return emitOpError(t); });
4840 }

4842 // MaskableOpInterface methods.
4843 
4844 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
4845 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
4846 Type TransferReadOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
4847  return inferTransferOpMaskType(getVectorType(), getPermutationMap());
4848 }

4851 // TransferReadOp: VectorTransferOpInterface methods.

4853 VectorType TransferReadOp::getVectorType() {
4854  return cast<VectorType>(getVector().getType());
4855 }

4857 template <typename TransferOp>
4858 static bool isInBounds(TransferOp op, int64_t resultIdx, int64_t indicesIdx) {
4859  // TODO: support more aggressive createOrFold on:
4860  // op.getIndices()[indicesIdx] + vectorType < dim(op.getSource(), indicesIdx)
4861  if (op.getShapedType().isDynamicDim(indicesIdx))
4862  return false;
4863  Value index = op.getIndices()[indicesIdx];
4864  std::optional<int64_t> cstOp = getConstantIntValue(index);
4865  if (!cstOp.has_value())
4866  return false;
4867 
4868  int64_t sourceSize = op.getShapedType().getDimSize(indicesIdx);
4869  int64_t vectorSize = op.getVectorType().getDimSize(resultIdx);
4870 
4871  return cstOp.value() + vectorSize <= sourceSize;
4872 }
4873 
4874 template <typename TransferOp>
4875 static LogicalResult foldTransferInBoundsAttribute(TransferOp op) {
4876  // TODO: support 0-d corner case.
4877  // TODO: Be less conservative.
4878  if (op.getTransferRank() == 0)
4879  return failure();
4880  AffineMap permutationMap = op.getPermutationMap();
4881  bool changed = false;
4882  SmallVector<bool, 4> newInBounds;
4883  newInBounds.reserve(op.getTransferRank());
4884  // Idxs of non-bcast dims - used when analysing bcast dims.
4885  SmallVector<unsigned> nonBcastDims;
4886 
4887  // 1. Process non-broadcast dims
4888  for (unsigned i = 0; i < op.getTransferRank(); ++i) {
4889  // 1.1. Already marked as in-bounds, nothing to see here.
4890  if (op.isDimInBounds(i)) {
4891  newInBounds.push_back(true);
4892  continue;
4893  }
4894  // 1.2. Currently out-of-bounds, check whether we can statically determine
4895  // it is inBounds.
4896  bool inBounds = false;
4897  auto dimExpr = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(permutationMap.getResult(i));
4898  if (dimExpr) {
4899  inBounds = isInBounds(op, /*resultIdx=*/i,
4900  /*indicesIdx=*/dimExpr.getPosition());
4901  nonBcastDims.push_back(i);
4902  }
4903 
4904  newInBounds.push_back(inBounds);
4905  // We commit the pattern if it is "more inbounds".
4906  changed |= inBounds;
4907  }
4908 
4909  // 2. Handle broadcast dims
4910  // If all non-broadcast dims are "in bounds", then all bcast dims should be
4911  // "in bounds" as well.
4912  bool allNonBcastDimsInBounds = llvm::all_of(
4913  nonBcastDims, [&newInBounds](unsigned idx) { return newInBounds[idx]; });
4914  if (allNonBcastDimsInBounds) {
4915  for (size_t idx : permutationMap.getBroadcastDims()) {
4916  changed |= !newInBounds[idx];
4917  newInBounds[idx] = true;
4918  }
4919  }
4920 
4921  if (!changed)
4922  return failure();
4923  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
4924  OpBuilder b(op.getContext());
4925  op.setInBoundsAttr(b.getBoolArrayAttr(newInBounds));
4926  return success();
4927 }
4928 
4929 template <typename TransferOp>
4930 static LogicalResult foldTransferFullMask(TransferOp op) {
4931  auto mask = op.getMask();
4932  if (!mask)
4933  return failure();
4934 
4935  if (getMaskFormat(mask) != MaskFormat::AllTrue)
4936  return failure();
4937 
4938  op.getMaskMutable().clear();
4939  return success();
4940 }
4941 
4942 /// ```
4943 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
4944 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
4945 /// %0 = vector.transfer_read %w0[%c1, %c0], %cf0 {in_bounds = [true, true]}
4946 /// : tensor<4x4xf32>, vector<1x4xf32>
4947 /// ```
4948 /// -> Folds into
4949 /// ```
4950 /// %v0
4951 /// ```
4952 static Value foldRAW(TransferReadOp readOp) {
4953  if (!llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(readOp.getShapedType()))
4954  return {};
4955  auto defWrite = readOp.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
4956  while (defWrite) {
4957  if (checkSameValueRAW(defWrite, readOp))
4958  return defWrite.getVector();
4959  if (!isDisjointTransferIndices(
4960  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(defWrite.getOperation()),
4961  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(readOp.getOperation())))
4962  break;
4963  defWrite = defWrite.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
4964  }
4965  return {};
4966 }
4967 
4968 OpFoldResult TransferReadOp::fold(FoldAdaptor) {
4969  if (Value vec = foldRAW(*this))
4970  return vec;
4971  /// transfer_read(memrefcast) -> transfer_read
4972  if (succeeded(foldTransferInBoundsAttribute(*this)))
4973  return getResult();
4974  if (succeeded(foldTransferFullMask(*this)))
4975  return getResult();
4976  if (succeeded(memref::foldMemRefCast(*this)))
4977  return getResult();
4978  if (succeeded(tensor::foldTensorCast(*this)))
4979  return getResult();
4980  return OpFoldResult();
4981 }

5001 namespace {
5002 /// Store to load forwarding for transfer operations with permuation maps.
5003 /// Even if the permutation maps are different we can still propagate the store
5004 /// into the load if the size of the dimensions read and written match. Then we
5005 /// can replace the transfer_read + transfer_write by vector.broadcast and
5006 /// vector.transpose.
5007 /// Example:
5008 /// ```
5009 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c0, %c0, %c0]
5010 /// {in_bounds = [true, true],
5011 /// permutation_map = affine_map<(d0, d1, d2) -> (d2, d1)>} :
5012 /// vector<4x1xf32>, tensor<4x4x4xf32>
5013 /// %r = vector.transfer_read %w0[%c0, %c0, %c0], %cf0
5014 /// {in_bounds = [true, true, true, true],
5015 /// permutation_map = affine_map<(d0, d1, d2) -> (d1, 0, d2, 0)>} :
5016 /// tensor<4x4x4xf32>, vector<1x100x4x5xf32>
5017 /// ```
5018 /// To:
5019 /// ```
5020 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %arg1 : vector<4x1xf32> to vector<100x5x4x1xf32>
5021 /// %r = vector.transpose %0, [3, 0, 2, 1] :
5022 /// vector<100x5x4x1xf32> to vector<1x100x4x5xf32>
5023 /// ```
5024 struct TransferReadAfterWriteToBroadcast
5025  : public OpRewritePattern<TransferReadOp> {
5026  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5027 
5028  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransferReadOp readOp,
5029  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5030  auto defWrite = readOp.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
5031  if (!defWrite)
5032  return failure();
5033  // Bail if we need an alias analysis.
5034  if (!readOp.hasPureTensorSemantics() || !defWrite.hasPureTensorSemantics())
5035  return failure();
5036  // Bail if we need a bounds analysis.
5037  if (readOp.hasOutOfBoundsDim() || defWrite.hasOutOfBoundsDim())
5038  return failure();
5039  // TODO: If the written transfer chunk is a superset of the read transfer
5040  // chunk we could do an extract_strided_slice.
5041  if (readOp.getTransferChunkAccessed() !=
5042  defWrite.getTransferChunkAccessed())
5043  return failure();
5044  // TODO: Support cases where a dim is explicitly written but implicitly
5045  // read (i.e., a unit dim that is rank reduced).
5046  if (getUnusedDimsBitVector({readOp.getPermutationMap()}) !=
5047  getUnusedDimsBitVector({defWrite.getPermutationMap()}))
5048  return failure();
5049  // This pattern should only catch the broadcast case, the non-broadcast case
5050  // should be done separately to keep application conditions clean and
5051  // separate.
5052  AffineMap readMap = compressUnusedDims(readOp.getPermutationMap());
5053  AffineMap writeMap = compressUnusedDims(defWrite.getPermutationMap());
5054  bool bcast = !readMap.getBroadcastDims().empty() ||
5055  !writeMap.getBroadcastDims().empty();
5056  if (!bcast)
5057  return failure();
5058  // At this point, we know we have a bcast.
5059  // Bail in the masked case (too complex atm and needed to properly account
5060  // for padding).
5061  if (readOp.getMask() || defWrite.getMask())
5062  return failure();
5063  // If indices are not the same a shift may be required, bail.
5064  if (readOp.getIndices() != defWrite.getIndices())
5065  return failure();
5066 
5067  Value vec = defWrite.getVector();
5068  // TODO: loop through the chain of transfer_write if we can prove that they
5069  // don't overlap with the transfer_read. This requires improving
5070  // `isDisjointTransferIndices` helper.
5071  AffineMap map = readMap.compose(writeMap);
5072  if (map.getNumResults() == 0)
5073  return failure();
5074  // Calculate the permutation to apply to go from the vector stored to the
5075  // vector read.
5076  SmallVector<unsigned> permutation;
5077  if (!map.isPermutationOfMinorIdentityWithBroadcasting(permutation))
5078  return failure();
5079 
5080  Location loc = readOp.getLoc();
5081  // Calculate the broadcast shape by applying the reverse permutation to the
5082  // final shape we want.
5083  ArrayRef<int64_t> destShape = readOp.getVectorType().getShape();
5084  SmallVector<int64_t> broadcastShape(destShape.size());
5085  SmallVector<bool> broadcastScalableFlags(destShape.size());
5086  for (const auto &pos : llvm::enumerate(permutation)) {
5087  broadcastShape[pos.value()] = destShape[pos.index()];
5088  broadcastScalableFlags[pos.value()] =
5089  readOp.getVectorType().getScalableDims()[pos.index()];
5090  }
5091  VectorType broadcastedType = VectorType::get(
5092  broadcastShape, defWrite.getVectorType().getElementType(),
5093  broadcastScalableFlags);
5094  vec = vector::BroadcastOp::create(rewriter, loc, broadcastedType, vec);
5095  SmallVector<int64_t> transposePerm(permutation.begin(), permutation.end());
5096  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::TransposeOp>(readOp, vec,
5097  transposePerm);
5098  return success();
5099  }
5100 };
5101 } // namespace
5102 
5103 void TransferReadOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
5104  MLIRContext *context) {
5105  results.add<TransferReadAfterWriteToBroadcast>(context);
5106 }

5109 TransferReadOp::bubbleDownCasts(OpBuilder &builder) {
5110  if (!hasPureBufferSemantics())
5111  return failure();
5112  return mlir::detail::bubbleDownInPlaceMemorySpaceCastImpl(getBaseMutable(),
5113  getResult());
5114 }

5166 
5167 ParseResult TransferWriteOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser,
5168  OperationState &result) {
5169  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
5170  SMLoc typesLoc;
5171  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand vectorInfo, sourceInfo;
5172  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 8> indexInfo;
5173  SmallVector<Type, 2> types;
5174  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand maskInfo;
5175  if (parser.parseOperand(vectorInfo) || parser.parseComma() ||
5176  parser.parseOperand(sourceInfo) ||
5177  parser.parseOperandList(indexInfo, OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Square))
5178  return failure();
5179  ParseResult hasMask = parser.parseOptionalComma();
5180  if (hasMask.succeeded() && parser.parseOperand(maskInfo))
5181  return failure();
5182  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
5183  parser.getCurrentLocation(&typesLoc) || parser.parseColonTypeList(types))
5184  return failure();
5185  if (types.size() != 2)
5186  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires two types");
5187  auto indexType = builder.getIndexType();
5188  VectorType vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(types[0]);
5189  if (!vectorType)
5190  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires vector type");
5191  ShapedType shapedType = llvm::dyn_cast<ShapedType>(types[1]);
5192  if (!shapedType || !llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(shapedType))
5193  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires memref or ranked tensor type");
5194  auto permMapAttrName =
5195  TransferWriteOp::getPermutationMapAttrName(result.name);
5196  auto permMapAttr = result.attributes.get(permMapAttrName);
5197  AffineMap permMap;
5198  if (!permMapAttr) {
5199  if (shapedType.getRank() <
5200  getEffectiveVectorRankForXferOp(shapedType, vectorType))
5201  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
5202  "expected a custom permutation_map when "
5203  "rank(source) != rank(destination)");
5204  permMap = getTransferMinorIdentityMap(shapedType, vectorType);
5205  result.attributes.set(permMapAttrName, AffineMapAttr::get(permMap));
5206  } else {
5207  permMap = llvm::cast<AffineMapAttr>(permMapAttr).getValue();
5208  }
5209  auto inBoundsAttrName = TransferWriteOp::getInBoundsAttrName(result.name);
5210  Attribute inBoundsAttr = result.attributes.get(inBoundsAttrName);
5211  if (!inBoundsAttr) {
5212  result.addAttribute(inBoundsAttrName,
5213  builder.getBoolArrayAttr(
5214  SmallVector<bool>(permMap.getNumResults(), false)));
5215  }
5216  if (parser.resolveOperand(vectorInfo, vectorType, result.operands) ||
5217  parser.resolveOperand(sourceInfo, shapedType, result.operands) ||
5218  parser.resolveOperands(indexInfo, indexType, result.operands))
5219  return failure();
5220  if (hasMask.succeeded()) {
5221  if (llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(shapedType.getElementType()))
5222  return parser.emitError(
5223  maskInfo.location, "does not support masks with vector element type");
5224  if (vectorType.getRank() != permMap.getNumResults()) {
5225  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
5226  "expected the same rank for the vector and the "
5227  "results of the permutation map");
5228  }
5229  auto maskType = inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permMap);
5230  if (parser.resolveOperand(maskInfo, maskType, result.operands))
5231  return failure();
5232  }
5233  result.addAttribute(TransferWriteOp::getOperandSegmentSizeAttr(),
5234  builder.getDenseI32ArrayAttr(
5235  {1, 1, static_cast<int32_t>(indexInfo.size()),
5236  static_cast<int32_t>(hasMask.succeeded())}));
5237  return failure(llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(shapedType) &&
5238  parser.addTypeToList(shapedType, result.types));
5239 }
5240 
5241 void TransferWriteOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
5242  p << " " << getVector() << ", " << getBase() << "[" << getIndices() << "]";
5243  if (getMask())
5244  p << ", " << getMask();
5245  printTransferAttrs(p, *this);
5246  p << " : " << getVectorType() << ", " << getShapedType();
5247 }
5248 
5249 LogicalResult TransferWriteOp::verify() {
5250  // Consistency of elemental types in shape and vector.
5251  ShapedType shapedType = getShapedType();
5252  VectorType vectorType = getVectorType();
5253  VectorType maskType = getMaskType();
5254  auto permutationMap = getPermutationMap();
5255  VectorType inferredMaskType =
5256  maskType ? inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permutationMap)
5257  : VectorType();
5258 
5259  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != shapedType.getRank())
5260  return emitOpError("requires ") << shapedType.getRank() << " indices";
5261 
5262  // We do not allow broadcast dimensions on TransferWriteOps for the moment,
5263  // as the semantics is unclear. This can be revisited later if necessary.
5264  if (hasBroadcastDim())
5265  return emitOpError("should not have broadcast dimensions");
5266 
5267  if (failed(verifyTransferOp(cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(getOperation()),
5268  shapedType, vectorType, maskType,
5269  inferredMaskType, permutationMap, getInBounds())))
5270  return failure();
5271 
5272  return verifyPermutationMap(permutationMap,
5273  [&](Twine t) { return emitOpError(t); });
5274 }

5283  return inferTransferOpMaskType(getVectorType(), getPermutationMap());
5284 }
