5294 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5295 // TransferWriteOp: fold methods.
5296 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5297 /// Fold:
5298 /// ```
5299 /// %t1 = ...
5300 /// %v = vector.transfer_read %t0[%c0...], {in_bounds = [true...]} :
5301 /// tensor<static_sizesxf32>, vector<static_sizesxf32>
5302 /// %t2 = vector.transfer_write %v, %t1[%c0...] {in_bounds = [true...]} :
5303 /// vector<static_sizesxf32>, tensor<static_sizesxf32>
5304 /// ```
5305 ///
5306 /// into:
5307 ///
5308 /// ```
5309 /// %t0
5310 /// ```
5311 ///
5312 /// The producer of t1 may or may not be DCE'd depending on whether it is a
5313 /// block argument or has side effects.
5314 static LogicalResult foldReadInitWrite(TransferWriteOp write,
5315  ArrayRef<Attribute>,
5316  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
5317  // TODO: support 0-d corner case.
5318  if (write.getTransferRank() == 0)
5319  return failure();
5320  auto rankedTensorType =
5321  llvm::dyn_cast<RankedTensorType>(write.getBase().getType());
5322  // If not operating on tensors, bail.
5323  if (!rankedTensorType)
5324  return failure();
5325  // If no read, bail.
5326  auto read = write.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferReadOp>();
5327  if (!read)
5328  return failure();
5329  // TODO: support 0-d corner case.
5330  if (read.getTransferRank() == 0)
5331  return failure();
5332  // For now, only accept minor identity. Future: composition is minor identity.
5333  if (!read.getPermutationMap().isMinorIdentity() ||
5334  !write.getPermutationMap().isMinorIdentity())
5335  return failure();
5336  // Bail on mismatching ranks.
5337  if (read.getTransferRank() != write.getTransferRank())
5338  return failure();
5339  // Bail on potential out-of-bounds accesses.
5340  if (read.hasOutOfBoundsDim() || write.hasOutOfBoundsDim())
5341  return failure();
5342  // Tensor types must be the same.
5343  if (read.getBase().getType() != rankedTensorType)
5344  return failure();
5345  // Vector types must be the same.
5346  if (read.getVectorType() != write.getVectorType())
5347  return failure();
5348  // Vector and Tensor shapes must match.
5349  if (read.getVectorType().getShape() != rankedTensorType.getShape())
5350  return failure();
5351  // If any index is nonzero.
5352  auto isNotConstantZero = [](Value v) {
5353  auto cstOp = getConstantIntValue(v);
5354  return !cstOp.has_value() || cstOp.value() != 0;
5355  };
5356  if (llvm::any_of(read.getIndices(), isNotConstantZero) ||
5357  llvm::any_of(write.getIndices(), isNotConstantZero))
5358  return failure();
5359  // Success.
5360  results.push_back(read.getBase());
5361  return success();
5362 }
5363 
5364 static bool checkSameValueWAR(vector::TransferReadOp read,
5365  vector::TransferWriteOp write) {
5366  return read.getBase() == write.getBase() &&
5367  read.getIndices() == write.getIndices() &&
5368  read.getPermutationMap() == write.getPermutationMap() &&
5369  read.getVectorType() == write.getVectorType() && !read.getMask() &&
5370  !write.getMask();
5371 }
5372 /// Fold transfer_write write after read:
5373 /// ```
5374 /// %t0 = ...
5375 /// %v = vector.transfer_read %t0[%c0...] :
5376 /// tensor<static_sizesxf32>, vector<static_sizesxf32>
5377 /// %t1 = vector.transfer_write %v, %t0[%c0...] :
5378 /// vector<static_sizesxf32>, tensor<static_sizesxf32>
5379 /// ```
5380 ///
5381 /// into:
5382 ///
5383 /// ```
5384 /// %t0
5385 /// ```
5386 static LogicalResult foldWAR(TransferWriteOp write,
5387  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
5388  if (!llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(write.getBase().getType()))
5389  return failure();
5390  auto read = write.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferReadOp>();
5391  if (!read)
5392  return failure();
5393 
5394  if (!checkSameValueWAR(read, write))
5395  return failure();
5396  results.push_back(read.getBase());
5397  return success();
5398 }
5399 
5400 LogicalResult TransferWriteOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor,
5401  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
5402  if (succeeded(foldReadInitWrite(*this, adaptor.getOperands(), results)))
5403  return success();
5404  if (succeeded(foldWAR(*this, results)))
5405  return success();
5406  if (succeeded(foldTransferInBoundsAttribute(*this)))
5407  return success();
5408  if (succeeded(foldTransferFullMask(*this)))
5409  return success();
5410  return memref::foldMemRefCast(*this);
5411 }

5434 namespace {
5435 /// Remove dead transfer write from the SSA chain so that it an be eliminated by
5436 /// DCE
5437 /// ```
5438 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5439 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5440 /// %w1 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %w0[%c2, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5441 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5442 /// %w2 = vector.transfer_write %v1, %w1[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5443 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5444 /// ```
5445 ///
5446 /// into:
5447 ///
5448 /// ```
5449 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5450 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5451 /// %w1 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c2, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5452 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5453 /// %w2 = vector.transfer_write %v1, %w1[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5454 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5455 /// ```
5456 ///
5457 /// `%w0 = vector.transfer_write` op will be removed by DCE if it doesn't have
5458 /// any other uses.
5459 class FoldWaw final : public OpRewritePattern<TransferWriteOp> {
5460 public:
5461  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5462  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransferWriteOp writeOp,
5463  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5464  if (!llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(writeOp.getShapedType()))
5465  return failure();
5466  vector::TransferWriteOp writeToModify = writeOp;
5467 
5468  auto defWrite = writeOp.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
5469  while (defWrite) {
5470  if (checkSameValueWAW(writeOp, defWrite)) {
5471  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(writeToModify, [&]() {
5472  writeToModify.getBaseMutable().assign(defWrite.getBase());
5473  });
5474  return success();
5475  }
5476  if (!isDisjointTransferIndices(
5477  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(defWrite.getOperation()),
5478  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(writeOp.getOperation())))
5479  break;
5480  // If the previous write op doesn't have any other use we an safely look
5481  // at the previous store to see if it can be removed.
5482  if (!defWrite->hasOneUse())
5483  break;
5484  writeToModify = defWrite;
5485  defWrite = defWrite.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
5486  }
5487  return failure();
5488  }
5489 };
5490 
5491 /// Rewrite tensor::ExtractSliceOp(vector::TransferWriteOp) to
5492 /// vector::TransferWriteOp(tensor::ExtractSliceOp) if the full slice is
5493 /// overwritten and inserted into another tensor. After this rewrite, the
5494 /// operations bufferize in-place since all of them work on the same slice.
5495 ///
5496 /// For example:
5497 /// ```mlir
5498 /// %0 = vector.transfer_write %vec, %init_tensor[%c0, %c0]
5499 /// : vector<8x16xf32>, tensor<8x16xf32>
5500 /// %1 = tensor.extract_slice %0[0, 0] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5501 /// : tensor<8x16xf32> to tensor<?x?xf32>
5502 /// %r = tensor.insert_slice %1 into %iter_arg[%iv0, %iv1] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5503 /// : tensor<?x?xf32> into tensor<27x37xf32>
5504 /// ```
5505 /// folds to
5506 /// ```mlir
5507 /// %0 = tensor.extract_slice %iter_arg[%iv0, %iv1] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5508 /// : tensor<27x37xf32> to tensor<?x?xf32>
5509 /// %1 = vector.transfer_write %vec, %0[%c0, %c0]
5510 /// : vector<8x16xf32>, tensor<?x?xf32>
5511 /// %r = tensor.insert_slice %1 into %iter_arg[%iv0, %iv1] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5512 /// : tensor<?x?xf32> into tensor<27x37xf32>
5513 /// ```
5514 struct SwapExtractSliceOfTransferWrite
5515  : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::InsertSliceOp> {
5516 public:
5517  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5518 
5519  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::InsertSliceOp insertOp,
5520  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5521  if (!insertOp.hasUnitStride())
5522  return failure();
5523  auto extractOp =
5524  insertOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<tensor::ExtractSliceOp>();
5525  if (!extractOp || !extractOp.hasUnitStride() || !extractOp->hasOneUse())
5526  return failure();
5527  auto transferOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<TransferWriteOp>();
5528  if (!transferOp || !transferOp->hasOneUse())
5529  return failure();
5530 
5531  // Fail if vector::TransferWriteOp or tensor::ExtractSliceOp is
5532  // rank-reducing.
5533  if (insertOp.getSourceType().getRank() != transferOp.getTransferRank()) {
5534  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(insertOp,
5535  "use-def chain is rank-reducing");
5536  }
5537 
5538  // Fail if tensor::ExtractSliceOp has non-zero offset.
5539  if (!extractOp.hasZeroOffset()) {
5540  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(insertOp,
5541  "ExtractSliceOp has non-zero offset");
5542  }
5543 
5544  // Fail if tensor::TransferWriteOp has non-zero offset.
5545  if (!llvm::all_of(transferOp.getIndices(), [](Value value) {
5546  return getConstantIntValue(value) == static_cast<int64_t>(0);
5547  })) {
5548  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(insertOp,
5549  "TranferWriteOp has non-zero offset");
5550  }
5551 
5552  // Fail if tensor::ExtractSliceOp and tensor::InsertSliceOp sizes differ.
5553  if (insertOp.getMixedSizes().size() != extractOp.getMixedSizes().size()) {
5554  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
5555  insertOp, "InsertSliceOp and ExtractSliceOp ranks differ");
5556  }
5557 
5558  for (auto [insertSize, extractSize] :
5559  llvm::zip_equal(insertOp.getMixedSizes(), extractOp.getMixedSizes())) {
5560  if (!isEqualConstantIntOrValue(insertSize, extractSize)) {
5561  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
5562  insertOp, "InsertSliceOp and ExtractSliceOp sizes differ");
5563  }
5564  }
5565 
5566  // Fail if the vector::TransferWriteOp may not overwrite the full tensor.
5567  assert(transferOp.getVectorType().hasStaticShape() &&
5568  "expected vector to have a static shape");
5569  ArrayRef<int64_t> vectorShape = transferOp.getVectorType().getShape();
5570  SmallVector<int64_t> resultShape = applyPermutationMap(
5571  transferOp.getPermutationMap(), transferOp.getShapedType().getShape());
5572  if (transferOp.getMask() || !vectorShape.equals(resultShape)) {
5573  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
5574  insertOp, "TransferWriteOp may not write the full tensor.");
5575  }
5576 
5577  // Swap the tensor::ExtractSliceOp in front of the vector::TransferWriteOp.
5578  // Set all in_bounds to false and let the folder infer them.
5579  SmallVector<bool> newInBounds(vectorShape.size(), false);
5580  auto newExtractOp = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
5581  rewriter, extractOp.getLoc(), insertOp.getSourceType(),
5582  insertOp.getDest(), insertOp.getMixedOffsets(),
5583  insertOp.getMixedSizes(), insertOp.getMixedStrides());
5584  auto newTransferWriteOp = TransferWriteOp::create(
5585  rewriter, transferOp.getLoc(), transferOp.getVector(),
5586  newExtractOp.getResult(), transferOp.getIndices(),
5587  transferOp.getPermutationMapAttr(),
5588  rewriter.getBoolArrayAttr(newInBounds));
5589  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(insertOp, [&]() {
5590  insertOp.getSourceMutable().assign(newTransferWriteOp.getResult());
5591  });
5592  return success();
5593  }
5594 };
5595 
5596 } // namespace
5597 
5598 void TransferWriteOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
5599  MLIRContext *context) {
5600  results.add<FoldWaw, SwapExtractSliceOfTransferWrite>(context);
5601 }

5603 FailureOr<std::optional<SmallVector<Value>>>
5604 TransferWriteOp::bubbleDownCasts(OpBuilder &builder) {
5605  if (!hasPureBufferSemantics())
5606  return failure();
5607  return mlir::detail::bubbleDownInPlaceMemorySpaceCastImpl(getBaseMutable(),
5608  ValueRange());
5609 }

5613 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5614 
5615 static LogicalResult verifyLoadStoreMemRefLayout(Operation *op,
5616  VectorType vecTy,
5617  MemRefType memRefTy) {
5618  // If rank==0 or size==1 it's equivalent to scalar load/store, so we don't
5619  // need any strides limitations.
5620  if (!vecTy.isScalable() &&
5621  (vecTy.getRank() == 0 || vecTy.getNumElements() == 1))
5622  return success();
5623 
5624  if (!memRefTy.isLastDimUnitStride())
5625  return op->emitOpError("most minor memref dim must have unit stride");
5626  return success();
5627 }
5628 
5629 LogicalResult vector::LoadOp::verify() {
5630  VectorType resVecTy = getVectorType();
5631  MemRefType memRefTy = getMemRefType();
5632 
5633  if (failed(verifyLoadStoreMemRefLayout(*this, resVecTy, memRefTy)))
5634  return failure();
5635 
5636  if (memRefTy.getRank() < resVecTy.getRank())
5637  return emitOpError(
5638  "destination memref has lower rank than the result vector");
5639 
5640  // Checks for vector memrefs.
5641  Type memElemTy = memRefTy.getElementType();
5642  if (auto memVecTy = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(memElemTy)) {
5643  if (memVecTy != resVecTy)
5644  return emitOpError("base memref and result vector types should match");
5645  memElemTy = memVecTy.getElementType();
5646  }
5647 
5648  if (resVecTy.getElementType() != memElemTy)
5649  return emitOpError("base and result element types should match");
5650  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memRefTy.getRank())
5651  return emitOpError("requires ") << memRefTy.getRank() << " indices";
5652  return success();
5653 }
5654 
5655 OpFoldResult LoadOp::fold(FoldAdaptor) {
5656  if (succeeded(memref::foldMemRefCast(*this)))
5657  return getResult();
5658  return OpFoldResult();
5659 }
5660 
5661 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>> LoadOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
5662  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getVectorType().getShape());
5663 }
5664 
5665 FailureOr<std::optional<SmallVector<Value>>>
5666 LoadOp::bubbleDownCasts(OpBuilder &builder) {
5667  return mlir::detail::bubbleDownInPlaceMemorySpaceCastImpl(getBaseMutable(),
5668  getResult());
5669 }

5674 
5675 LogicalResult vector::StoreOp::verify() {
5676  VectorType valueVecTy = getVectorType();
5677  MemRefType memRefTy = getMemRefType();
5678 
5679  if (failed(verifyLoadStoreMemRefLayout(*this, valueVecTy, memRefTy)))
5680  return failure();
5681 
5682  if (memRefTy.getRank() < valueVecTy.getRank())
5683  return emitOpError("source memref has lower rank than the vector to store");
5684 
5685  // Checks for vector memrefs.
5686  Type memElemTy = memRefTy.getElementType();
5687  if (auto memVecTy = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(memElemTy)) {
5688  if (memVecTy != valueVecTy)
5689  return emitOpError(
5690  "base memref and valueToStore vector types should match");
5691  memElemTy = memVecTy.getElementType();
5692  }
5693 
5694  if (valueVecTy.getElementType() != memElemTy)
5695  return emitOpError("base and valueToStore element type should match");
5696  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memRefTy.getRank())
5697  return emitOpError("requires ") << memRefTy.getRank() << " indices";
5698  return success();
5699 }

5722  VectorType passVType = getPassThruVectorType();
5723  VectorType resVType = getVectorType();
5724  MemRefType memType = getMemRefType();
5725

5727  return emitOpError("base and result element type should match");

5729  return emitOpError("requires ") << memType.getRank() << " indices";
5730  if (resVType.getShape() != maskVType.getShape())
5731  return emitOpError("expected result shape to match mask shape");
5732  if (resVType != passVType)
5733  return emitOpError("expected pass_thru of same type as result type");
5734  return success();
5735 }

5836 LogicalResult GatherOp::verify() {
5837  VectorType indVType = getIndexVectorType();
5838  VectorType maskVType = getMaskVectorType();
5839  VectorType resVType = getVectorType();
5840  ShapedType baseType = getBaseType();
5841 
5842  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(baseType))
5843  return emitOpError("requires base to be a memref or ranked tensor type");
5844 
5845  if (resVType.getElementType() != baseType.getElementType())
5846  return emitOpError("base and result element type should match");
5847  if (llvm::size(getOffsets()) != baseType.getRank())
5848  return emitOpError("requires ") << baseType.getRank() << " indices";
5849  if (resVType.getShape() != indVType.getShape())
5850  return emitOpError("expected result dim to match indices dim");
5851  if (resVType.getShape() != maskVType.getShape())
5852  return emitOpError("expected result dim to match mask dim");
5853  if (resVType != getPassThruVectorType())
5854  return emitOpError("expected pass_thru of same type as result type");
5855  return success();
5856 }

5860 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
5861 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
5862 Type GatherOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
5863  auto vecType = this->getIndexVectorType();
5864  return VectorType::get(vecType.getShape(),
5865  IntegerType::get(vecType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
5866  vecType.getScalableDims());
5867 }

5870  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getVectorType().getShape());
5871 }
5872 
5873 /// Cheeck if `indexVec` is constant 1D vec of consecutive values [0, 1, 2, ...]
5874 static LogicalResult isZeroBasedContiguousSeq(Value indexVec) {
5875  auto vecType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(indexVec.getType());
5876  if (!vecType || vecType.getRank() != 1 || vecType.isScalable())
5877  return failure();
5878 
5879  if (indexVec.getDefiningOp<StepOp>())
5880  return success();
5881 
5882  DenseIntElementsAttr elements;
5883  if (!matchPattern(indexVec, m_Constant(&elements)))
5884  return failure();
5885 
5886  return success(
5887  llvm::equal(elements, llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, vecType.getNumElements())));
5888 }

5901  return success();

5903  return failure();
5904  }

5906  }

5917  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(op, "base must be of memref type");

6123 
6124 LogicalResult ShapeCastOp::verify() {
6125 
6126  VectorType sourceType = getSourceVectorType();
6127  VectorType resultType = getResultVectorType();
6128 
6129  // Check that element type is preserved
6130  if (sourceType.getElementType() != resultType.getElementType())
6131  return emitOpError("has different source and result element types");
6132 
6133  // Check that number of elements is preserved
6134  int64_t sourceNElms = sourceType.getNumElements();
6135  int64_t resultNElms = resultType.getNumElements();
6136  if (sourceNElms != resultNElms) {
6137  return emitOpError() << "has different number of elements at source ("
6138  << sourceNElms << ") and result (" << resultNElms
6139  << ")";
6140  }
6141 
6142  // Check that (non-)scalability is preserved
6143  int64_t sourceNScalableDims = sourceType.getNumScalableDims();
6144  int64_t resultNScalableDims = resultType.getNumScalableDims();
6145  if (sourceNScalableDims != resultNScalableDims)
6146  return emitOpError() << "has different number of scalable dims at source ("
6147  << sourceNScalableDims << ") and result ("
6148  << resultNScalableDims << ")";
6149 
6150  return success();
6151 }
6152 
6153 /// Return true if `transpose` does not permute a pair of non-unit dims.
6154 /// By `order preserving` we mean that the flattened versions of the input and
6155 /// output vectors are (numerically) identical. In other words `transpose` is
6156 /// effectively a shape cast.
6157 static bool isOrderPreserving(TransposeOp transpose) {
6158  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation = transpose.getPermutation();
6159  VectorType sourceType = transpose.getSourceVectorType();
6160  ArrayRef<int64_t> inShape = sourceType.getShape();
6161  ArrayRef<bool> inDimIsScalable = sourceType.getScalableDims();
6162  auto isNonScalableUnitDim = [&](int64_t dim) {
6163  return inShape[dim] == 1 && !inDimIsScalable[dim];
6164  };
6165  int64_t current = 0;
6166  for (auto p : permutation) {
6167  if (!isNonScalableUnitDim(p)) {
6168  if (p < current) {
6169  return false;
6170  }
6171  current = p;
6172  }
6173  }
6174  return true;
6175 }
6176 
6177 OpFoldResult ShapeCastOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6178 
6179  VectorType resultType = getType();
6180 
6181  // No-op shape cast.
6182  if (getSource().getType() == resultType)
6183  return getSource();
6184 
6185  // shape_cast(shape_cast(x)) -> shape_cast(x)
6186  if (auto precedingShapeCast = getSource().getDefiningOp<ShapeCastOp>()) {
6187  setOperand(precedingShapeCast.getSource());
6188  return getResult();
6189  }
6190 
6191  // shape_cast(transpose(x)) -> shape_cast(x)
6192  if (auto transpose = getSource().getDefiningOp<TransposeOp>()) {
6193  if (isOrderPreserving(transpose)) {
6194  setOperand(transpose.getVector());
6195  return getResult();
6196  }
6197  return {};
6198  }
6199 
6200  // Y = shape_cast(broadcast(X))
6201  // -> X, if X and Y have same type
6202  if (auto bcastOp = getSource().getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>()) {
6203  if (bcastOp.getSourceType() == resultType)
6204  return bcastOp.getSource();
6205  }
6206 
6207  // shape_cast(constant) -> constant
6208  if (auto denseAttr =
6209  dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
6210  return denseAttr.reshape(getType());
6211 
6212  // shape_cast(poison) -> poison
6213  if (llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<ub::PoisonAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
6214  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(getContext());
6215 
6216  return {};
6217 }
6218 
6219 namespace {
6220 
6221 /// Helper function that computes a new vector type based on the input vector
6222 /// type by removing the trailing one dims:
6223 ///
6224 /// vector<4x1x1xi1> --> vector<4x1xi1>
6225 ///
6226 static VectorType trimTrailingOneDims(VectorType oldType) {
6227  ArrayRef<int64_t> oldShape = oldType.getShape();
6228  ArrayRef<int64_t> newShape = oldShape;
6229 
6230  ArrayRef<bool> oldScalableDims = oldType.getScalableDims();
6231  ArrayRef<bool> newScalableDims = oldScalableDims;
6232 
6233  while (!newShape.empty() && newShape.back() == 1 && !newScalableDims.back()) {
6234  newShape = newShape.drop_back(1);
6235  newScalableDims = newScalableDims.drop_back(1);
6236  }
6237 
6238  // Make sure we have at least 1 dimension.
6239  // TODO: Add support for 0-D vectors.
6240  if (newShape.empty()) {
6241  newShape = oldShape.take_back();
6242  newScalableDims = oldScalableDims.take_back();
6243  }
6244 
6245  return VectorType::get(newShape, oldType.getElementType(), newScalableDims);
6246 }
6247 
6248 /// Folds qualifying shape_cast(create_mask) into a new create_mask
6249 ///
6250 /// Looks at `vector.shape_cast` Ops that simply "drop" the trailing unit
6251 /// dimension. If the input vector comes from `vector.create_mask` for which
6252 /// the corresponding mask input value is 1 (e.g. `%c1` below), then it is safe
6253 /// to fold shape_cast into create_mask.
6254 ///
6255 /// BEFORE:
6256 /// %1 = vector.create_mask %c1, %dim, %c1, %c1 : vector<1x[4]x1x1xi1>
6257 /// %2 = vector.shape_cast %1 : vector<1x[4]x1x1xi1> to vector<1x[4]xi1>
6258 /// AFTER:
6259 /// %0 = vector.create_mask %c1, %dim : vector<1x[4]xi1>
6260 class ShapeCastCreateMaskFolderTrailingOneDim final
6261  : public OpRewritePattern<ShapeCastOp> {
6262 public:
6263  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6264 
6265  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShapeCastOp shapeOp,
6266  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6267  Value shapeOpSrc = shapeOp->getOperand(0);
6268  auto createMaskOp = shapeOpSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>();
6269  auto constantMaskOp = shapeOpSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>();
6270  if (!createMaskOp && !constantMaskOp)
6271  return failure();
6272 
6273  VectorType shapeOpResTy = shapeOp.getResultVectorType();
6274  VectorType shapeOpSrcTy = shapeOp.getSourceVectorType();
6275 
6276  VectorType newVecType = trimTrailingOneDims(shapeOpSrcTy);
6277  if (newVecType != shapeOpResTy)
6278  return failure();
6279 
6280  auto numDimsToDrop =
6281  shapeOpSrcTy.getShape().size() - shapeOpResTy.getShape().size();
6282 
6283  // No unit dims to drop
6284  if (!numDimsToDrop)
6285  return failure();
6286 
6287  if (createMaskOp) {
6288  auto maskOperands = createMaskOp.getOperands();
6289  auto numMaskOperands = maskOperands.size();
6290 
6291  // Check every mask dim size to see whether it can be dropped
6292  for (size_t i = numMaskOperands - 1; i >= numMaskOperands - numDimsToDrop;
6293  --i) {
6294  auto constant = maskOperands[i].getDefiningOp<arith::ConstantIndexOp>();
6295  if (!constant || (constant.value() != 1))
6296  return failure();
6297  }
6298  SmallVector<Value> newMaskOperands =
6299  maskOperands.drop_back(numDimsToDrop);
6300 
6301  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>(shapeOp, shapeOpResTy,
6302  newMaskOperands);
6303  return success();
6304  }
6305 
6306  if (constantMaskOp) {
6307  auto maskDimSizes = constantMaskOp.getMaskDimSizes();
6308  auto numMaskOperands = maskDimSizes.size();
6309 
6310  // Check every mask dim size to see whether it can be dropped
6311  for (size_t i = numMaskOperands - 1; i >= numMaskOperands - numDimsToDrop;
6312  --i) {
6313  if (maskDimSizes[i] != 1)
6314  return failure();
6315  }
6316 
6317  auto newMaskOperands = maskDimSizes.drop_back(numDimsToDrop);
6318  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>(shapeOp, shapeOpResTy,
6319  newMaskOperands);
6320  return success();
6321  }
6322 
6323  return failure();
6324  }
6325 };
6326 
6327 /// Pattern to rewrite Y = ShapeCast(Broadcast(X)) as either
6328 /// i) Y = ShapeCast(X), or
6329 /// ii) Y = Broadcast(X)
6330 /// If both (i) and (ii) are possible, (i) is chosen.
6331 class ShapeCastBroadcastFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<ShapeCastOp> {
6332 public:
6333  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6334 
6335  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShapeCastOp shapeCastOp,
6336  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6337  auto broadcastOp =
6338  shapeCastOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<vector::BroadcastOp>();
6339  if (!broadcastOp)
6340  return failure();
6341 
6342  auto srcVectorType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(broadcastOp.getSourceType());
6343  bool srcIsScalar = !srcVectorType;
6344 
6345  // Replace Y = ShapeCast(Broadcast(X)) with Y = ShapeCast(X).
6346  // Example:
6347  // %0 = vector.broadcast %in : vector<3x4xf32> to vector<1x3x4xf32>
6348  // %1 = vector.shape_cast %0 : vector<1x3x4xf32> to vector<12xf32>
6349  // to
6350  // %1 = vector.shape_cast %in : vector<3x4xf32> to vector<12xf32>
6351  if (srcVectorType) {
6352  if (srcVectorType.getNumElements() ==
6353  shapeCastOp.getResultVectorType().getNumElements()) {
6354  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(
6355  shapeCastOp, shapeCastOp.getResultVectorType(),
6356  broadcastOp.getSource());
6357  return success();
6358  }
6359  }
6360 
6361  // Replace Y = ShapeCast(Broadcast(X)) with Y = Broadcast(X)
6362  // Example
6363  // %0 = vector.broadcast %in : vector<3xf32> to vector<2x4x3xf32>
6364  // %1 = vector.shape_cast %0 : vector<2x4x3xf32> to vector<8x3xf32>
6365  // to
6366  // %1 = vector.broadcast %in : vector<3xf32> to vector<8x3xf32>
6367  VectorType dstVectorType = shapeCastOp.getResultVectorType();
6368  if (srcIsScalar || isBroadcastableTo(srcVectorType, dstVectorType) ==
6369  BroadcastableToResult::Success) {
6370  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(
6371  shapeCastOp, dstVectorType, broadcastOp.getSource());
6372  return success();
6373  }
6374  return failure();
6375  }
6376 };
6377 
6378 } // namespace
6379 
6380 void ShapeCastOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
6381  MLIRContext *context) {
6382  results
6383  .add<ShapeCastCreateMaskFolderTrailingOneDim, ShapeCastBroadcastFolder>(
6384  context);
6385 }

6387 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6388 // VectorBitCastOp
6389 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6390 
6391 LogicalResult BitCastOp::verify() {
6392  auto sourceVectorType = getSourceVectorType();
6393  auto resultVectorType = getResultVectorType();
6394 
6395  for (int64_t i = 0, e = sourceVectorType.getRank() - 1; i < e; i++) {
6396  if (sourceVectorType.getDimSize(i) != resultVectorType.getDimSize(i))
6397  return emitOpError("dimension size mismatch at: ") << i;
6398  }
6399 
6400  DataLayout dataLayout = DataLayout::closest(*this);
6401  auto sourceElementBits =
6402  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(sourceVectorType.getElementType());
6403  auto resultElementBits =
6404  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(resultVectorType.getElementType());
6405 
6406  if (sourceVectorType.getRank() == 0) {
6407  if (sourceElementBits != resultElementBits)
6408  return emitOpError("source/result bitwidth of the 0-D vector element "
6409  "types must be equal");
6410  } else if (sourceElementBits * sourceVectorType.getShape().back() !=
6411  resultElementBits * resultVectorType.getShape().back()) {
6412  return emitOpError(
6413  "source/result bitwidth of the minor 1-D vectors must be equal");
6414  }
6415 
6416  return success();
6417 }
6418 
6419 OpFoldResult BitCastOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6420  // Nop cast.
6421  if (getSource().getType() == getResult().getType())
6422  return getSource();
6423 
6424  // Canceling bitcasts.
6425  if (auto otherOp = getSource().getDefiningOp<BitCastOp>()) {
6426  if (getResult().getType() == otherOp.getSource().getType())
6427  return otherOp.getSource();
6428 
6429  setOperand(otherOp.getSource());
6430  return getResult();
6431  }
6432 
6433  Attribute sourceConstant = adaptor.getSource();
6434  if (!sourceConstant)
6435  return {};
6436 
6437  Type srcElemType = getSourceVectorType().getElementType();
6438  Type dstElemType = getResultVectorType().getElementType();
6439 
6440  if (auto floatPack = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseFPElementsAttr>(sourceConstant)) {
6441  if (floatPack.isSplat()) {
6442  auto splat = floatPack.getSplatValue<FloatAttr>();
6443 
6444  // Casting fp16 into fp32.
6445  if (srcElemType.isF16() && dstElemType.isF32()) {
6446  uint32_t bits = static_cast<uint32_t>(
6447  splat.getValue().bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue());
6448  // Duplicate the 16-bit pattern.
6449  bits = (bits << 16) | (bits & 0xffff);
6450  APInt intBits(32, bits);
6451  APFloat floatBits(llvm::APFloat::IEEEsingle(), intBits);
6452  return DenseElementsAttr::get(getResultVectorType(), floatBits);
6453  }
6454  }
6455  }
6456 
6457  if (auto intPack = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseIntElementsAttr>(sourceConstant)) {
6458  if (intPack.isSplat()) {
6459  auto splat = intPack.getSplatValue<IntegerAttr>();
6460 
6461  if (llvm::isa<IntegerType>(dstElemType)) {
6462  uint64_t srcBitWidth = srcElemType.getIntOrFloatBitWidth();
6463  uint64_t dstBitWidth = dstElemType.getIntOrFloatBitWidth();
6464 
6465  // Casting to a larger integer bit width.
6466  if (dstBitWidth > srcBitWidth && dstBitWidth % srcBitWidth == 0) {
6467  APInt intBits = splat.getValue().zext(dstBitWidth);
6468 
6469  // Duplicate the lower width element.
6470  for (uint64_t i = 0; i < dstBitWidth / srcBitWidth - 1; i++)
6471  intBits = (intBits << srcBitWidth) | intBits;
6472  return DenseElementsAttr::get(getResultVectorType(), intBits);
6473  }
6474  }
6475  }
6476  }
6477 
6478  return {};
6479 }
6480 
6481 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6482 // TypeCastOp
6483 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6484 
6485 static SmallVector<int64_t, 8> extractShape(MemRefType memRefType) {
6486  auto vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(memRefType.getElementType());
6487  SmallVector<int64_t, 8> res(memRefType.getShape());
6488  if (vectorType)
6489  res.append(vectorType.getShape().begin(), vectorType.getShape().end());
6490  return res;
6491 }
6492 
6493 /// Build the canonical memRefType with a single vector.
6494 /// E.g. memref<4 x 5 x vector<6 x f32>> -> memref<vector<4 x 5 x 6 x f32>>.
6495 void TypeCastOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
6496  Value source) {
6497  result.addOperands(source);
6498  MemRefType memRefType = llvm::cast<MemRefType>(source.getType());
6499  VectorType vectorType =
6500  VectorType::get(extractShape(memRefType),
6501  getElementTypeOrSelf(getElementTypeOrSelf(memRefType)));
6502  result.addTypes(MemRefType::get({}, vectorType, MemRefLayoutAttrInterface(),
6503  memRefType.getMemorySpace()));
6504 }
6505 
6506 LogicalResult TypeCastOp::verify() {
6507  MemRefType canonicalType = getMemRefType().canonicalizeStridedLayout();
6508  if (!canonicalType.getLayout().isIdentity())
6509  return emitOpError("expects operand to be a memref with identity layout");
6510  if (!getResultMemRefType().getLayout().isIdentity())
6511  return emitOpError("expects result to be a memref with identity layout");
6512  if (getResultMemRefType().getMemorySpace() !=
6513  getMemRefType().getMemorySpace())
6514  return emitOpError("expects result in same memory space");
6515 
6516  auto sourceType = getMemRefType();
6517  auto resultType = getResultMemRefType();
6518  if (getElementTypeOrSelf(getElementTypeOrSelf(sourceType)) !=
6519  getElementTypeOrSelf(getElementTypeOrSelf(resultType)))
6520  return emitOpError(
6521  "expects result and operand with same underlying scalar type: ")
6522  << resultType;
6523  if (extractShape(sourceType) != extractShape(resultType))
6524  return emitOpError(
6525  "expects concatenated result and operand shapes to be equal: ")
6526  << resultType;
6527  return success();
6528 }

6530 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6531 // TransposeOp
6532 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6533 
6534 void vector::TransposeOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
6535  Value vector, ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation) {
6536  VectorType vt = llvm::cast<VectorType>(vector.getType());
6537  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> transposedShape(vt.getRank());
6538  SmallVector<bool, 4> transposedScalableDims(vt.getRank());
6539  for (unsigned i = 0; i < permutation.size(); ++i) {
6540  transposedShape[i] = vt.getShape()[permutation[i]];
6541  transposedScalableDims[i] = vt.getScalableDims()[permutation[i]];
6542  }
6543 
6544  result.addOperands(vector);
6545  result.addTypes(VectorType::get(transposedShape, vt.getElementType(),
6546  transposedScalableDims));
6547  result.addAttribute(TransposeOp::getPermutationAttrName(result.name),
6548  builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(permutation));
6549 }
6550 
6551 OpFoldResult vector::TransposeOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6552  // Eliminate splat constant transpose ops.
6553  if (auto splat =
6554  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<SplatElementsAttr>(adaptor.getVector()))
6555  return splat.reshape(getResultVectorType());
6556 
6557  // Eliminate poison transpose ops.
6558  if (llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<ub::PoisonAttr>(adaptor.getVector()))
6559  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(getContext());
6560 
6561  // Eliminate identity transposes, and more generally any transposes that
6562  // preserves the shape without permuting elements.
6563  //
6564  // Examples of what to fold:
6565  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [0, 1] : vector<1x1xi8> to vector<1x1xi8>
6566  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [0, 1] : vector<2x2xi8> to vector<2x2xi8>
6567  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [1, 0] : vector<1x1xi8> to vector<1x1xi8>
6568  //
6569  // Example of what NOT to fold:
6570  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [1, 0] : vector<2x2xi8> to vector<2x2xi8>
6571  //
6572  if (getSourceVectorType() == getResultVectorType() &&
6573  isOrderPreserving(*this))
6574  return getVector();
6575 
6576  return {};
6577 }
6578 
6579 LogicalResult vector::TransposeOp::verify() {
6580  VectorType vectorType = getSourceVectorType();
6581  VectorType resultType = getResultVectorType();
6582  int64_t rank = resultType.getRank();
6583  if (vectorType.getRank() != rank)
6584  return emitOpError("vector result rank mismatch: ") << rank;
6585  // Verify transposition array.
6586  ArrayRef<int64_t> perm = getPermutation();
6587  int64_t size = perm.size();
6588  if (rank != size)
6589  return emitOpError("transposition length mismatch: ") << size;
6590  SmallVector<bool, 8> seen(rank, false);
6591  for (const auto &ta : llvm::enumerate(perm)) {
6592  if (ta.value() < 0 || ta.value() >= rank)
6593  return emitOpError("transposition index out of range: ") << ta.value();
6594  if (seen[ta.value()])
6595  return emitOpError("duplicate position index: ") << ta.value();
6596  seen[ta.value()] = true;
6597  if (resultType.getDimSize(ta.index()) != vectorType.getDimSize(ta.value()))
6598  return emitOpError("dimension size mismatch at: ") << ta.value();
6599  }
6600  return success();
6601 }

6604  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getResultVectorType().getShape());
6605 }

6607 void TransposeOp::inferResultRanges(ArrayRef<ConstantIntRanges> argRanges,
6608  SetIntRangeFn setResultRanges) {
6609  setResultRanges(getResult(), argRanges.front());
6610 }

6614 // Rewrites two back-to-back TransposeOp operations into a single TransposeOp.
6615 class TransposeFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<vector::TransposeOp> {
6616 public:
6617  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6618 
6619  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(vector::TransposeOp transposeOp,
6620  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6621  // Composes two permutations: result[i] = permutation1[permutation2[i]].
6622  auto composePermutations = [](ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation1,
6623  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation2) {
6624  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> result;
6625  for (auto index : permutation2)
6626  result.push_back(permutation1[index]);
6627  return result;
6628  };
6629 
6630  // Return if the input of 'transposeOp' is not defined by another transpose.
6631  vector::TransposeOp parentTransposeOp =
6632  transposeOp.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::TransposeOp>();
6633  if (!parentTransposeOp)
6634  return failure();
6635 
6636  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> permutation = composePermutations(
6637  parentTransposeOp.getPermutation(), transposeOp.getPermutation());
6638  // Replace 'transposeOp' with a new transpose operation.
6639  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::TransposeOp>(
6640  transposeOp, transposeOp.getResult().getType(),
6641  parentTransposeOp.getVector(), permutation);
6642  return success();
6643  }
6644 };
6645 
6646 /// Replace transpose(splat-like(v)) with broadcast(v)
6647 class FoldTransposeSplat final : public OpRewritePattern<TransposeOp> {
6648 public:
6649  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6650 
6651  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransposeOp transposeOp,
6652  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6653  Value splat = getScalarSplatSource(transposeOp.getVector());
6654  if (!splat)
6655  return failure();
6656 
6657  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(
6658  transposeOp, transposeOp.getResultVectorType(), splat);
6659  return success();
6660  }
6661 };

6663 /// Folds transpose(create_mask) into a new transposed create_mask.
6664 class FoldTransposeCreateMask final : public OpRewritePattern<TransposeOp> {
6665 public:
6666  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6667 
6668  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransposeOp transpOp,
6669  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6670  Value transposeSrc = transpOp.getVector();
6671  auto createMaskOp = transposeSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>();
6672  auto constantMaskOp = transposeSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>();
6673  if (!createMaskOp && !constantMaskOp)
6674  return failure();
6675 
6676  // Get the transpose permutation and apply it to the vector.create_mask or
6677  // vector.constant_mask operands.
6678  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation = transpOp.getPermutation();
6679 
6680  if (createMaskOp) {
6681  auto maskOperands = createMaskOp.getOperands();
6682  SmallVector<Value> newOperands(maskOperands.begin(), maskOperands.end());
6683  applyPermutationToVector(newOperands, permutation);
6684 
6685  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>(
6686  transpOp, transpOp.getResultVectorType(), newOperands);
6687  return success();
6688  }
6689 
6690  // ConstantMaskOp case.
6691  auto maskDimSizes = constantMaskOp.getMaskDimSizes();
6692  auto newMaskDimSizes = applyPermutation(maskDimSizes, permutation);
6693 
6694  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>(
6695  transpOp, transpOp.getResultVectorType(), newMaskDimSizes);
6696  return success();
6697  }
6698 };

6700 /// Folds transpose(shape_cast) into a new shape_cast.
6701 class FoldTransposeShapeCast final : public OpRewritePattern<TransposeOp> {
6702 public:
6703  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6704 
6705  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransposeOp transposeOp,
6706  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6707  auto shapeCastOp =
6708  transposeOp.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>();
6709  if (!shapeCastOp)
6710  return failure();
6711  if (!isOrderPreserving(transposeOp))
6712  return failure();
6713 
6714  VectorType resultType = transposeOp.getType();
6715 
6716  // We don't need to check isValidShapeCast at this point, because it is
6717  // guaranteed that merging the transpose into the the shape_cast is a valid
6718  // shape_cast, because the transpose just inserts/removes ones.
6719 
6720  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(transposeOp, resultType,
6721  shapeCastOp.getSource());
6722  return success();
6723  }
6724 };
6725 
6726 /// Folds transpose(broadcast(x)) to broadcast(x) if the transpose is
6727 /// 'order preserving', where 'order preserving' means the flattened
6728 /// inputs and outputs of the transpose have identical (numerical) values.
6729 ///
6730 /// Example:
6731 /// ```
6732 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %input : vector<1x1xi32> to vector<1x8xi32>
6733 /// %1 = vector.transpose %0, [1, 0] : vector<1x8xi32>
6734 /// to vector<8x1xi32>
6735 /// ```
6736 /// can be rewritten as the equivalent
6737 /// ```
6738 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %input : vector<1x1xi32> to vector<8x1xi32>.
6739 /// ```
6740 /// The algorithm works by partitioning dimensions into groups that can be
6741 /// locally permuted while preserving order, and checks that the transpose
6742 /// only permutes within these groups.
6743 ///
6744 /// Groups are either contiguous sequences of 1s, or non-1s (1-element groups).
6745 /// Consider broadcasting 4x1x1x7 to 2x3x4x5x6x7. This is equivalent to
6746 /// broadcasting from 1x1x4x1x1x7.
6747 /// ^^^ ^ ^^^ ^
6748 /// groups: 0 1 2 3
6749 /// Order preserving permutations for this example are ones that only permute
6750 /// within the groups [0,1] and [3,4], like (1 0 2 4 3 5 6).
6751 class FoldTransposeBroadcast : public OpRewritePattern<vector::TransposeOp> {
6752 public:
6753  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6754  FoldTransposeBroadcast(MLIRContext *context, PatternBenefit benefit = 1)
6755  : OpRewritePattern<vector::TransposeOp>(context, benefit) {}
6756 
6757  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(vector::TransposeOp transpose,
6758  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6759 
6760  vector::BroadcastOp broadcast =
6761  transpose.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::BroadcastOp>();
6762  if (!broadcast) {
6763  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(transpose,
6764  "not preceded by a broadcast");
6765  }
6766 
6767  auto inputType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(broadcast.getSourceType());
6768  VectorType outputType = transpose.getResultVectorType();
6769 
6770  // transpose(broadcast(scalar)) -> broadcast(scalar) is always valid
6771  bool inputIsScalar = !inputType;
6772  if (inputIsScalar) {
6773  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(transpose, outputType,
6774  broadcast.getSource());
6775  return success();
6776  }
6777 
6778  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation = transpose.getPermutation();
6779  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
6780  int64_t inputRank = inputType.getRank();
6781  int64_t outputRank = transpose.getType().getRank();
6782  int64_t deltaRank = outputRank - inputRank;
6783 
6784  int low = 0;
6785  for (int inputIndex = 0; inputIndex < inputRank; ++inputIndex) {
6786  bool notOne = inputShape[inputIndex] != 1;
6787  bool prevNotOne = (inputIndex != 0 && inputShape[inputIndex - 1] != 1);
6788  bool groupEndFound = notOne || prevNotOne;
6789  if (groupEndFound) {
6790  int high = inputIndex + deltaRank;
6791  // Return failure if not all permutation destinations for indices in
6792  // [low, high) are in [low, high), i.e. the permutation is not local to
6793  // the group.
6794  for (int i = low; i < high; ++i) {
6795  if (permutation[i] < low || permutation[i] >= high) {
6796  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
6797  transpose, "permutation not local to group");
6798  }
6799  }
6800  low = high;
6801  }
6802  }
6803 
6804  // We don't need to check the final group [low, outputRank) because if it is
6805  // not locally bound, there must be a preceding group that already failed
6806  // the check (impossible to have just 1 non-locally bound group).
6807 
6808  // The preceding logic also ensures that at this point, the output of the
6809  // transpose is definitely broadcastable from the input shape, assert so:
6810  assert(vector::isBroadcastableTo(inputType, outputType) ==
6811  vector::BroadcastableToResult::Success &&
6812  "not broadcastable directly to transpose output");
6813 
6814  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(transpose, outputType,
6815  broadcast.getSource());
6816 
6817  return success();
6818  }
6819 };
6820 
6821 } // namespace
6822 
6823 void vector::TransposeOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(
6824  RewritePatternSet &results, MLIRContext *context) {
6825  results.add<FoldTransposeCreateMask, FoldTransposeShapeCast, TransposeFolder,
6826  FoldTransposeSplat, FoldTransposeBroadcast>(context);
6827 }

6833 void ConstantMaskOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
6834  VectorType type, ConstantMaskKind kind) {
6835  assert(kind == ConstantMaskKind::AllTrue ||
6836  kind == ConstantMaskKind::AllFalse);
6837  build(builder, result, type,
6838  kind == ConstantMaskKind::AllTrue
6839  ? type.getShape()
6840  : SmallVector<int64_t>(type.getRank(), 0));
6841 }
6842 
6843 LogicalResult ConstantMaskOp::verify() {
6844  auto resultType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType());
6845  // Check the corner case of 0-D vectors first.
6846  if (resultType.getRank() == 0) {
6847  if (getMaskDimSizes().size() != 1)
6848  return emitError("array attr must have length 1 for 0-D vectors");
6849  auto dim = getMaskDimSizes()[0];
6850  if (dim != 0 && dim != 1)
6851  return emitError("mask dim size must be either 0 or 1 for 0-D vectors");
6852  return success();
6853  }
6854 
6855  // Verify that array attr size matches the rank of the vector result.
6856  if (static_cast<int64_t>(getMaskDimSizes().size()) != resultType.getRank())
6857  return emitOpError(
6858  "must specify array attr of size equal vector result rank");
6859  // Verify that each array attr element is in bounds of corresponding vector
6860  // result dimension size.
6861  auto resultShape = resultType.getShape();
6862  auto resultScalableDims = resultType.getScalableDims();
6863  ArrayRef<int64_t> maskDimSizes = getMaskDimSizes();
6864  for (const auto [index, maskDimSize] : llvm::enumerate(maskDimSizes)) {
6865  if (maskDimSize < 0 || maskDimSize > resultShape[index])
6866  return emitOpError(
6867  "array attr of size out of bounds of vector result dimension size");
6868  if (resultScalableDims[index] && maskDimSize != 0 &&
6869  maskDimSize != resultShape[index])
6870  return emitOpError(
6871  "only supports 'none set' or 'all set' scalable dimensions");
6872  }
6873  // Verify that if one mask dim size is zero, they all should be zero (because
6874  // the mask region is a conjunction of each mask dimension interval).
6875  bool anyZeros = llvm::is_contained(maskDimSizes, 0);
6876  bool allZeros = llvm::all_of(maskDimSizes, [](int64_t s) { return s == 0; });
6877  if (anyZeros && !allZeros)
6878  return emitOpError("expected all mask dim sizes to be zeros, "
6879  "as a result of conjunction with zero mask dim");
6880  return success();
6881 }
6882 
6883 bool ConstantMaskOp::isAllOnesMask() {
6884  auto resultType = getVectorType();
6885  // Check the corner case of 0-D vectors first.
6886  if (resultType.getRank() == 0) {
6887  assert(getMaskDimSizes().size() == 1 && "invalid sizes for zero rank mask");
6888  return getMaskDimSizes()[0] == 1;
6889  }
6890  for (const auto [resultSize, maskDimSize] :
6891  llvm::zip_equal(resultType.getShape(), getMaskDimSizes())) {
6892  if (maskDimSize < resultSize)
6893  return false;
6894  }
6895  return true;
6896 }
6897 
6898 OpFoldResult ConstantMaskOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6899  ArrayRef<int64_t> bounds = getMaskDimSizes();
6900  ArrayRef<int64_t> vectorSizes = getVectorType().getShape();
6901 
6902  auto createBoolSplat = [&](bool x) {
6903  return SplatElementsAttr::get(getVectorType(),
6904  BoolAttr::get(getContext(), x));
6905  };
6906 
6907  // Check the corner case of 0-D vectors first.
6908  if (vectorSizes.empty()) {
6909  assert(bounds.size() == 1 && "invalid sizes for zero rank mask");
6910  return createBoolSplat(bounds[0] == 1);
6911  }
6912  // Fold vector.constant_mask to splat if possible.
6913  if (bounds == vectorSizes)
6914  return createBoolSplat(true);
6915  if (llvm::all_of(bounds, [](int64_t x) { return x == 0; }))
6916  return createBoolSplat(false);
6917  return OpFoldResult();
6918 }

6927  SmallVector<Value> operands =
6928  getValueOrCreateConstantIndexOp(builder, result.location, mixedOperands);
6929  build(builder, result, type, operands);
6930 }

6932 LogicalResult CreateMaskOp::verify() {
6933  auto vectorType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType());
6934  // Verify that an operand was specified for each result vector each dimension.
6935  if (vectorType.getRank() == 0) {
6936  if (getNumOperands() != 1)
6937  return emitOpError(
6938  "must specify exactly one operand for 0-D create_mask");
6939  } else if (getNumOperands() !=
6940  llvm::cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType()).getRank()) {
6941  return emitOpError(
6942  "must specify an operand for each result vector dimension");
6943  }
6944  return success();
6945 }
6946 
6947 namespace {
6948 
6949 /// Pattern to rewrite a CreateMaskOp with a ConstantMaskOp.
6950 ///
6951 /// Ex 1:
6952 /// %c2 = arith.constant 2 : index
6953 /// %c3 = arith.constant 3 : index
6954 /// %0 = vector.create_mask %c3, %c2 : vector<4x3xi1>
6955 /// Becomes:
6956 /// vector.constant_mask [3, 2] : vector<4x3xi1>
6957 ///
6958 /// Ex 2:
6959 /// %c_neg_1 = arith.constant -1 : index
6960 /// %0 = vector.create_mask %c_neg_1 : vector<[8]xi1>
6961 /// becomes:
6962 /// vector.constant_mask [0] : vector<[8]xi1>
6963 ///
6964 /// Ex 3:
6965 /// %c8 = arith.constant 8 : index
6966 /// %c16 = arith.constant 16 : index
6967 /// %0 = vector.vscale
6968 /// %1 = arith.muli %0, %c16 : index
6969 /// %10 = vector.create_mask %c8, %1 : vector<8x[16]xi1>
6970 /// becomes:
6971 /// %0 = vector.constant_mask [8, 16] : vector<8x[16]xi1>
6972 class CreateMaskFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<CreateMaskOp> {
6973 public:
6974  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6975 
6976  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(CreateMaskOp createMaskOp,
6977  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6978  VectorType maskType = createMaskOp.getVectorType();
6979  ArrayRef<int64_t> maskTypeDimSizes = maskType.getShape();
6980  ArrayRef<bool> maskTypeDimScalableFlags = maskType.getScalableDims();
6981 
6982  // Special case: Rank zero shape.
6983  constexpr std::array<int64_t, 1> rankZeroShape{1};
6984  constexpr std::array<bool, 1> rankZeroScalableDims{false};
6985  if (maskType.getRank() == 0) {
6986  maskTypeDimSizes = rankZeroShape;
6987  maskTypeDimScalableFlags = rankZeroScalableDims;
6988  }
6989 
6990  // Determine if this CreateMaskOp can be folded to a ConstantMaskOp and
6991  // collect the `constantDims` (for the ConstantMaskOp).
6992  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> constantDims;
6993  for (auto [i, dimSize] : llvm::enumerate(createMaskOp.getOperands())) {
6994  if (auto intSize = getConstantIntValue(dimSize)) {
6995  // Constant value.
6996  // If the mask dim is non-scalable this can be any value.
6997  // If the mask dim is scalable only zero (all-false) is supported.
6998  if (maskTypeDimScalableFlags[i] && intSize >= 0)
6999  return failure();
7000  constantDims.push_back(*intSize);
7001  } else if (auto vscaleMultiplier = getConstantVscaleMultiplier(dimSize)) {
7002  // Constant vscale multiple (e.g. 4 x vscale).
7003  // Must be all-true to fold to a ConstantMask.
7004  if (vscaleMultiplier < maskTypeDimSizes[i])
7005  return failure();
7006  constantDims.push_back(*vscaleMultiplier);
7007  } else {
7008  return failure();
7009  }
7010  }
7011 
7012  // Clamp values to constant_mask bounds.
7013  for (auto [value, maskDimSize] : llvm::zip(constantDims, maskTypeDimSizes))
7014  value = std::clamp<int64_t>(value, 0, maskDimSize);
7015 
7016  // If one of dim sizes is zero, set all dims to zero.
7017  if (llvm::is_contained(constantDims, 0))
7018  constantDims.assign(constantDims.size(), 0);
7019 
7020  // Replace 'createMaskOp' with ConstantMaskOp.
7021  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<ConstantMaskOp>(createMaskOp, maskType,
7022  constantDims);
7023  return success();
7024  }
7025 };
7026 
7027 } // namespace
7028 
7029 void CreateMaskOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
7030  MLIRContext *context) {
7031  results.add<CreateMaskFolder>(context);
7032 }

7038 void MaskOp::build(
7039  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, Value mask,
7040  Operation *maskableOp,
7041  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Operation *)> maskRegionBuilder) {
7042  assert(maskRegionBuilder &&
7043  "builder callback for 'maskRegion' must be present");
7044 
7045  result.addOperands(mask);
7046  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(builder);
7047  Region *maskRegion = result.addRegion();
7048  builder.createBlock(maskRegion);
7049  maskRegionBuilder(builder, maskableOp);
7050 }

7060 void MaskOp::build(
7061  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, TypeRange resultTypes,
7062  Value mask, Value passthru, Operation *maskableOp,
7063  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Operation *)> maskRegionBuilder) {
7064  build(builder, result, mask, maskableOp, maskRegionBuilder);
7065  if (passthru)
7066  result.addOperands(passthru);

7069 
7070 ParseResult MaskOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
7071  // Create the op region.
7072  result.regions.reserve(1);
7073  Region &maskRegion = *result.addRegion();
7074 
7075  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
7076 
7077  // Parse all the operands.
7078  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand mask;
7079  if (parser.parseOperand(mask))
7080  return failure();
7081 
7082  // Optional passthru operand.
7083  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand passthru;
7084  ParseResult parsePassthru = parser.parseOptionalComma();
7085  if (parsePassthru.succeeded() && parser.parseOperand(passthru))
7086  return failure();
7087 
7088  // Parse op region.
7089  if (parser.parseRegion(maskRegion, /*arguments=*/{}, /*argTypes=*/{}))
7090  return failure();
7091 
7092  MaskOp::ensureTerminator(maskRegion, builder, result.location);
7093 
7094  // Parse the optional attribute list.
7095  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
7096  return failure();
7097 
7098  // Parse all the types.
7099  Type maskType;
7100  if (parser.parseColonType(maskType))
7101  return failure();
7102 
7103  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
7104  if (parser.parseOptionalArrowTypeList(resultTypes))
7105  return failure();
7106  result.types.append(resultTypes);
7107 
7108  // Resolve operands.
7109  if (parser.resolveOperand(mask, maskType, result.operands))
7110  return failure();
7111 
7112  if (parsePassthru.succeeded()) {
7113  if (resultTypes.empty())
7114  return parser.emitError(
7115  parser.getNameLoc(),
7116  "expects a result if passthru operand is provided");
7117 
7118  if (parser.resolveOperand(passthru, resultTypes[0], result.operands))
7119  return failure();
7120  }
7121 
7122  return success();
7123 }
7124 
7125 void mlir::vector::MaskOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
7126  p << " " << getMask();
7127  if (getPassthru())
7128  p << ", " << getPassthru();
7129 
7130  // Print single masked operation and skip terminator.
7131  p << " { ";
7132  Block *singleBlock = &getMaskRegion().getBlocks().front();
7133  if (singleBlock && !singleBlock->getOperations().empty())
7134  p.printCustomOrGenericOp(&singleBlock->front());
7135  p << " }";
7136 
7137  p.printOptionalAttrDict(getOperation()->getAttrs());
7138 
7139  p << " : " << getMask().getType();
7140  if (getNumResults() > 0)
7141  p << " -> " << getResultTypes();
7142 }
7143 
7144 void MaskOp::ensureTerminator(Region &region, Builder &builder, Location loc) {
7145  // 1. For an empty `vector.mask`, create a default terminator.
7146  if (region.empty() || region.front().empty()) {
7147  OpTrait::SingleBlockImplicitTerminator<vector::YieldOp>::Impl<
7148  MaskOp>::ensureTerminator(region, builder, loc);
7149  return;
7150  }
7151 
7152  // 2. For a non-empty `vector.mask` with an explicit terminator, do nothing.
7153  Block &block = region.front();
7154  if (isa<vector::YieldOp>(block.back()))
7155  return;
7156 
7157  // 3. For a non-empty `vector.mask` without an explicit terminator:
7158 
7159  // Create default terminator if the number of masked operations is not
7160  // one. This case will trigger a verification failure.
7161  if (block.getOperations().size() != 1) {
7162  OpTrait::SingleBlockImplicitTerminator<vector::YieldOp>::Impl<
7163  MaskOp>::ensureTerminator(region, builder, loc);
7164  return;
7165  }
7166 
7167  // Create a terminator that yields the results from the masked operation.
7168  OpBuilder opBuilder(builder.getContext());
7169  Operation *maskedOp = &block.front();
7170  opBuilder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
7171  vector::YieldOp::create(opBuilder, loc, maskedOp->getResults());
7172 }
7173 
7174 LogicalResult MaskOp::verify() {
7175  // Structural checks.
7176  Block &block = getMaskRegion().getBlocks().front();
7177  if (block.getOperations().empty())
7178  return emitOpError("expects a terminator within the mask region");
7179 
7180  unsigned numMaskRegionOps = block.getOperations().size();
7181  if (numMaskRegionOps > 2)
7182  return emitOpError("expects only one operation to mask");
7183 
7184  // Terminator checks.
7185  auto terminator = dyn_cast<vector::YieldOp>(block.back());
7186  if (!terminator)
7187  return emitOpError("expects a terminator within the mask region");
7188 
7189  if (terminator->getNumOperands() != getNumResults())
7190  return emitOpError(
7191  "expects number of results to match mask region yielded values");
7192 
7193  // Empty vector.mask. Nothing else to check.
7194  if (numMaskRegionOps == 1)
7195  return success();
7196 
7197  auto maskableOp = dyn_cast<MaskableOpInterface>(block.front());
7198  if (!maskableOp)
7199  return emitOpError("expects a MaskableOpInterface within the mask region");
7200 
7201  // Result checks.
7202  if (maskableOp->getNumResults() != getNumResults())
7203  return emitOpError("expects number of results to match maskable operation "
7204  "number of results");
7205 
7206  if (!llvm::equal(maskableOp->getResults(), terminator.getOperands()))
7207  return emitOpError("expects all the results from the MaskableOpInterface "
7208  "to match all the values returned by the terminator");
7209 
7210  if (!llvm::equal(maskableOp->getResultTypes(), getResultTypes()))
7211  return emitOpError(
7212  "expects result type to match maskable operation result type");
7213 
7214  if (llvm::count_if(maskableOp->getResultTypes(),
7215  [](Type t) { return llvm::isa<VectorType>(t); }) > 1)
7216  return emitOpError("multiple vector results not supported");
7217 
7218  // Mask checks.
7219  Type expectedMaskType = maskableOp.getExpectedMaskType();
7220  if (getMask().getType() != expectedMaskType)
7221  return emitOpError("expects a ")
7222  << expectedMaskType << " mask for the maskable operation";
7223 
7224  // Passthru checks.
7225  Value passthru = getPassthru();
7226  if (passthru) {
7227  if (!maskableOp.supportsPassthru())
7228  return emitOpError(
7229  "doesn't expect a passthru argument for this maskable operation");
7230 
7231  if (maskableOp->getNumResults() != 1)
7232  return emitOpError("expects result when passthru argument is provided");
7233 
7234  if (passthru.getType() != maskableOp->getResultTypes()[0])
7235  return emitOpError("expects passthru type to match result type");
7236  }
7237 
7238  return success();
7239 }
7240 
7241 /// Folds empty `vector.mask` with no passthru operand and with or without
7242 /// return values. For example:
7243 ///
7244 /// %0 = vector.mask %mask { vector.yield %a : vector<8xf32> } :
7245 /// vector<8xi1> -> vector<8xf32>
7246 /// %1 = user_op %0 : vector<8xf32>
7247 ///
7248 /// becomes:
7249 ///
7250 /// %0 = user_op %a : vector<8xf32>
7251 ///
7252 /// Empty `vector.mask` with passthru operand are handled by the canonicalizer
7253 /// as it requires creating new operations.
7254 
7255 static LogicalResult foldEmptyMaskOp(MaskOp maskOp, MaskOp::FoldAdaptor adaptor,
7256  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
7257  if (!maskOp.isEmpty() || maskOp.hasPassthru())
7258  return failure();
7259 
7260  Block *block = maskOp.getMaskBlock();
7261  auto terminator = cast<vector::YieldOp>(block->front());
7262  if (terminator.getNumOperands() == 0) {
7263  // `vector.mask` has no results, just remove the `vector.mask`.
7264  return success();
7265  }
7266 
7267  // `vector.mask` has results, propagate the results.
7268  llvm::append_range(results, terminator.getOperands());
7269  return success();
7270 }
7271 
7272 LogicalResult MaskOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor,
7273  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
7274  if (succeeded(foldEmptyMaskOp(*this, adaptor, results)))
7275  return success();
7276 
7277  MaskFormat maskFormat = getMaskFormat(getMask());
7278  if (maskFormat != MaskFormat::AllTrue)
7279  return failure();
7280 
7281  // Move maskable operation outside of the `vector.mask` region.
7282  Operation *maskableOp = getMaskableOp();
7283  maskableOp->dropAllUses();
7284  maskableOp->moveBefore(getOperation());
7285 
7286  llvm::append_range(results, maskableOp->getResults());
7287  return success();
7288 }
7289 
7290 /// Canonialize empty `vector.mask` operations that can't be handled in
7291 /// `VectorMask::fold` as they require creating new operations.
7292 ///
7293 /// Example 1: Empty `vector.mask` with passthru operand.
7294 ///
7295 /// %0 = vector.mask %mask, %passthru { vector.yield %a : vector<8xf32> } :
7296 /// vector<8xi1> -> vector<8xf32>
7297 ///
7298 /// becomes:
7299 ///
7300 /// %0 = arith.select %mask, %a, %passthru : vector<8xf32>
7301 ///
7302 class CanonializeEmptyMaskOp : public OpRewritePattern<MaskOp> {
7303  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
7304 
7305  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(MaskOp maskOp,
7306  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
7307  if (!maskOp.isEmpty())
7308  return failure();
7309 
7310  if (!maskOp.hasPassthru())
7311  return failure();
7312 
7313  Block *block = maskOp.getMaskBlock();
7314  auto terminator = cast<vector::YieldOp>(block->front());
7315  assert(terminator.getNumOperands() == 1 &&
7316  "expected one result when passthru is provided");
7317 
7318  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<arith::SelectOp>(
7319  maskOp, maskOp.getResultTypes(), maskOp.getMask(),
7320  terminator.getOperand(0), maskOp.getPassthru());
7321 
7322  return success();
7323  }
7324 };
7325 
7326 void MaskOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
7327  MLIRContext *context) {
7328  results.add<CanonializeEmptyMaskOp>(context);
7329 }

7333 /// Returns the operation masked by this 'vector.mask'.
7334 Operation *MaskOp::getMaskableOp() {
7335  Block *block = getMaskBlock();
7336  if (block->getOperations().size() < 2)
7337  return nullptr;
7338 
7339  return &block->front();
7340 }

7342 /// Returns true if 'vector.mask' has a passthru value.
7343 bool MaskOp::hasPassthru() { return getPassthru() != Value(); }

7345 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7346 // ScanOp
7347 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7348 
7349 LogicalResult ScanOp::verify() {
7350  VectorType srcType = getSourceType();
7351  VectorType initialType = getInitialValueType();
7352  // Check reduction dimension < rank.
7353  int64_t srcRank = srcType.getRank();
7354  int64_t reductionDim = getReductionDim();
7355  if (reductionDim >= srcRank)
7356  return emitOpError("reduction dimension ")
7357  << reductionDim << " has to be less than " << srcRank;
7358 
7359  // Check that rank(initial_value) = rank(src) - 1.
7360  int64_t initialValueRank = initialType.getRank();
7361  if (initialValueRank != srcRank - 1)
7362  return emitOpError("initial value rank ")
7363  << initialValueRank << " has to be equal to " << srcRank - 1;
7364 
7365  // Check shapes of initial value and src.
7366  ArrayRef<int64_t> srcShape = srcType.getShape();
7367  ArrayRef<int64_t> initialValueShapes = initialType.getShape();
7368  SmallVector<int64_t> expectedShape;
7369  for (int i = 0; i < srcRank; i++) {
7370  if (i != reductionDim)
7371  expectedShape.push_back(srcShape[i]);
7372  }
7373  if (!llvm::equal(initialValueShapes, expectedShape)) {
7374  return emitOpError("incompatible input/initial value shapes");
7375  }
7376 
7377  // Verify supported reduction kind.
7378  Type eltType = getDestType().getElementType();
7379  if (!isSupportedCombiningKind(getKind(), eltType))
7380  return emitOpError("unsupported reduction type ")
7381  << eltType << " for kind '" << stringifyCombiningKind(getKind())
7382  << "'";
7383 
7384  return success();
7385 }
7386 
7387 void mlir::vector::populateVectorToVectorCanonicalizationPatterns(
7388  RewritePatternSet &patterns, PatternBenefit benefit) {
7389  patterns
7390  .add<CreateMaskFolder, MaskedLoadFolder, MaskedStoreFolder, GatherFolder,
7391  ScatterFolder, ExpandLoadFolder, CompressStoreFolder,
7392  StridedSliceConstantMaskFolder, TransposeFolder>(
7393  patterns.getContext(), benefit);
7394 }

7400 OpFoldResult SplatOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
7401  auto constOperand = adaptor.getInput();
7402  if (!isa_and_nonnull<IntegerAttr, FloatAttr>(constOperand))
7403  return {};
7404 
7405  // SplatElementsAttr::get treats single value for second arg as being a splat.
7406  return SplatElementsAttr::get(getType(), {constOperand});
7407 }
7408 
7409 // Canonicalizer for vector.splat. It always gets canonicalized to a
7410 // vector.broadcast.
7411 class SplatToBroadcastPattern final : public OpRewritePattern<SplatOp> {
7412 public:
7413  using OpRewritePattern<SplatOp>::OpRewritePattern;
7414  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(SplatOp splatOp,
7415  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
7416  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(splatOp, splatOp.getType(),
7417  splatOp.getOperand());
7418  return success();
7419  }
7420 };
7421 void SplatOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
7422  MLIRContext *context) {
7423  results.add<SplatToBroadcastPattern>(context);
7424 }
7425 
7426 void SplatOp::inferResultRanges(ArrayRef<ConstantIntRanges> argRanges,
7427  SetIntRangeFn setResultRanges) {
7428  setResultRanges(getResult(), argRanges.front());
7429 }
7430 
7431 Value mlir::vector::makeArithReduction(OpBuilder &b, Location loc,
7432  CombiningKind kind, Value v1, Value acc,
7433  arith::FastMathFlagsAttr fastmath,
7434  Value mask) {
7435  Type t1 = getElementTypeOrSelf(v1.getType());
7436  Type tAcc = getElementTypeOrSelf(acc.getType());
7437  Value result;
7438 
7439  switch (kind) {
7440  case CombiningKind::ADD:
7441  if (t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex())
7442  result = b.createOrFold<arith::AddIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7443  else if (llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc))
7444  result = b.createOrFold<arith::AddFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7445  else
7446  llvm_unreachable("invalid value types for ADD reduction");
7447  break;
7448  case CombiningKind::AND:
7449  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7450  result = b.createOrFold<arith::AndIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7451  break;
7452  case CombiningKind::MAXNUMF:
7453  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7454  "expected float values");
7455  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaxNumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7456  break;
7457  case CombiningKind::MAXIMUMF:
7458  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7459  "expected float values");
7460  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaximumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7461  break;
7462  case CombiningKind::MINNUMF:
7463  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7464  "expected float values");
7465  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinNumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7466  break;
7467  case CombiningKind::MINIMUMF:
7468  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7469  "expected float values");
7470  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinimumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7471  break;
7472  case CombiningKind::MAXSI:
7473  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7474  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaxSIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7475  break;
7476  case CombiningKind::MINSI:
7477  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7478  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinSIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7479  break;
7480  case CombiningKind::MAXUI:
7481  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7482  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaxUIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7483  break;
7484  case CombiningKind::MINUI:
7485  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7486  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinUIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7487  break;
7488  case CombiningKind::MUL:
7489  if (t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex())
7490  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MulIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7491  else if (llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc))
7492  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MulFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7493  else
7494  llvm_unreachable("invalid value types for MUL reduction");
7495  break;
7496  case CombiningKind::OR:
7497  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7498  result = b.createOrFold<arith::OrIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7499  break;
7500  case CombiningKind::XOR:
7501  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7502  result = b.createOrFold<arith::XOrIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7503  break;
7504  };
7505 
7506  assert(result && "unknown CombiningKind");
7507  return selectPassthru(b, mask, result, acc);
7508 }
7509 
7510 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7511 // StepOp
7512 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7513 
7514 void StepOp::inferResultRanges(ArrayRef<ConstantIntRanges> argRanges,
7515  SetIntRangeFn setResultRanges) {
7516  auto resultType = cast<VectorType>(getType());
7517  if (resultType.isScalable()) {
7518  return;
7519  }
7520  unsigned bitwidth = ConstantIntRanges::getStorageBitwidth(resultType);
7521  APInt zero(bitwidth, 0);
7522  APInt high(bitwidth, resultType.getDimSize(0) - 1);
7523  ConstantIntRanges result = {zero, high, zero, high};
7524  setResultRanges(getResult(), result);
7525 }

7530 
7531 /// Create the vector.yield-ended region of a vector.mask op with `maskableOp`
7532 /// as masked operation.
7533 void mlir::vector::createMaskOpRegion(OpBuilder &builder,
7534  Operation *maskableOp) {
7535  assert(maskableOp->getBlock() && "MaskableOp must be inserted into a block");
7536  Block *insBlock = builder.getInsertionBlock();
7537  // Create a block and move the op to that block.
7538  insBlock->getOperations().splice(
7539  insBlock->begin(), maskableOp->getBlock()->getOperations(), maskableOp);
7540  YieldOp::create(builder, maskableOp->getLoc(), maskableOp->getResults());
7541 }
7542 
7543 /// Creates a vector.mask operation around a maskable operation. Returns the
7544 /// vector.mask operation if the mask provided is valid. Otherwise, returns
7545 /// the maskable operation itself.
7546 Operation *mlir::vector::maskOperation(OpBuilder &builder,
7547  Operation *maskableOp, Value mask,
7548  Value passthru) {
7549  if (!mask)
7550  return maskableOp;
7551  if (passthru)
7552  return MaskOp::create(builder, maskableOp->getLoc(),
7553  maskableOp->getResultTypes(), mask, passthru,
7554  maskableOp, createMaskOpRegion);
7555  return MaskOp::create(builder, maskableOp->getLoc(),
7556  maskableOp->getResultTypes(), mask, maskableOp,
7557  createMaskOpRegion);
7558 }
7559 
7560 /// Creates a vector select operation that picks values from `newValue` or
7561 /// `passthru` for each result vector lane based on `mask`. This utility is used
7562 /// to propagate the pass-thru value of vector.mask or for cases where only the
7563 /// pass-thru value propagation is needed. VP intrinsics do not support
7564 /// pass-thru values and every mask-out lane is set to poison. LLVM backends are
7565 /// usually able to match op + select patterns and fold them into a native
7566 /// target instructions.
7567 Value mlir::vector::selectPassthru(OpBuilder &builder, Value mask,
7568  Value newValue, Value passthru) {
7569  if (!mask)
7570  return newValue;
7571 
7572  return arith::SelectOp::create(builder, newValue.getLoc(), newValue.getType(),
7573  mask, newValue, passthru);
7574 }
